examples.question: Pavel has 30 square yards of orange field. There are 94 oranges per square yard. Pavel can harvest his oranges every 12 months. How many oranges can Pavel harvest within a year?
Rania saw a 210-foot whale with 7 72-inch remoras attached to it. What percentage of the whale's body length is the combined length of the remoras?

Sofia makes coffee using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in the ratio of 97:37. If she used a total of 1474 teaspoons of sugar and cups of water, calculate the number of teaspoonfuls of sugar she used.

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 50 minutes to cover every 77 miles of the city. If the city is 77 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover the whole city?
Luis is rolling a 4-sided die. How much more likely is it (expressed as a percentage) that he rolls a number greater than 2 than that he rolls two odd numbers in a row?
A juggler can juggle 640 balls. An eighth of the balls are tennis balls, and 1/10 of the tennis balls are white. How many white tennis balls are there?

A group of 190 students has various hobbies. 19 like to paint, 7 like to play football, and the rest like to either bake or hike. How many like to bake if the number that like to hike is twice the number that prefer playing football?

Zahra is popping popcorn for a snack. As the pan of kernels heats up, the kernels start popping faster. 60 pop in the first 30 seconds of cooking, then 4 times that amount in the next 30 seconds. The kernels increase to 6 times the initial popping rate in the next 30 seconds, but in the final 30 seconds, the popping slows down to half the rate as the past 30 seconds. After Zahra takes the pan off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 30 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. How many pieces of popcorn does Zahra have to eat?
To make a call from a hotel room phone, you must pay $0.9 for each minute of your call. After 20 minutes, that price drops to $0.5 per minute. How much would a 86-minute call cost?

When Mei watches her brother, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 71 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 45 stuffed animals inside. The tower of stacking rings has 29 multicolored rings on it. Mei recently bought a tube of bouncy balls, bringing her total number of toys for her brother up to 204. How many bouncy balls came in the tube?

A farmer is buying feed for his alpacas. He buys a variety of apples, wheats, cucumbers and oats. Since oats are a rare treat, he only buys five 3-kg boxes of them for the whole stable. He only wants enough cucumbers to feed the alpacas while the vegetables are fresh, so he buys thirteen 6-kg bags. Apples are the main diet of his alpacas, so he buys thirty one 42-kg packs. Wheats are a staple to supplement the apples, so he buys fifteen 15-kg sacks. If his farm truck can carry 180 kgs at a time, how many trips does the farmer need to transport all the feed?

Keisha and Andre have 109 minutes to walk to the gym together. It takes them 27 minutes to get to the corner where the cinema is. It takes them another 31 minutes to get to the bank. How much longer do they have to get to gym without being late?

Bodhi went to buy some school supplies. He bought 22 rulers which cost ¥4.5 each, 8 colored pencils which cost ¥14.0 each, and a rim of bond paper which cost ¥22. How much did Bodhi spend on everything?
Ravi places crackers on some trays. Each tray can hold 28 crackers. If he has 252 crackers and 7 trays, how many crackers won't he be able to place on the tray?

Pavel wants to make different sized ice cubes with 328 grams of water. He can make giant cubes that use 12 grams per cube, medium cubes that use 11 grams, and small cubes that use 1/5 of gram. If he makes 8 giant cubes, 15 small cubes, and 13 medium cubes, how many grams of water does he have left?

Mia walks 24 kilometers every day on her favorite walking trail, which includes 12 kilometers of walking on the beach and 12 kilometers of walking on the sidewalk. On the sidewalk, Mia walks at two times the rate of speed that she does on the beach. If 60 minutes of her walk is spent on the beach, how long does it take for her to complete the entire 24-kilometer walk, in minutes?
Liam picks 205 pineapples on Wednesday. Then he picks 97 pineapples on Thursday. On Friday, he picks quadruple the number of pineapples he did on Wednesday. How many pineapples does Liam have?

In a 150-item quiz, 60% of the questions are history, and the rest are equally divided as literature and chemistry questions. If Mia is sure to get 40% of the history questions, and 1/10 of the literature and chemistry questions correctly, how many points is she sure to get?

Amelia is knitting winter wear for her 2 grandchildren. They're twins, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a vest, shawl, beanie, socks, and leg warmers for each of them. It takes 17 skeins of wool to make a vest, 11 for a shawl, 18 for a beanie, 12 for a pair of socks, and 6 for a pair of leg warmers. How many skeins of wool will she need to buy?

Benjamin watches TV after he finishes his homework every night. On Tuesday and Wednesday, he watched a 4-hour episode of his favorite show each night. On Thursday, he watched a few episodes of a 45-minute show. On Friday, he finished homework early and watched a 6-hour episode and a 15-minute show. On Saturday, he got to stay up late, so he watched two 4-hour episodes. If he watched 23 hours of TV in all, how many 45-minute episodes did he watch on Thursday?
Jasmine's dog has 1000 puppies, 270 of which have spots. Priya's dog has 640 puppies, 140 of which have spots. What percentage of all the puppies have spots?

Emma was preparing for a game night at her house, where she intended to serve stuffed peppers. She noticed that she was out of plastic spoons, so she bought a new package of spoons. Later, her husband also bought a package of 18 new spoons and gave them to Emma. While Emma was making the stuffed peppers, she used ten of the spoons to sample her stuffed peppers. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 30 spoons. How many spoons were in the package that Emma bought?

Camila is an avid gardener. Two days ago, she received 29 new potted plants from her favorite plant nursery. She already has 7 potted plants on each of the 52 window ledges of her large country home. Feeling generous, she has decided that she will give 6 potted plants from each ledge to friends and family tomorrow. How many potted plants will Camila remain with?

In Mr. Smith's class of 35 students, 20% of the class are basketball players. Out of the remaining class, 25% of the students are dancers or part of robotics club members. These 3 groups of students will need to leave early today to travel to an away tournament. How many students are leaving early?
Pavel is 13 years old. In 3 years his sister Valentina will be 3 times as old as Pavel is now. How old is Valentina right now?

Kai is selling brownie and orange pie for a fundraiser. On Tuesday, he sold 21 boxes of brownie and 18 fewer boxes of orange pie, than on Wednesday. On Wednesday, he sold 13 more boxes of brownies than on Tuesday and 27 boxes of orange pie. If the brownie cost ¥8 and the orange pie cost ¥28, how much did Kai earn for two days?
Sanjay receives 150 emails a day. 32% of those emails don't require any response. Sanjay responds to the rest of them. How many emails does Sanjay respond to in a 6 day work week?

According to its nutritional info, a bag of breads has 475 calories per serving. If a 275 ounces bag has 5 servings, how many ounces can you eat if your daily calorie target is 2395 and you have already consumed 1350 calories?
Mateo and Santiago are currently 10 years apart in age. If Mateo, who is younger than Santiago, is 35 years old, what's the average of their ages?
A grandfather eats 6 tacos per day, his partner eats 3 tacos per day, and their son eats 6 tacos per day. How many tacos does this family eat in one week?

Mrs. Lee is looking for a townhouse that will not go beyond her $360000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $340000. On top of that, the buyer has to pay a brokerage fee which is 3% of the selling price, and also the transfer fee that is 10% of the selling price. How much more is the total price of the townhouse than Mrs. Lee's budget?

A clinic has a capacity of 1800 rooms with 1/4 occupied. Due to the natural disaster, 40 patients are admitted into the clinic each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied rooms in the clinic after 3 weeks.

Prof. Martinez sold his cottage for $880000. He paid the registration fees that amount to 3% of the selling price and also paid a agent fee that is 5% of the selling price. If he also paid $440000 for the remaining loan amount of the cottage, how much is Prof. Martinez's net proceeds from selling the cottage?
A lasagna has 30 pieces. If Nadia can eat 5 pieces a day while Leon can eat five times as much, how many days will the lasagna last?

Daphne and Uma are sisters from Singapore who love collecting signatures from politicians. During their winter break from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After 4 weeks, Daphne and Uma compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. Daphne has 35 signatures in her book, and Uma has 30. The sisters have 2 more weeks of winter break, and they decide they want to reach 120 signatures between them by the end of the break. How many signatures do the sisters need to collect to reach their goal?

Wei is raising money for a conference. He has applied for help from the local charity, which has decided to cover a fifth of the cost of the conference. How much money is Wei missing if he has ₣30 and the conference costs ₣210?
A stack is made out of 8 white tiles, thrice as many orange tiles, and an unknown number of green tiles. If there are 38 tiles in the stack in total, how many green tiles are there?
Yusuf has ₣102.5 and wants to buy 25 washers from a bin at the construction supply store. Each washer costs ₣0.98. How much money does Yusuf have left after paying for the washers?

Ava went to the cafe and bought various types of treats. She bought 1 dozen danishes which cost $17 per dozen, 8 dozen tarts which cost $74 per dozen, and 3 dozen scones for $113 per dozen. How much was the total cost?

Hiroshi goes to the store to buy some tea. The normal brand of tea he buys costs ₺20 per kilogram. He had to buy a more expensive brand that costs 45% more since his favorite brand was sold out. He decides to buy a week's worth of tea and he uses 1 kilogram of tea per day. He also decided to buy himself a bagel for ₺3. How much did everything cost?
A loaf of sourdough at the cafe costs €8. Muffins cost €4 each. How much more do 6 loaves of sourdough cost than 4 muffins?

Umar hid 6 dozen eggs in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Quinn finds 12 eggs. Isabella finds two times as many as Quinn. Mia finds 4 less than Isabella, and Nia finds a quarter as many as Mia. How many eggs are still hidden in the yard?

Oakwood High School is holding graduation in their Auditorium this year which has space for 7300 people. After accounting for 1200 seats for graduates and 100 seats for faculty attending, how many tickets would each graduate receive to give to their friends and family if the tickets are split equally?

A maintenance worker has to clean a university with 210 floors. They have 10 days to get it done. It takes them 20 minutes per floor. If they work 10 hours each day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning floors?

Bodhi went to their orchard to pick some strawberries and found 3/5 as many caterpillars as grasshoppers in the garden. If there were 25 grasshoppers, calculate the total number of insects in the garden.
There are 18 girls in the park. If there are two-thirds the number of boys in the park, how many kids are in the park?

Daphne went to the coast for vacation. Her parents gave her ₣1400 to buy whatever she wanted. At the seaside store, cotton candy was on sale for "Buy 15 pounds at ₣23 per pound, get 5 pounds 1/4 off." She scooped up 22 pounds. She also bought a mixed bag of coral pieces for ₣11.75 and 11 pins that were ₣21.0 each. How much money does Daphne have left?

Viktor has a plant stand at the town square. He sells three kinds of plants: tulips, roses and sunflowers. He usually sells tulips for €2.25 per bundle, roses for €5.13 per bundle and sunflowers for €5.47 per bundle. Viktor has no change today, so he has decided to round all his prices to the nearest dollar. If Viktor sells 12 bundles of tulips, 29 bundles of roses and 37 bundles of sunflowers, how much will he make?
Kayla can peel 6 mushrooms a minute and saute 40 mushrooms in 17 minutes. How long will it take her to peel and saute 120 mushrooms?
Oliver scored 354 points in one game of darts. Camila scored 42 points more than two-fourths as many as Oliver. How many points did Oliver and Camila have in total?
The area of Diego's rectangular kitchen is 390 square meters. If the length of his room is 5 meters, what is the perimeter of the room in meters?
Qasim has 5 ₣50 bills. He buys 6 coloring books for ₣8 each. He also buys 5 packs of trading cards for ₣4 each. How much money does he have left?
Yara sliced a whole kiwi into 31 pieces. She ate 4 slices, her sister ate 6 more than her, and her cousin ate 3 more than her sister. How many slices of kiwi did they all eat?

One troll can mine 5 kgs of ore per day with basic shovel. He can mine twice as much with a bronze pickaxe and 60% more with a titanium pickaxe than with a bronze pickaxe. How many kgs of ore can 20 trolls with titanium pickaxes mine in a month with 31 days?
A carton of lemonade is 13 ozs of lemonade. Pavel drinks 4 cartons of lemonade. If lemonade has 8 calories per oz how many calories did he consume?

Gabrielle is learning to write and decides to keep re-writing the alphabet until she knows it. She writes it in full two times, writes two-fourths of it once, then re-writes everything she has already written. How many letters has Gabrielle written in total?

Viktor has 18 tubes of black paint and 16 tubes of magenta paint. Alejandro has 1/3 as many tubes of black paint as Viktor, and eight times as many tubes of magenta paint as Viktor. How many tubes of paint does Alejandro have?
A student has 20 marbles. His sister has 5 fewer marbles than he has. How many marbles do they have together?
In a set of artist's cards, there are 30 purple cards, and 50% more yellow cards. Blue cards are as many as the sum of purple and yellow cards. How many cards of all mentioned colors are there?

Sanjay works a 7-hour shift each day, 3 days a week. He earns ₺17 per hour and gets a ₺582 bonus each week if the company performs well. How much money did Sanjay make in June if the company performed very well for the whole month?

Umar collects garbage from 3 different apartment complexes. The first 2 have 450 apartments each and the last one is 20% bigger than the other 2 combined. Umar collects garbage 2 times a week from each place and he gets paid ₣0.45 per collection for each apartment. How much money does he make in a week?

Beatriz has 9 jars of chocolate chips in her storage room. Each jar of chocolate chips can decorate 11 muffins. Beatriz wants to bake enough muffins to use up all of her chocolate chips. If each rack holds 11 muffins, how many racks worth of muffins should she bake?

I have 18 liters of peach drink that are 2/3 water and I wish to add it to 21 liters of grape drink that is two-thirds water. But as I pour it, I spill 3 liters of the peach drink. How much water is in the remaining 36 liters?

Mohammed has a bag of pebbles with 62 inside. He tripped over root while carrying it and dropped 2/4 of them. He scrambled to search for them but only came up with 18. When he went back home, he inspected the pebbles further. Five of them he picked up weren't pebbles, but actually beads so he got rid of it. How many pebbles did Mohammed end up with?

Elena is trying to decide whether to do her business accounting herself or hire one bookkeeper. If she does it herself, she'll be able to do 7 fewer hours of contract work, losing ¥42/hour in missed income. The bookkeeper charges ¥78. How much more money will she have if she hires the bookkeeper?

On Tuesday, Ibrahim wants to exercise for seven times the amount of time he did on Monday and Sunday combined. On Sunday he exercised for 23 minutes. On Monday he exercised for 55 minutes. How many minutes does he have to exercise on Tuesday to reach his goal?
Aisha has 47 light white spools of thread, 73 dark white spools of thread, 32 light brown spools of thread, and 88 dark brown spools of thread. What percent of the spools are white?
A painter works for 2 weeks every month and for 6 days every week. If he gets paid ₣150 every day, how much does he earn if he works for a year?

It takes Sakura 28 minutes to finish a brain teaser and 4 minutes to finish a chess puzzle. Over the vacation she solved 4 brain teasers and 7 chess puzzles. How much time did she spend playing these games?

Yuki is feeding his livestock hay. Each alpaca needs 9 kg, and each horse needs 6 kg less than twice the amount each alpaca needs. If there are 35 alpacas and 22 horses, how many kg of hay does Yuki need?

Comet Hyakutake orbits the sun every 75 years. Diego's uncle saw the Comet when he was 46 years old. Diego saw the comet a second time when he was two times the age his uncle was when he saw the Comet. How old was Diego when he saw the Comet for the first time?

Valentina has a flower bed that is 217 meters long. Valentina wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Valentina's flowers grow 3 meters wide so she needs to leave 15.5 meters between every plant. Valentina already owns 11 flowers. Each flowering plant costs €14 at the store, how much money will Valentina spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?
Leilani is required to submit a 160-page thesis. She already finished writing one-fifth of the thesis. How many pages does she have left to write?

There are 172 fourth-graders at Pine Valley School. 83 of them are girls. On Thursday, 3 fourth-grade girls and 4 fourth-grade boys were absent. How many fourth grade boys were at Pine Valley School on Thursday?

There are currently 19 red balls, 29 green balls, and 48 yellow balls in the shop. Red balls cost ¥13, yellow balls cost ¥6, and green balls cost ¥7. How much will the shop have received after all the balls are sold?

Mateo's van breaks down. The van weighs 2000 kilograms and he has groceries in it weighing 250 kilograms. He also has his 2 young friends who weigh 75 kilograms each in it. If the force to move the van is 3% of the weight, how much force does he need to push the van?
Elena finished 1/3 of a 315 piece puzzle, and then started and finished another 481 piece puzzle within an hour. How many puzzle pieces did Elena place during that hour?
At the beginning of the conference, there were 63 nurses and 63 engineers. After 45 minutes, 1/2 of the total number of people left. How many engineers are left if 22 nurses stayed at the conference?
The Charity fundraiser team hid 180 coins. The Lopez twins each found 43 coins. All the other coins except 17 were found by their friends. How many coins did the friends find?

Wei caught 4 trouts last Sunday, the first trout he caught weighs 70 kilograms, the second trout he caught weighs 33 kilograms, and the last trout he caught weighs 32 kilograms. If a kilogram of trout costs €1.0, how much will he earn after selling all the trouts to the market?

Diego was a pen pal with 7 people. He stopped being penpals with 3 of them. They each send 3 letters a week that are 9 pages long. He responds in kind. He can write a page every 5 minutes. How many hours does he spend writing a week?

The Jones family is busy making brownies. So far, they've made 7000 brownies. They have 1027 lemon brownies, 2009 strawberry brownies, and some peanut butter brownies. How many peanut butter brownies have they made?
If Kai and Mateo have 860 yards of fence between them, and they agree to split it with Mateo getting 100 yards more than Kai, how much is left over for Kai?
Kayla buys 10 shares of a stock for €56 each. The stock price increases 30% the first year Kayla holds it, then decreases 25% in the second year. What is the final value of all Kayla's shares?
Amelia has three times as many LinkedIn friends as Zahra. Mei has ten times as many friends on LinkedIn as Zahra. If Amelia has 45 friends on LinkedIn, how many LinkedIn friends does Mei have?

Nadia qualified for a spot on the swimming team, so she went shopping for some athletic gear. She bought a jersey for $21, a pair of swimming leggings for $4 more than the jersey cost, and a pair of cleats that were originally $32 but were on sale for one-eighth price. She had a coupon for $3 off the package of $9 athletic headbands that she also bought. How much did she spend on athletic gear?
Kai hires a luxury car from 1 PM to 5 PM. He gets 2 hours free. The first paid hour is $10 and each hour after that is twice the cost. How much did he pay?

The biggest waterslide at Neptunes Kingdom is 330 meters long, and people slide down at 55 meters/minute. The second biggest waterslide is 240 meters long, but steeper, so people slide down at 80 meters/minute. How much longer does it take to ride the biggest slide compared to the second biggest slide?

1000 people apply for a job at Amazon. Of the people that apply, only 40% receive interviews. Of those who receive interviews, 49% receive a job offer. Of those who receive a job offer, two-fourths of the people accept the position. How many people accept the position?

There are 6 periods in the day for a normal student but Liam has to take 1 extra classes. Each class is 60 minutes long. He goes to class for 6 days a week. He then spends 1/7 of his weekly minutes each on Saturday and Sunday as extra learning time. How many hours a week does he spend learning?

There are 15 students playing football and two times that number playing badminton. There are 19 boys and 28 girls playing table tennis. If each student only participates in one group, how many students are there in total?

When the water is cold Wei swims a mile in 26 minutes. When the water is warm Wei swims a mile in 5 minutes more than twice as long. How much longer does Wei take to swim 6 miles on a hot day than a cold day?

Nia operates the cash register exactly three times as fast as her less-experienced colleague Sakura. Daily, Sakura processes 55 customers. What is the total weekly production for the two if they work all days of the week?

Keisha can run eight times faster than she can walk, but she can skip at a rate of speed that is 3/4 as fast as she can run. If she can skip at 3 miles per hour, how many miles can she travel in 8 hours if she spends one-half of the time running and 1/2 of the time walking?

Jin slew 150 goblins with his mighty sword, while DeShawn, using a spear, slew five-sixths as many goblins as Jin. Using a rusty iron axe, Gabriel slew two times as many goblins as DeShawn. But Oscar, having forgotten his sword at home, slew three-sixths as many goblins as Gabriel using a nail file. How many goblins has Oscar slain?
A new virus infects 16 people. Every day, each infected person infects 3 others. How many people are infected after 3 days?

Mia's aunt said that she had ₺300 budgeted for her birthday party. She wants to make sure she and her friends all get to play one round of laser tag, have ₺5 in pinball tokens, and get to ride the roller coaster seven times. A round of laser tag is ₺10. The roller coaster cost ₺5 a ride. How many friends can she invite?
If Nia eats 5 eggs a day for 84 days and then increases it to 7 eggs a day for 24 days, how many dozens of eggs will Nia need for 108 days?
The vending machines sell cookies for 50 cents and pretzels for 75 cents. Jamal spent $1200 and got 6 bags of cookies and had 7% of his money left in change. How many pretzels did he buy?

At Kai's house, there are seven times as many apples as bananas. He has a total of 53 bananas in his house. Kai bought 60 more bananas at the store and 36 fewer apples than the number of bananas. Find the combined total of the number of apples and bananas Kai has in the house?

A group of 54 students has various hobbies. 35 like to dance, 2 like to play badminton, and the rest like to either paint or bake. How many like to paint if the number that like to bake is twice the number that prefer playing badminton?

Uma makes tea using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in the ratio of 164:78. If she used a total of 726 teaspoons of sugar and cups of water, calculate the number of teaspoonfuls of sugar she used.
Olivia saw a 10-foot dolphin with 8 3-inch remoras attached to it. What percentage of the dolphin's body length is the combined length of the remoras?

Isabella is popping popcorn for a snack. As the pan of kernels heats up, the kernels start popping faster. 20 pop in the first 18 seconds of cooking, then 3 times that amount in the next 18 seconds. The kernels increase to 4 times the initial popping rate in the next 18 seconds, but in the final 18 seconds, the popping slows down to half the rate as the past 18 seconds. After Isabella takes the pan off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 18 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. How many pieces of popcorn does Isabella have to eat?

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 176 minutes to cover every 35 miles of the city. If the city is 70 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover the whole city?
A juggler can juggle 420 balls. Half of the balls are tennis balls, and 1/3 of the tennis balls are teal. How many teal tennis balls are there?

Liam wants to make different sized ice cubes with 334 ounces of water. He can make giant cubes that use 12 ounces per cube, medium cubes that use 11 ounces, and small cubes that use 2/4 of ounce. If he makes 8 giant cubes, 24 small cubes, and 12 medium cubes, how many ounces of water does he have left?

When Ava watches her cousin, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 74 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 42 stuffed animals inside. The tower of stacking rings has 32 multicolored rings on it. Ava recently bought a tube of bouncy balls, bringing her total number of toys for her cousin up to 189. How many bouncy balls came in the tube?

A farmer is buying feed for his pigs. He buys a variety of wheats, hay, beets and oats. Since oats are a rare treat, he only buys four 4-pound boxes of them for the whole stable. He only wants enough beets to feed the pigs while the vegetables are fresh, so he buys twelve 8-pound bags. Wheats are the main diet of his pigs, so he buys thirty two 37-pound packs. Hay are a staple to supplement the wheats, so he buys nineteen 16-pound sacks. If his farm truck can carry 200 pounds at a time, how many trips does the farmer need to transport all the feed?

Benjamin has 75 square yards of pomegranate field. There are 77 pomegranates per square yard. Benjamin can harvest his pomegranates every 12 months. How many pomegranates can Benjamin harvest within a year?
Arash places olives on some plates. Each plate can hold 26 olives. If he has 321 olives and 12 plates, how many olives won't he be able to place on the plate?

Thiago and Sakura have 107 minutes to walk to the bank together. It takes them 19 minutes to get to the corner where the gym is. It takes them another 21 minutes to get to the cinema. How much longer do they have to get to bank without being late?

Daphne walks 28 kilometers every day on her favorite walking trail, which includes 16 kilometers of walking on the beach and 12 kilometers of walking on the sidewalk. On the sidewalk, Daphne walks at three times the rate of speed that she does on the beach. If 64 minutes of her walk is spent on the beach, how long does it take for her to complete the entire 28-kilometer walk, in minutes?
Qasim's dog has 1000 puppies, 230 of which have spots. Ibrahim's dog has 520 puppies, 150 of which have spots. What percentage of all the puppies have spots?

Ibrahim is selling brownie and banana pie for a fundraiser. On Friday, he sold 26 boxes of brownie and 11 fewer boxes of banana pie, than on Saturday. On Saturday, he sold 11 more boxes of brownies than on Friday and 29 boxes of banana pie. If the brownie cost ₺10 and the banana pie cost ₺32, how much did Ibrahim earn for two days?

Arash went to buy some school supplies. He bought 18 colored pencils which cost ¥5.5 each, 8 pencils which cost ¥16.25 each, and a rim of bond paper which cost ¥24. How much did Arash spend on everything?
To make a call from a hotel room phone, you must pay ₣0.6 for each minute of your call. After 15 minutes, that price drops to ₣0.5 per minute. How much would a 51-minute call cost?
Carlos is rolling a twelve-sided die. How much more likely is it (expressed as a percentage) that he rolls a number greater than 3 than that he rolls two odd numbers in a row?

Jasmine is an avid gardener. Two days ago, she received 23 new potted plants from her favorite plant nursery. She already has 11 potted plants on each of the 58 window ledges of her large country home. Feeling generous, she has decided that she will give 3 potted plants from each ledge to friends and family tomorrow. How many potted plants will Jasmine remain with?

Ananya was preparing for a lunch party at her house, where she intended to serve grilled salmon. She noticed that she was out of plastic forks, so she bought a new package of forks. Later, her husband also bought a package of 10 new forks and gave them to Ananya. While Ananya was making the grilled salmon, she used eight of the forks to sample her grilled salmon. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 31 forks. How many forks were in the package that Ananya bought?
Kai picks 194 apricots on Sunday. Then he picks 212 apricots on Monday. On Tuesday, he picks triple the number of apricots he did on Sunday. How many apricots does Kai have?

In Mrs. Garcia's class of 125 students, 40% of the class are swimmers. Out of the remaining class, 32% of the students are debate team members or part of choir members. These 3 groups of students will need to leave early today to travel to an away meet. How many students are leaving early?

According to its nutritional info, a bag of breads has 450 calories per serving. If a 100 ounces bag has 5 servings, how many ounces can you eat if your daily calorie target is 1905 and you have already consumed 1725 calories?
Nadia receives 100 emails a day. 16% of those emails don't require any response. Nadia responds to the rest of them. How many emails does Nadia respond to in a 4 day work week?
Mateo is 24 years old. In 6 years his sister Olga will be 3 times as old as Mateo is now. How old is Olga right now?

Aisha is knitting winter wear for her 2 grandchildren. They're twins, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a shawl, hat, beanie, mittens, and leg warmers for each of them. It takes 14 skeins of wool to make a shawl, 18 for a hat, 11 for a beanie, 13 for a pair of mittens, and 17 for a pair of leg warmers. How many skeins of wool will she need to buy?

In a 40-item quiz, 25% of the questions are biology, and the rest are equally divided as geography and geometry questions. If Sophia is sure to get 30% of the biology questions, and a tenth of the geography and geometry questions correctly, how many points is she sure to get?
Winnie has ¥82.3 and wants to buy 22 nuts from a bin at the home improvement store. Each nut costs ¥0.65. How much money does Winnie have left after paying for the nuts?
Arash and Amelia are currently 16 years apart in age. If Arash, who is younger than Amelia, is 15 years old, what's the average of their ages?

Luca watches TV after he finishes his homework every night. On Sunday and Monday, he watched a 4-hour episode of his favorite show each night. On Tuesday, he watched a few episodes of a 15-minute show. On Wednesday, he finished homework early and watched a 4-hour episode and a 45-minute show. On Thursday, he got to stay up late, so he watched two 3-hour episodes. If he watched 19 hours of TV in all, how many 15-minute episodes did he watch on Tuesday?
A father eats 7 pizzas per day, his wife eats 5 pizzas per day, and their daughter eats 4 pizzas per day. How many pizzas does this family eat in one week?

Uma and Gabrielle are sisters from Amsterdam who love collecting signatures from musicians. During their spring break from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After 4 weeks, Uma and Gabrielle compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. Uma has 22 signatures in her book, and Gabrielle has 43. The sisters have 3 more weeks of spring break, and they decide they want to reach 140 signatures between them by the end of the break. How many signatures do the sisters need to collect to reach their goal?

A care facility has a capacity of 1900 rooms with 2/5 occupied. Due to the pandemic, 80 patients are admitted into the care facility each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied rooms in the care facility after 2 weeks.

Mrs. Smith is looking for a house that will not go beyond her $330000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $300000. On top of that, the buyer has to pay a brokerage fee which is 6% of the selling price, and also the transfer fee that is 12% of the selling price. How much more is the total price of the house than Mrs. Smith's budget?
A cake has 30 portions. If Tara can eat 2 portions a day while Kimia can eat twice as much, how many days will the cake last?

Mr. Brown sold his villa for $880000. He paid the transfer fees that amount to 3% of the selling price and also paid a brokerage fee that is 4% of the selling price. If he also paid $270000 for the remaining loan amount of the villa, how much is Mr. Brown's net proceeds from selling the villa?

Theo is raising money for a music festival. He has applied for help from the youth club, which has decided to cover 1/2 of the cost of the music festival. How much money is Theo missing if he has ¥115 and the music festival costs ¥590?
A loaf of bread at the store costs €8. Croissants cost €2 each. How much more do 5 loaves of bread cost than 3 croissants?

A janitor has to clean a office building with 120 floors. They have 10 days to get it done. It takes them 20 minutes per floor. If they work 8 hours each day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning floors?
Priya went to their backyard to pick some cherries and found five-sixths as many bees as wasps in the field. If there were 72 wasps, calculate the total number of insects in the field.
There are 12 girls in the field. If there are seven times the number of boys in the field, how many kids are in the field?

Sakura went to the patisserie and bought various types of baked goods. She bought 1 dozen croissants which cost $15 per dozen, 5 dozen macarons which cost $83 per dozen, and 3 dozen brownies for $116 per dozen. How much was the total cost?

Esteban goes to the store to buy some rice. The normal brand of rice he buys costs ₣20 per kg. He had to buy a more expensive brand that costs 30% more since his favorite brand was sold out. He decides to buy a week's worth of rice and he uses 2 kg of rice per day. He also decided to buy himself a cookie for ₣2. How much did everything cost?
A stack is made out of 3 purple tiles, six times as many green tiles, and an unknown number of black tiles. If there are 42 tiles in the stack in total, how many black tiles are there?

Ananya hid 5 dozen eggs in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Theo finds 10 eggs. Faisal finds twice as many as Theo. Keisha finds 4 less than Faisal, and Rania finds 1/2 as many as Keisha. How many eggs are still hidden in the yard?

Bodhi collects garbage from 3 different apartment complexes. The first 2 have 200 apartments each and the last one is 60% bigger than the other 2 combined. Bodhi collects garbage 2 times a week from each place and he gets paid ¥0.3 per collection for each apartment. How much money does he make in a week?

Greenville High School is holding graduation in their Convention Center this year which has space for 8400 people. After accounting for 900 seats for graduates and 300 seats for faculty attending, how many tickets would each graduate receive to give to their friends and family if the tickets are split equally?

Roya went to the beach for vacation. Her parents gave her ₣1300 to buy whatever she wanted. At the souvenir store, fudge was on sale for "Buy 15 kgs at ₣22 per kg, get 4 kgs 1/2 off." She scooped up 21 kgs. She also bought a mixed bag of sand dollars for ₣11.5 and 17 postcards that were ₣20.5 each. How much money does Roya have left?
Valentina can peel 8 clams a minute and saute 20 clams in 5 minutes. How long will it take her to peel and saute 120 clams?
The area of Arjun's rectangular office is 684 square feet. If the length of his room is 6 yards, what is the perimeter of the room in feet?

Oscar has a flower stand at the community market. He sells three kinds of flowers: daisies, sunflowers and orchids. He usually sells daisies for ₺1.92 per basket, sunflowers for ₺3.83 per basket and orchids for ₺5.16 per basket. Oscar has no change today, so he has decided to round all his prices to the nearest dollar. If Oscar sells 6 baskets of daisies, 15 baskets of sunflowers and 40 baskets of orchids, how much will he make?
A carton of sparkling water is 9 ounces of sparkling water. Thiago drinks 5 cartons of sparkling water. If sparkling water has 2 calories per ounce how many calories did he consume?

Mateo has 6 tubes of purple paint and 14 tubes of orange paint. Alejandro has two-thirds as many tubes of purple paint as Mateo, and five times as many tubes of orange paint as Mateo. How many tubes of paint does Alejandro have?
Leon has 8 $50 bills. He buys 7 toy cars for $3 each. He also buys 4 packs of stickers for $1 each. How much money does he have left?
Kayla sliced a whole mango into 30 pieces. She ate 4 slices, her brother ate 6 more than her, and her cousin ate 4 more than her brother. How many slices of mango did they all eat?
Yara scored 315 points in one game of archery. Bodhi scored 27 points more than four-fifths as many as Yara. How many points did Yara and Bodhi have in total?

One troll can mine 5 kgs of ore per day with wooden pickaxe. He can mine two times as much with a silver pickaxe and 40% more with a titanium pickaxe than with a silver pickaxe. How many kgs of ore can 25 trolls with titanium pickaxes mine in a month with 28 days?
In a set of magician's cards, there are 28 green cards, and 50% more purple cards. Yellow cards are as many as the sum of green and purple cards. How many cards of all mentioned colors are there?

Olivia is learning to write and decides to keep re-writing the hiragana (with 48 letters) until she knows it. She writes it in full three times, writes four-sixths of it once, then re-writes everything she has already written. How many letters has Olivia written in total?
A boy has 14 stickers. His brother has 5 fewer stickers than he has. How many stickers do they have together?
Ava has 58 light black spools of thread, 124 dark black spools of thread, 66 light turquoise spools of thread, and 77 dark turquoise spools of thread. What percent of the spools are black?

Jasmine has 7 jars of icing in her kitchen cabinet. Each jar of icing can decorate 16 brownies. Jasmine wants to bake enough brownies to use up all of her icing. If each baking sheet holds 14 brownies, how many baking sheets worth of brownies should she bake?

Gabriel has a bag of coins with 94 inside. He tripped over rock while carrying it and dropped three-sixths of them. He scrambled to search for them but only came up with 11. When he went back home, he inspected the coins further. Six of them he picked up weren't coins, but actually buttons so he got rid of it. How many coins did Gabriel end up with?

Ibrahim's truck breaks down. The truck weighs 1350 pounds and he has equipment in it weighing 200 pounds. He also has his 4 young colleagues who weigh 75 pounds each in it. If the force to move the truck is 2% of the weight, how much force does he need to push the truck?

Keisha has a flower bed that is 162 feet long. Keisha wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Keisha's flowers grow 5 feet wide so she needs to leave 13.5 feet between every plant. Keisha already owns 11 flowers. Each flowering plant costs $12 at the store, how much money will Keisha spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?

Ali works a 6-hour shift each day, 3 days a week. He earns ¥11 per hour and gets a ¥432 bonus each week if the company performs well. How much money did Ali make in July if the company performed very well for the whole month?

I have 9 liters of apple drink that are 1/2 water and I wish to add it to 18 liters of mango drink that is four-sixths water. But as I pour it, I spill 5 liters of the apple drink. How much water is in the remaining 22 liters?

On Wednesday, Nadia wants to exercise for four times the amount of time he did on Tuesday and Monday combined. On Monday he exercised for 43 minutes. On Tuesday he exercised for 45 minutes. How many minutes does he have to exercise on Wednesday to reach his goal?

It takes Camila 8 minutes to finish a jigsaw puzzle and 6 minutes to finish a word puzzle. Over the day off she solved 4 jigsaw puzzles and 10 word puzzles. How much time did she spend playing these games?

Amelia is trying to decide whether to do her taxes herself or hire one accountant. If she does it herself, she'll be able to do 4 fewer hours of freelance work, losing €65/hour in missed income. The accountant charges €89. How much more money will she have if she hires the accountant?

Comet Hale-Bopp orbits the sun every 55 years. Yusuf's father saw the Comet when he was 24 years old. Yusuf saw the comet a second time when he was three times the age his father was when he saw the Comet. How old was Yusuf when he saw the Comet for the first time?
A carpenter works for 4 weeks every month and for 5 days every week. If he gets paid ¥40 every day, how much does he earn if he works for a year?

There are 94 second-graders at Sunny Hill School. 73 of them are girls. On Tuesday, 8 second-grade girls and 5 second-grade boys were absent. How many second grade boys were at Sunny Hill School on Tuesday?

There are currently 11 orange balls, 27 green balls, and 48 purple balls in the shop. Orange balls cost ₺6, purple balls cost ₺2, and green balls cost ₺4. How much will the shop have received after all the balls are sold?

Andre is feeding his livestock silage. Each donkey needs 12 kg, and each cow needs 9 kg less than twice the amount each donkey needs. If there are 20 donkeys and 17 cows, how many kg of silage does Andre need?
Elena is required to submit a 272-page thesis. She already finished writing 2/4 of the thesis. How many pages does she have left to write?
Sanjay finished 2/3 of a 363 piece puzzle, and then started and finished another 471 piece puzzle within an hour. How many puzzle pieces did Sanjay place during that hour?

The Johnson family is busy making muffins. So far, they've made 7550 muffins. They have 1705 blueberry muffins, 1655 strawberry muffins, and some vanilla muffins. How many vanilla muffins have they made?

Andre caught 6 cods last Sunday, the first cod he caught weighs 54 kgs, the second cod he caught weighs 46 kgs, and the last cod he caught weighs 23 kgs. If a kg of cod costs €2.0, how much will he earn after selling all the cods to the market?
The Treasure hunt team hid 200 balls. The Lopez twins each found 11 balls. All the other balls except 12 were found by their friends. How many balls did the friends find?
If Quinn and Amelia have 620 meters of fence between them, and they agree to split it with Amelia getting 140 meters more than Quinn, how much is left over for Quinn?
Beatriz buys 10 shares of a stock for ₺25 each. The stock price increases 10% the first year Beatriz holds it, then decreases 20% in the second year. What is the final value of all Beatriz's shares?

Diego was a pen pal with 11 people. He stopped being penpals with 4 of them. They each send 4 letters a week that are 6 pages long. He responds in kind. He can write a page every 5 minutes. How many hours does he spend writing a week?

The biggest waterslide at Splash World is 300 yards long, and people slide down at 50 yards/minute. The second biggest waterslide is 240 yards long, but steeper, so people slide down at 60 yards/minute. How much longer does it take to ride the biggest slide compared to the second biggest slide?

Jasmine can run five times faster than she can walk, but she can skip at a rate of speed that is 3/5 as fast as she can run. If she can skip at 6 miles per hour, how many miles can she travel in 6 hours if she spends 2/4 of the time running and three-sixths of the time walking?

Mei qualified for a spot on the swimming team, so she went shopping for some athletic gear. She bought a jersey for $22, a pair of swimming leggings for $9 more than the jersey cost, and a pair of cleats that were originally $78 but were on sale for two-fourths price. She had a coupon for $4 off the package of $12 athletic headbands that she also bought. How much did she spend on athletic gear?

There are 6 periods in the day for a normal student but Umar has to take 3 extra classes. Each class is 55 minutes long. He goes to class for 6 days a week. He then spends one-half of his weekly minutes each on Saturday and Sunday as extra learning time. How many hours a week does he spend learning?
Gabriel hires a party bus from 7 PM to 11 PM. He gets 1 hours free. The first paid hour is €16 and each hour after that is twice the cost. How much did he pay?
Bodhi has twice as many Twitter friends as Roya. Priya has eight times as many friends on Twitter as Roya. If Bodhi has 32 friends on Twitter, how many Twitter friends does Priya have?

800 people apply for a job at Netflix. Of the people that apply, only 30% receive interviews. Of those who receive interviews, 40% receive a job offer. Of those who receive a job offer, one-eighth of the people accept the position. How many people accept the position?

Kai slew 350 ogres with his mighty sword, while Jin, using a spear, slew 2/5 as many ogres as Kai. Using a rusty iron axe, Qasim slew eight times as many ogres as Jin. But Benjamin, having forgotten his sword at home, slew 1/10 as many ogres as Qasim using a nail file. How many ogres has Benjamin slain?

Isabella's dad said that she had €260 budgeted for her birthday party. She wants to make sure she and her friends all get to play one round of mini-golf, have €10 in arcade tokens, and get to ride the go-karts two times. A round of mini-golf is €4. The go-karts cost €6 a ride. How many friends can she invite?

There are 5 students playing volleyball and thrice that number playing football. There are 24 boys and 16 girls playing basketball. If each student only participates in one group, how many students are there in total?

When the water is cold Gabriel swims a mile in 12 minutes. When the water is warm Gabriel swims a mile in 8 minutes more than thrice as long. How much longer does Gabriel take to swim 3 miles on a hot day than a cold day?
If Beatriz eats 3 eggs a day for 20 days and then increases it to 6 eggs a day for 66 days, how many dozens of eggs will Beatriz need for 86 days?

Kimia operates the cash register exactly seven times as fast as her less-experienced colleague Olivia. Daily, Olivia processes 36 customers. What is the total weekly production for the two if they work all days of the week?
At the beginning of the party, there were 74 artists and 54 teachers. After half an hour, 1/8 of the total number of people left. How many teachers are left if 31 artists stayed at the party?

At Xavier's house, there are eight times as many bananas as oranges. He has a total of 28 oranges in his house. Xavier bought 63 more oranges at the store and 26 fewer bananas than the number of oranges. Find the combined total of the number of bananas and oranges Xavier has in the house?
The vending machines sell popcorn for 75 cents and cookies for 125 cents. Mateo spent ₺1200 and got 9 bags of popcorn and had 6% of his money left in change. How many cookies did he buy?
A new bacteria infects 20 people. Every day, each infected person infects 5 others. How many people are infected after 3 days?

A group of 290 students has various hobbies. 12 like to paint, 8 like to play chess, 13 like to swim, 39 like to play cricket, and the rest like to either play video games or hike. What percentage of the students like to play video games if the number of the students that like to hike is 5 less than two times the number that prefer playing cricket?

Gabriel is rolling a d4 die. How much more likely is it (expressed as a difference in percentage points) that he rolls a number greater than 1 twice in a row, than that he rolls four odd numbers in a row?

Andre is popping popcorn for a snack. As the pot of kernels heats up, the kernels start popping faster. 80 pop in the first 10 seconds of cooking, then 4 times that amount in the next 10 seconds. The kernels increase to 6 times the initial popping rate in the next 10 seconds. In the final 10 seconds, the popping slows down to half the rate as the past 10 seconds. After Andre takes the pot off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 10 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. Andre gives 1/10 of the made popcorn to his brother Jin. How many more pieces of popcorn does Andre have to eat than his brother?

Hiroshi has 20 hectares of apricot field. There are 28 apricots per two-fourths of a hectare. Hiroshi can harvest his apricots every 6 months. In addition, Hiroshi owns a 12-hectare grape field that produces 14 grapes per hectare. The grapes can be harvested every 4 months. In the span of two years, how many more apricots does Hiroshi harvest than grapes?

A farmer is buying feed for his cows. He buys a variety of apples, hay, cucumbers and corn. Since corn are a rare treat, he only buys four 6-pound boxes of them for the whole stable. He only wants enough cucumbers to feed the cows while the vegetables are fresh, so he buys fourteen 8-pound bags. Apples are the main diet of his cows, so he buys thirty five 42-pound packs. Hay are a staple to supplement the apples, so he buys eighteen 18-pound sacks. Finally, he buys 43 pounds of groceries, and 27 pounds of tools, and 100 pounds of wood. A farm truck can carry 140 pounds at a time. If the farmer has three trucks, how many trips does the farmer need to transport all the purchased items?

Olivia makes tea using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in a ratio of 51:5. She also uses 7 tablespoons of milk for every 5 cups of water, and uses 2 tablespoons of heavy cream for every teaspoon of sugar. She used a total of 220 teaspoons of sugar, cups of water, tablespoons of cream, and tablespoons of milk. How many teaspoons of sugar did she use?

When Sofia watches her brother, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 33 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 5 stuffed animals inside. The number of action figures in the action figure pack is twice the number of blocks and stuffed animals combined. The crayon box has 12 different colors of crayon, and the sticker book has 9 pages, each with 13 stickers. The tower of stacking rings has 28 multicolored rings on it. Sofia recently bought a tube of bouncy balls, bringing her total number of items for her brother up to 320. How many bouncy balls came in the tube?

A juggler can juggle 480 balls. A tenth of the balls are golf balls, and the rest are tennis balls. 1/2 of the golf balls are purple, of which 1/6 are marked. 1/9 of the tennis balls are indigo, and all except a third of those indigo balls are marked. How many marked balls are there in total?

Yara saw a 32-foot whale with 16 remoras, each 12 inches long attached to it. Then, 1/2 of the remoras swam away. Later, Yara saw another 10-foot whale with 6 remoras, each 8 inches long, attached to it. On average, what percentage of each whale's body length is covered by the remoras?

To make a call from a phone booth, you must pay $0.7 for each minute of your call. After 10 minutes, the price drops to $0.5 per minute. After 30 minutes from the start of the call, the price drops even more to $0.1 per two minutes. If your total bill is more than $15, you get a 15% discount on your total bill. How much would a 90-minute call cost?

Gabriel places almonds on plates and bowls. Each plate can hold 20 almonds while each bowl can hold four times that. Gabriel has 675 almonds, 9 plates and 3 bowls. Unfortunately, 2 bowls break. Gabriel then eats one-fifth of all the almonds. How many more plates does Gabriel need so he can place all the remaining almonds?

Luca wants to make different sized ice cubes with 337 ounces of water. He can make giant cubes that use 14 ounces per cube, medium cubes that use 3 ounces, small cubes that use 1/2 of a ounce, and tiny cubes that are half the size of small cubes. He makes 47 total ice cubes, including 9 giant cubes, 14 small cubes, 12 medium cubes, and some tiny cubes. How many ounces of water does Luca have left?

Mateo's dog has 149 puppies, 25 of which have spots. Mohammed's dog has 49 puppies, 12 of which have spots. Ibrahim has 54 dogs, each having 13 puppies with spots. After a visit to the vet, Mateo discovered that half of his unspotted puppies actually have spots that were not visible before. What percentage of all the puppies have spots?

Fatima and Mei have 247 minutes to walk to the gym together starting from their home. It takes them 26 minutes to get to the corner where the library is. It takes them another 18 minutes to get to the grocery store. When they reach the grocery store, they remember they forgot their wallets at home, so they have to return to pick up their wallets and then walk all the way back to the grocery store again. Once they reach the grocery store for the second time, how much longer do they have to get to the gym without being late?

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 30 minutes to cover every 3 miles of the city. However, we know that the wind speed is going to be halved in one hour. If the city is 72 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover a quarter of the city?

In a 100-item quiz, 40% of the questions are chemistry, 20% are geography, and the rest are equally divided as history and algebra questions. If Aisha is sure to get 25% of the geography questions, 100% of the chemistry questions, and a tenth of the history and algebra questions correctly, how many points is she sure to get?

Diego picks 67 pineapples on Wednesday. Then he picks 176 pineapples on Thursday. On Friday, he picks quintuple the number of pineapples he did on Wednesday. On Saturday, he picks half the amount of what he picked in the past 3 days combined. On Sunday, Diego is going to sell pineapples in boxes of 17 pineapples each. He is going to sell each box for $12. How much is Diego going to make?

Leon went to buy some school supplies. He bought 8 crayons which cost ¥7.0 each, 8 notebooks which cost ¥13.75 each, and a ream of bond paper which cost ¥10. He also bought 4 folders which cost ¥11 each. Leon can either pay a one-time ¥20 fee to become a member and get a 20% discount on all purchases, or not become a member and receive only a 5% discount. What is the least amount Leon can spend on everything?

Emma walks 32 kilometers every day on her favorite walking trail, which includes 14 kilometers of walking on the beach and 18 kilometers of walking on the sidewalk. On the sidewalk, Emma walks at three times the rate of speed that she does on the beach. However, due to a recent injury, Emma's speed has decreased by half both on the beach and sidewalk. If 56 minutes of her walk is spent on the beach, how long does it take for her to complete the entire 32-kilometer walk, in minutes?

Sakura is an avid gardener. Two days ago, she received 49 new potted plants from her favorite plant nursery. She already has 7 potted plants on each of the 60 window ledges of her large country home. She also purchased 100 new plants yesterday at a 50% discount. Feeling generous, she has decided that she will give 3 potted plants from each ledge to friends and family tomorrow. How many potted plants will Sakura remain with?

Valentina was preparing for a game night at her house, where she intended to serve vegetable lasagna. She noticed that she was out of plastic forks, so she bought a new package of forks. Later, her husband also bought a package of 19 new forks and gave them to Valentina. While Valentina was making the vegetable lasagna, she used six of the forks to sample her vegetable lasagna, then threw away 8 defective forks. The guests also brought 2 packs of forks, each having 8 inside them. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 49 forks. How many forks were in the package that Valentina bought?

Sakura is knitting winter wear for her 4 grandchildren. They're quadruplets, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a vest, cardigan, shawl, gloves, and mittens for each of them. It takes 5 skeins of wool to make a vest, 4 for a cardigan, 10 for a shawl, 12 for a pair of gloves, and 9 for a pair of mittens. Sakura wants to make two warm jackets for herself, each needing 4 skeins of wool. Each dozen skeins of wool costs $9. The store has a promotion where customers receive a $20 discount on purchases over $100. How much should Sakura pay for all the skeins of wool she needs?

Sanjay receives 32 emails a day. 25% of those emails don't require any response. From the rest, Sanjay can only respond to 2 less than the 1/2 of them. How many emails does Sanjay respond to in a 4 day work week? Sanjay work overtime on the last day so he can respond to 20% more emails than usual.

Faisal watches TV after he finishes his homework every night. On Wednesday and Thursday, he watched 4-hour episodes of his favorite show each night. On Friday, he watched a few episodes of a 30-minute show. On Saturday, he finished homework early and watched a 5-hour episode and a 15-minute show. On Sunday, he got to stay up late, so he watched four 3-hour episodes. On Monday, he watched three episodes, each 45 minutes. If he watched 28 hours of TV in all, how many 30-minute episodes did he watch on Friday?

According to its nutritional info, a bag of breads has 225 calories per serving. A 300 ounces bag has 5 servings. The healthy daily calorie target is 15 calories per pound of body weight. Carlos weighs 200 lbs, and he has already consumed 900 calories and burned 150 calories through exercise. Zahra weighs 150 lbs, and she has already consumed 900 in food and 225 calories in ice cream. How many more ounces of breads does Carlos need to consume than Zahra?

In Ms. Johnson's class of 100 students, 46% of the class are soccer players. Out of the remaining class, 50% of the students are robotics club members or part of dancers. These 3 groups of students will need to leave early today to travel to an away competition. Half of the soccer players are absent for being sick. Also, 3 cheerleaders will accompany each of these groups. How many students are leaving early to the competition?

Mrs. Smith is looking for a new house that will not go beyond her $410000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $500000. On top of that, the buyer has to pay a brokerage fee which is 7% of the selling price, and also the transfer fee that is 12% of the selling price. If Mrs. Smith can get 20% discount on the selling price, how much more will be the total cost than Mrs. Smith's budget?

Diego is 21 years old. In 5 years, his cousin Priya will be 2 times as old as Diego is now. Diego's brother, Qasim, is 9 years younger than Diego, and Priya sister Mia is 10 years older than Qasim. What will be the average of all four in 4 years?

Wei is selling cupcakes and plum pies for a fundraiser. On Monday, he sold 28 boxes of cupcake and 19 fewer boxes of plum pie, than on Tuesday. On Tuesday, he sold 14 more boxes of cupcakes than on Monday and 27 boxes of plum pie. On Wednesday, he sold as much as he did in the past two days combined. If the cupcake cost $11 and the plum pie cost $23, what was Wei's average daily earning?

Valeria and Viktor went to a construction supply store. Viktor is a member, but Valeria is not. Valeria has ₣97.37 and wants to buy 15 anchors from a bin at the store. She also needs 8 nails, each costing ₣0.64. Each anchor costs ₣0.35. Additionally, Valeria picks up 8 gallons of paint. Viktor starts with ₣90 and wants 10 gallons of paint, each priced at ₣7.0, and 4 carpenter pencils, each costing ₣2. The store offers a 10% discount on paint for members. How much more money does Valeria have left than Viktor after they leave the store?

A care facility has a capacity of 1700 rooms with 1/5 occupied and one-fifth of all the rooms being out of service. Due to the pandemic, 20 patients are admitted into the care facility each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied rooms in the care facility after 2 weeks.

Ravi, Pavel are currently 22 years apart in age. Ravi and Leilani are currently 10 years apart. Ravi, who is younger than Pavel but older than Leilani, will be 47 in 8 years. How much younger is Leilani than the average age of all three?

An uncle eats 16 pizzas per day, his spouse eats 16 pizzas per day, and their grandchild eats one-half of the combined number of pizzas they eat per day. After one month, the family decides to go on a diet in the second month, reducing their food consumption by 25% for the first half of the month, and then by an additional 50% for the second half. How many pizzas does this family eat in two months?

A loaf of sourdough at the cafe costs $10. The cost of a muffin is one-eighth of a loaf of sourdough. The cafe has a promotion that if one buys 6 muffins or more, they get a 10% discount on muffins. How much more do 2 loaves of sourdough cost than 8 muffins?

A giant pizza has 87 servings. Aisha can eat 3 servings a day while Amelia can eat twice as much and Ava can eat four times as much as Amelia. After 2 days, Ava decides to go on a diet and cut the consumption by half. How many days will it take for the pizza to be fully eaten?

Nadia went to the bakery and bought various types of pastries. She bought 60 donuts at $14 per dozen, 60 mini cupcakes at $25 per dozen, and 24 mini cheesecakes. After a 20% discount, she paid a total of $1540. What was the cost of mini cheesecakes per dozen?

A janitor has to clean a building with 80 rooms. They have 4 days to get it done. It takes them 6 minutes per room. However, due to a recent injury, the janitor has become slower and it will take them twice as long to clean a room these days. If they work for 10 hours a day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning rooms?

Uma and Zahra are sisters from Marrakech who love collecting signatures from politicians. During their spring break from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After 6 weeks, Uma and Zahra compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. Uma has 29 signatures in her book, and Zahra has 37. The sisters have 4 more weeks of spring break, and they decide they want to reach 130 signatures between them by the end of the break. However, during the remaining 4 weeks, Uma is only able to collect signatures on weekends, reducing her weekly collection by 5 per week, while Zahra decides to increase her weekly collection. How many signatures will Zahra need to collect per week to make sure they reach their goal?

Dr. Miller sold his apartment for $490000. He paid the legal fees that amounted to 1% of the selling price and also paid a realtor fee that is 5% of the selling price. He also paid $390000 for the remaining loan amount on the apartment, and $10000 for closing costs. Dr. Miller used the net proceeds from selling the apartment to invest in stocks. The stocks gained 10% each year for two years. How much were Dr. Miller's net proceeds after two years?

Bodhi goes to the store to buy some rice. The normal brand of rice he buys costs $15 per pound. He has to buy a more expensive brand that costs 20% more since his favorite brand was sold out. He decides to buy a week's worth of rice and he uses 2 pounds of rice per day. The store has a 20% discount on rice which applies only up to 10 pounds; any additional rice is sold at the regular price. Bodhi also decides to buy himself a cookie for $1. How much does Bodhi have to pay?

Thiago is raising money for a 3-day science fair. Each day costs $250 for hotel, $30 for food, and $30 for transportation. Thiago only has $35. His friends have chipped in and will cover the cost of all the food for the science fair. Thiago has also applied for help from the school, which has decided to cover 1/4 of the remaining cost of the science fair. How much money is Thiago still missing?
A pyramid is made out of 9 green cubes, twice as many white cubes, and an unknown number of pink cubes. If there are 45 cubes in the pyramid in total, what percentage of cubes are pink?

Sunnyside High is holding graduation in its Sports Arena this year which has space for 7500 people. After accounting for the 600 seats for graduate, 250 seats for the faculty attending, and reserving 50 seats for the event's staff, how many tickets would each graduate receive to give to their friends and family if the tickets are split equally?

Sakura went to the boardwalk for vacation. Her parents gave her €1300 to buy whatever she wanted. At the gift shop, saltwater taffy was on sale for "Buy 16 kgs at €22 per kg, get 4 kgs 1/4 off." She scooped up 22 kgs. She also bought a mixed bag of starfish for €11.0 and 12 keychains that were €20.0 each. Sakura then donated €5 at a charity stand along the way. How much money does Sakura have left?

Viktor initially had 9 dozen pancakes, then ate 3 pancakes for breakfast, and then hid the rest in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Liam finds 5 pancakes. Yusuf finds two times as many as Liam. Pavel finds 4 less than Yusuf. Daphne finds half as many as Pavel, and James finds four dozen pancakes more than Yusuf and Liam combined. How many pancakes are still hidden in the yard?

Kimia has a flower bed that is 126 feet long. Kimia wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Kimia's flowers grow 7feet wide so she needs to leave 14 feet between every plant (including the plants width). Kimia already owns 6 flowers. Each flowering plant costs ₣4 at the store. However, if she buys more than 2 plants, she'll receive a ₣5 discount on the entire purchase. How much money will Kimia spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?
There are 24 girls in the park. If there are one-third the number of boys in the park, what percentage of the kids in the park are girls?

Qasim collects garbage from 5 different apartment complexes. The first 4 have 100 apartments each and the last one is 30% bigger than the other 4 combined. However, this week, 5 apartments from each of the first 4 complexes were vacant and did not require collection service. Qasim collects garbage 2 times a week from each place and he gets paid ₣0.3 per collection for each apartment. He also earns an additional 10% in tips. How much money does he make in a week?

Yara went to her orchard to pick some strawberries and found nine times as many beetles as caterpillars in the garden. Yara then found 66 white animals, half of which were rabbits. In addition, she saw 24 bees, and 13 caterpillars. What percentage of animals in the garden were rabbits?

Olga can peel 12 clams a minute and saute 30 clams in 9 minutes. How many minutes will it take her to peel and saute 180 clams if it takes 19 seconds to wash each clam before peeling it? Note that Olga can't work in parallel and needs to take a 11-minute break after peeling the clams before she can start sautéing them.

A class of 230 students has various hobbies. 5 like to dance, 8 like to play chess, 13 like to swim, 32 like to play volleyball, and the rest like to either play video games or play music. What percentage of the students like to play video games if the number of the students that like to play music is 7 less than two times the number that prefer playing volleyball?

Tariq is rolling a four-sided die. How much more likely is it (expressed as a difference in percentage points) that he rolls a number greater than 2 twice in a row, than that he rolls four even numbers in a row?

Olga makes coffee using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in a ratio of 48:10. She also uses 6 tablespoons of milk for every 10 cups of water, and uses 2 tablespoons of heavy cream for every teaspoon of sugar. She used a total of 210 teaspoons of sugar, cups of water, tablespoons of cream, and tablespoons of milk. How many teaspoons of sugar did she use?

A juggler can juggle 360 balls. Half of the balls are tennis balls, and the rest are golf balls. A third of the tennis balls are teal, of which 1/4 are marked. 1/3 of the golf balls are pink, and all except a fifth of those pink balls are marked. How many marked balls are there in total?

When Nadia watches her cousin, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 36 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 8 stuffed animals inside. The number of action figures in the action figure pack is twice the number of blocks and stuffed animals combined. The crayon box has 12 different colors of crayon, and the sticker book has 9 pages, each with 12 stickers. The tower of stacking rings has 30 multicolored rings on it. Nadia recently bought a tube of bouncy balls, bringing her total number of items for her cousin up to 330. How many bouncy balls came in the tube?

Deshawn wants to make different sized ice cubes with 312 ounces of water. He can make giant cubes that use 15 ounces per cube, medium cubes that use 5 ounces, small cubes that use 1/2 of a ounce, and tiny cubes that are half the size of small cubes. He makes 46 total ice cubes, including 8 giant cubes, 14 small cubes, 12 medium cubes, and some tiny cubes. How many ounces of water does DeShawn have left?

Benjamin is popping popcorn for a snack. As the pan of kernels heats up, the kernels start popping faster. 80 pop in the first 26 seconds of cooking, then 2 times that amount in the next 26 seconds. The kernels increase to 3 times the initial popping rate in the next 26 seconds. In the final 26 seconds, the popping slows down to half the rate as the past 26 seconds. After Benjamin takes the pan off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 26 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. Benjamin gives 1/7 of the made popcorn to his brother Yusuf. How many more pieces of popcorn does Benjamin have to eat than his brother?

Oliver has 15 hectares of grape field. There are 15 grapes per 1/3 of a hectare. Oliver can harvest his grapes every 4 months. In addition, Oliver owns a 9-hectare apple field that produces 16 apples per hectare. The apples can be harvested every 4 months. In the span of two years, how many more grapes does Oliver harvest than apples?

Daphne is an avid gardener. Two days ago, she received 23 new potted plants from her favorite plant nursery. She already has 8 potted plants on each of the 56 window ledges of her large country home. She also purchased 200 new plants yesterday at a 50% discount. Feeling generous, she has decided that she will give 6 potted plants from each ledge to friends and family tomorrow. How many potted plants will Daphne remain with?

A farmer is buying feed for his sheep. He buys a variety of wheat, corn, beets and oats. Since oats are a rare treat, he only buys five 3-kg boxes of them for the whole stable. He only wants enough beets to feed the sheep while the vegetables are fresh, so he buys eleven 7-kg bags. Wheat are the main diet of his sheep, so he buys thirty four 44-kg packs. Corn are a staple to supplement the wheat, so he buys eighteen 19-kg sacks. Finally, he buys 43 kgs of groceries, and 27 kgs of tools, and 100 kgs of wood. A farm truck can carry 140 kgs at a time. If the farmer has three trucks, how many trips does the farmer need to transport all the purchased items?

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 75 minutes to cover every 10 miles of the city. However, we know that the wind speed is going to be halved in one hour. If the city is 72 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover 1/4 of the city?

Ali saw a 30-foot whale with 18 remoras, each 15 inches long attached to it. Then, 1/3 of the remoras swam away. Later, Ali saw another 10-foot whale with 6 remoras, each 8 inches long, attached to it. On average, what percentage of each whale's body length is covered by the remoras?

To make a call from a phone booth, you must pay ₺0.9 for each minute of your call. After 10 minutes, the price drops to ₺0.6 per minute. After 35 minutes from the start of the call, the price drops even more to ₺0.4 per two minutes. If your total bill is more than ₺25, you get a 20% discount on your total bill. How much would a 115-minute call cost?

Gabriel and Pavel have 212 minutes to walk to the gym together starting from their home. It takes them 29 minutes to get to the corner where the library is. It takes them another 19 minutes to get to the cinema. When they reach the cinema, they remember they forgot their wallets at home, so they have to return to pick up their wallets and then walk all the way back to the cinema again. Once they reach the cinema for the second time, how much longer do they have to get to the gym without being late?

Oscar's dog has 130 puppies, 28 of which have spots. Andre's dog has 44 puppies, 14 of which have spots. Jin has 66 dogs, each having 11 puppies with spots. After a visit to the vet, Oscar discovered that half of his unspotted puppies actually have spots that were not visible before. What percentage of all the puppies have spots?

Ali places crackers on bowls and plates. Each bowl can hold 40 crackers while each plate can hold two times that. Ali has 675 crackers, 8 bowls and 5 plates. Unfortunately, 2 plates break. Ali then eats one-ninth of all the crackers. How many more bowls does Ali need so he can place all the remaining crackers?

In a 80-item quiz, 50% of the questions are chemistry, 5% are biology, and the rest are equally divided as geometry and literature questions. If Keisha is sure to get 25% of the biology questions, 70% of the chemistry questions, and a third of the geometry and literature questions correctly, how many points is she sure to get?

Olivia walks 29 miles every day on her favorite walking trail, which includes 13 miles of walking on the beach and 16 miles of walking on the sidewalk. On the sidewalk, Olivia walks at four times the rate of speed that she does on the beach. However, due to a recent injury, Olivia's speed has decreased by half both on the beach and sidewalk. If 65 minutes of her walk is spent on the beach, how long does it take for her to complete the entire 29-mile walk, in minutes?

Deshawn picks 142 pears on Saturday. Then he picks 172 pears on Sunday. On Monday, he picks triple the number of pears he did on Saturday. On Tuesday, he picks half the amount of what he picked in the past 3 days combined. On Wednesday, DeShawn is going to sell pears in boxes of 15 pears each. He is going to sell each box for $14. How much is DeShawn going to make?

Bodhi went to buy some school supplies. He bought 24 folders which cost €2.75 each, 12 pencils which cost €19.25 each, and a ream of bond paper which cost €23. He also bought 5 markers which cost €8 each. Bodhi can either pay a one-time €20 fee to become a member and get a 20% discount on all purchases, or not become a member and receive only a 5% discount. What is the least amount Bodhi can spend on everything?

Liam watches TV after he finishes his homework every night. On Saturday and Sunday, he watched 5-hour episodes of his favorite show each night. On Monday, he watched a few episodes of a 30-minute show. On Tuesday, he finished homework early and watched a 4-hour episode and a 60-minute show. On Wednesday, he got to stay up late, so he watched three 3-hour episodes. On Thursday, he watched five episodes, each 30 minutes. If he watched 28 hours of TV in all, how many 30-minute episodes did he watch on Monday?

Leon receives 30 emails a day. 20% of those emails don't require any response. From the rest, Leon can only respond to 2 less than the half of them. How many emails does Leon respond to in a 6 day work week? Leon work overtime on the last day so he can respond to 50% more emails than usual.

Fatima is knitting winter wear for her 5 grandchildren. They're quintuplets, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a beanie, vest, cardigan, gloves, and mittens for each of them. It takes 4 skeins of wool to make a beanie, 6 for a vest, 8 for a cardigan, 12 for a pair of gloves, and 10 for a pair of mittens. Fatima wants to make two warm jackets for herself, each needing 8 skeins of wool. Each dozen skeins of wool costs $8. The store has a promotion where customers receive a $20 discount on purchases over $100. How much should Fatima pay for all the skeins of wool she needs?

Benjamin is selling cupcakes and pineapple pies for a fundraiser. On Wednesday, he sold 27 boxes of cupcake and 18 fewer boxes of pineapple pie, than on Thursday. On Thursday, he sold 12 more boxes of cupcakes than on Wednesday and 27 boxes of pineapple pie. On Friday, he sold as much as he did in the past two days combined. If the cupcake cost ¥8 and the pineapple pie cost ¥22, what was Benjamin's average daily earning?

Uma was preparing for a potluck party at her house, where she intended to serve shrimp scampi. She noticed that she was out of plastic spoons, so she bought a new package of spoons. Later, her husband also bought a package of 11 new spoons and gave them to Uma. While Uma was making the shrimp scampi, she used seven of the spoons to sample her shrimp scampi, then threw away 5 defective spoons. The guests also brought 2 packs of spoons, each having 5 inside them. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 36 spoons. How many spoons were in the package that Uma bought?

Gabrielle and Arash went to a construction supply store. Arash is a member, but Gabrielle is not. Gabrielle has €92.27 and wants to buy 15 nails from a bin at the store. She also needs 8 washers, each costing €0.64. Each nail costs €0.21. Additionally, Gabrielle picks up 8 gallons of paint. Arash starts with €100 and wants 12 gallons of paint, each priced at €7.5, and 3 carpenter pencils, each costing €3. The store offers a 10% discount on paint for members. How much more money does Gabrielle have left than Arash after they leave the store?
