According to its nutritional info, a bag of popcorn has 300 calories per serving. A 325 grams bag has 5 servings. The healthy daily calorie target is 15 calories per pound of body weight. Ibrahim weighs 190 lbs, and he has already consumed 950 calories and burned 200 calories through exercise. Priya weighs 170 lbs, and she has already consumed 1100 in food and 250 calories in ice cream. How many more grams of popcorn does Ibrahim need to consume than Priya?

A care facility has a capacity of 1800 rooms with 1/6 occupied and one-ninth of all the rooms being out of service. Due to the pandemic, 25 patients are admitted into the care facility each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied rooms in the care facility after 2 weeks.

Oliver is 15 years old. In 8 years, his cousin Olivia will be 3 times as old as Oliver is now. Oliver's brother, Gabriel, is 11 years younger than Oliver, and Olivia sister Fatima is 8 years older than Gabriel. What will be the average of all four in 5 years?

Chen, Theo are currently 10 years apart in age. Chen and Tara are currently 7 years apart. Chen, who is younger than Theo but older than Tara, will be 60 in 7 years. How much younger is Tara than the average age of all three?

In Ms. Johnson's class of 150 students, 40% of the class are soccer players. Out of the remaining class, 30% of the students are dancers or part of choir members. These 3 groups of students will need to leave early today to travel to an away competition. Half of the soccer players are absent for being sick. Also, 3 cheerleaders will accompany each of these groups. How many students are leaving early to the competition?

An uncle eats 24 hamburgers per day, his spouse eats 24 hamburgers per day, and their grandchild eats one-half of the combined number of hamburgers they eat per day. After one month, the family decides to go on a diet in the second month, reducing their food consumption by 75% for the first half of the month, and then by an additional 50% for the second half. How many hamburgers does this family eat in two months?

Dr. Patel is looking for a new condo that will not go beyond her $390000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $560000. On top of that, the buyer has to pay a brokerage fee which is 7% of the selling price, and also the transfer fee that is 14% of the selling price. If Dr. Patel can get 25% discount on the selling price, how much more will be the total cost than Dr. Patel's budget?

A giant lasagna has 102 pieces. Leon can eat 3 pieces a day while Mohammed can eat thrice as much and Sakura can eat two times as much as Mohammed. After 2 days, Sakura decides to go on a diet and cut the consumption by half. How many days will it take for the lasagna to be fully eaten?

A loaf of bread at the store costs ¥5. The cost of a croissant is 3/4 of a loaf of bread. The store has a promotion that if one buys 6 croissants or more, they get a 10% discount on croissants. How much more do 10 loaves of bread cost than 8 croissants?

A maintenance worker has to clean a university with 150 floors. They have 6 days to get it done. It takes them 6 minutes per floor. However, due to a recent injury, the maintenance worker has become slower and it will take them twice as long to clean a floor these days. If they work for 10 hours a day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning floors?
A stack is made out of 5 orange tiles, two times as many pink tiles, and an unknown number of green tiles. If there are 20 tiles in the stack in total, what percentage of tiles are green?

Ava went to her allotment to pick some raspberries and found one-third as many bees as wasps in the patch. Ava then found 60 white animals, half of which were rabbits. In addition, she saw 24 caterpillars, and 12 wasps. What percentage of animals in the patch were rabbits?

Oliver goes to the store to buy some flour. The normal brand of flour he buys costs ₣16 per kilogram. He has to buy a more expensive brand that costs 25% more since his favorite brand was sold out. He decides to buy a week's worth of flour and he uses 2 kilograms of flour per day. The store has a 5% discount on flour which applies only up to 10 kilograms; any additional flour is sold at the regular price. Oliver also decides to buy himself a muffin for ₣4. How much does Oliver have to pay?

Nia went to the patisserie and bought various types of baked goods. She bought 60 croissants at $19 per dozen, 72 macarons at $20 per dozen, and 36 brownies. After a 5% discount, she paid a total of $1330. What was the cost of brownies per dozen?

Mr. Martinez sold his cottage for $690000. He paid the transfer fees that amounted to 3% of the selling price and also paid a brokerage fee that is 6% of the selling price. He also paid $590000 for the remaining loan amount on the cottage, and $5000 for closing costs. Mr. Martinez used the net proceeds from selling the cottage to invest in stocks. The stocks gained 10% each year for two years. How much were Mr. Martinez's net proceeds after two years?

Daphne and Olivia are sisters from Cairo who love collecting signatures from movie stars. During their spring break from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After 3 weeks, Daphne and Olivia compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. Daphne has 17 signatures in her book, and Olivia has 31. The sisters have 3 more weeks of spring break, and they decide they want to reach 120 signatures between them by the end of the break. However, during the remaining 3 weeks, Daphne is only able to collect signatures on weekends, reducing her weekly collection by 5 per week, while Olivia decides to increase her weekly collection. How many signatures will Olivia need to collect per week to make sure they reach their goal?

Kayla went to the pier for vacation. Her parents gave her ₺1400 to buy whatever she wanted. At the beach shop, rock candy was on sale for "Buy 16 kgs at ₺22 per kg, get 6 kgs 2/3 off." She scooped up 23 kgs. She also bought a mixed bag of sea glass for ₺11.0 and 14 stickers that were ₺20.5 each. Kayla then donated ₺5 at a charity stand along the way. How much money does Kayla have left?

Ali initially had 11 dozen cookies, then ate 3 cookies for breakfast, and then hid the rest in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Faisal finds 5 cookies. Hiroshi finds thrice as many as Faisal. Benjamin finds 3 less than Hiroshi. Wei finds a quarter as many as Benjamin, and Quinn finds three dozen cookies more than Hiroshi and Faisal combined. How many cookies are still hidden in the yard?

Greenville High School is holding graduation in its Convention Center this year which has space for 7700 people. After accounting for the 550 seats for graduate, 450 seats for the faculty attending, and reserving 100 seats for the event's staff, how many tickets would each graduate receive to give to their friends and family if the tickets are split equally?

Ali is raising money for a 3-day sports tournament. Each day costs ₣200 for hotel, ₣20 for food, and ₣10 for transportation. Ali only has ₣40. His friends have chipped in and will cover the cost of all the food for the sports tournament. Ali has also applied for help from the local charity, which has decided to cover 1/5 of the remaining cost of the sports tournament. How much money is Ali still missing?

Gabrielle has a flower bed that is 150 meters long. Gabrielle wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Gabrielle's flowers grow 3meters wide so she needs to leave 15 meters between every plant (including the plants width). Gabrielle already owns 7 flowers. Each flowering plant costs $3 at the store. However, if she buys more than 2 plants, she'll receive a $8 discount on the entire purchase. How much money will Gabrielle spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?
There are 39 girls in the yard. If there are two-sixths the number of boys in the yard, what percentage of the kids in the yard are girls?

Aisha can peel 10 clams a minute and saute 30 clams in 6 minutes. How many minutes will it take her to peel and saute 120 clams if it takes 14 seconds to wash each clam before peeling it? Note that Aisha can't work in parallel and needs to take a 7-minute break after peeling the clams before she can start sautéing them.

Hiroshi collects garbage from 6 different apartment complexes. The first 5 have 100 apartments each and the last one is 40% bigger than the other 5 combined. However, this week, 8 apartments from each of the first 5 complexes were vacant and did not require collection service. Hiroshi collects garbage 2 times a week from each place and he gets paid ₣0.25 per collection for each apartment. He also earns an additional 10% in tips. How much money does he make in a week?
Leon has 90 square yards of pineapple field. There are 99 pineapples per square yard. Leon can harvest his pineapples every 4 months. How many pineapples can Leon harvest within a year?
Jamal saw a 380-foot whale with 8 57-inch remoras attached to it. What percentage of the whale's body length is the combined length of the remoras?

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 63 minutes to cover every 13 miles of the city. If the city is 39 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover the whole city?

A farmer is buying feed for his alpacas. He buys a variety of hay, corns, cucumbers and wheats. Since wheats are a rare treat, he only buys four 6-kg boxes of them for the whole stable. He only wants enough cucumbers to feed the alpacas while the vegetables are fresh, so he buys fifteen 8-kg bags. Hay are the main diet of his alpacas, so he buys thirty two 43-kg packs. Corns are a staple to supplement the hay, so he buys twenty 19-kg sacks. If his farm truck can carry 190 kgs at a time, how many trips does the farmer need to transport all the feed?

Xena makes tea using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in the ratio of 135:21. If she used a total of 468 teaspoons of sugar and cups of water, calculate the number of teaspoonfuls of sugar she used.
A juggler can juggle 120 balls. A fifth of the balls are golf balls, and a quarter of the golf balls are black. How many black golf balls are there?

When Emma watches her cousin, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 74 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 37 stuffed animals inside. The tower of stacking rings has 30 multicolored rings on it. Emma recently bought a tube of bouncy balls, bringing her total number of toys for her cousin up to 215. How many bouncy balls came in the tube?

Viktor wants to make different sized ice cubes with 348 ounces of water. He can make giant cubes that use 12 ounces per cube, medium cubes that use 11 ounces, and small cubes that use 3/4 of ounce. If he makes 8 giant cubes, 24 small cubes, and 14 medium cubes, how many ounces of water does he have left?

Ali is popping popcorn for a snack. As the skillet of kernels heats up, the kernels start popping faster. 30 pop in the first 10 seconds of cooking, then 3 times that amount in the next 10 seconds. The kernels increase to 4 times the initial popping rate in the next 10 seconds, but in the final 10 seconds, the popping slows down to half the rate as the past 10 seconds. After Ali takes the skillet off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 10 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. How many pieces of popcorn does Ali have to eat?
To make a call from a phone booth, you must pay €0.8 for each minute of your call. After 30 minutes, that price drops to €0.4 per minute. How much would a 55-minute call cost?

A group of 157 students has various hobbies. 23 like to play video games, 41 like to play volleyball, and the rest like to either hike or paint. How many like to hike if the number that like to paint is twice the number that prefer playing volleyball?
Hiroshi is rolling a d10 die. How much more likely is it (expressed as a percentage) that he rolls a number greater than 2 than that he rolls two odd numbers in a row?
Sofia's dog has 1035 puppies, 250 of which have spots. Jasmine's dog has 445 puppies, 120 of which have spots. What percentage of all the puppies have spots?

Qasim and Faisal have 102 minutes to walk to the library together. It takes them 14 minutes to get to the corner where the gym is. It takes them another 53 minutes to get to the cinema. How much longer do they have to get to library without being late?
Oliver places olives on some plates. Each plate can hold 21 olives. If he has 291 olives and 13 plates, how many olives won't he be able to place on the plate?
Viktor went to buy some school supplies. He bought 16 folders which cost ₺5.75 each, 10 rulers which cost ₺18.5 each, and a rim of bond paper which cost ₺21. How much did Viktor spend on everything?

Nadia walks 26 kilometers every day on her favorite walking trail, which includes 10 kilometers of walking on the beach and 16 kilometers of walking on the sidewalk. On the sidewalk, Nadia walks at four times the rate of speed that she does on the beach. If 60 minutes of her walk is spent on the beach, how long does it take for her to complete the entire 26-kilometer walk, in minutes?

Xavier is selling brownie and plum pie for a fundraiser. On Wednesday, he sold 26 boxes of brownie and 15 fewer boxes of plum pie, than on Thursday. On Thursday, he sold 14 more boxes of brownies than on Wednesday and 27 boxes of plum pie. If the brownie cost €12 and the plum pie cost €20, how much did Xavier earn for two days?

Ananya is an avid gardener. Last night, she received 34 new potted plants from her favorite plant nursery. She already has 11 potted plants on each of the 62 window ledges of her large country home. Feeling generous, she has decided that she will give 3 potted plants from each ledge to friends and family tomorrow. How many potted plants will Ananya remain with?
Diego picks 200 kiwis on Saturday. Then he picks 145 kiwis on Sunday. On Monday, he picks quadruple the number of kiwis he did on Saturday. How many kiwis does Diego have?

Chen is knitting winter wear for her 4 grandchildren. They're quadruplets, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a vest, cardigan, poncho, mittens, and booties for each of them. It takes 17 skeins of wool to make a vest, 16 for a cardigan, 8 for a poncho, 4 for a pair of mittens, and 11 for a pair of booties. How many skeins of wool will she need to buy?

Quinn was preparing for a birthday party at her house, where she intended to serve beef stew. She noticed that she was out of plastic plates, so she bought a new package of plates. Later, her husband also bought a package of 19 new plates and gave them to Quinn. While Quinn was making the beef stew, she used seven of the plates to sample her beef stew. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 30 plates. How many plates were in the package that Quinn bought?

According to its nutritional info, a bag of cookies has 300 calories per serving. If a 300 oz bag has 4 servings, how many oz can you eat if your daily calorie target is 1925 and you have already consumed 1025 calories?
An uncle eats 6 tacos per day, his spouse eats 5 tacos per day, and their grandchild eats 7 tacos per day. How many tacos does this family eat in one month?

In a 110-item quiz, 40% of the questions are chemistry, and the rest are equally divided as biology and algebra questions. If Zahra is sure to get 25% of the chemistry questions, and 1/6 of the biology and algebra questions correctly, how many points is she sure to get?
Fatima receives 120 emails a day. 20% of those emails don't require any response. Fatima responds to the rest of them. How many emails does Fatima respond to in a 3 day work week?

Hiroshi watches TV after he finishes his homework every night. On Monday and Tuesday, he watched a 6-hour episode of his favorite show each night. On Wednesday, he watched a few episodes of a 30-minute show. On Thursday, he finished homework early and watched a 3-hour episode and a 30-minute show. On Friday, he got to stay up late, so he watched two 2-hour episodes. If he watched 23 hours of TV in all, how many 30-minute episodes did he watch on Wednesday?
Wei is 10 years old. In 7 years his cousin Chen will be 3 times as old as Wei is now. How old is Chen right now?
Nadia and Santiago are currently 12 years apart in age. If Nadia, who is younger than Santiago, is 62 years old, what's the average of their ages?

In Mrs. Garcia's class of 125 students, 36% of the class are swimmers. Out of the remaining class, 40% of the students are robotics club members or part of dancers. These 3 groups of students will need to leave early today to travel to an away meet. How many students are leaving early?
Luca has ₣74.22 and wants to buy 17 washers from a bin at the hardware store. Each washer costs ₣0.66. How much money does Luca have left after paying for the washers?

Sakura and Ananya are sisters from São Paulo who love collecting signatures from musicians. During their summer break from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After 7 weeks, Sakura and Ananya compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. Sakura has 30 signatures in her book, and Ananya has 31. The sisters have 3 more weeks of summer break, and they decide they want to reach 95 signatures between them by the end of the break. How many signatures do the sisters need to collect to reach their goal?

Mr. Davis sold his condo for $930000. He paid the transfer fees that amount to 3% of the selling price and also paid a brokerage fee that is 3% of the selling price. If he also paid $310000 for the remaining loan amount of the condo, how much is Mr. Davis's net proceeds from selling the condo?

Dr. Patel is looking for a condo that will not go beyond her $340000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $300000. On top of that, the buyer has to pay a brokerage fee which is 7% of the selling price, and also the transfer fee that is 11% of the selling price. How much more is the total price of the condo than Dr. Patel's budget?

Chen went to the cafe and bought various types of treats. She bought 3 dozen danishes which cost $12 per dozen, 8 dozen tarts which cost $82 per dozen, and 6 dozen scones for $113 per dozen. How much was the total cost?

A maintenance worker has to clean a university with 60 floors. They have 5 days to get it done. It takes them 15 minutes per floor. If they work 15 hours each day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning floors?
A pyramid is made out of 3 pink cubes, four times as many orange cubes, and an unknown number of black cubes. If there are 31 cubes in the pyramid in total, how many black cubes are there?
A loaf of bread at the store costs ¥4. Croissants cost ¥1 each. How much more do 3 loaves of bread cost than 6 croissants?
A cake has 48 portions. If Priya can eat 4 portions a day while Winnie can eat two times as much, how many days will the cake last?
Uma went to their greenhouse to pick some blueberries and found seven times as many bees as wasps in the plot. If there were 78 wasps, calculate the total number of insects in the plot.

Ravi is raising money for a conference. He has applied for help from the local charity, which has decided to cover half of the cost of the conference. How much money is Ravi missing if he has ₣195 and the conference costs ₣980?

Liam hid 5 dozen eggs in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Wei finds 4 eggs. Pavel finds two times as many as Wei. Nadia finds 4 less than Pavel, and Ravi finds a quarter as many as Nadia. How many eggs are still hidden in the yard?

Riverside Academy is holding graduation in their Gymnasium this year which has space for 7400 people. After accounting for 700 seats for graduates and 400 seats for faculty attending, how many tickets would each graduate receive to give to their friends and family if the tickets are split equally?

Deshawn goes to the store to buy some tea. The normal brand of tea he buys costs ₣20 per kilogram. He had to buy a more expensive brand that costs 10% more since his favorite brand was sold out. He decides to buy a week's worth of tea and he uses 1 kilogram of tea per day. He also decided to buy himself a bagel for ₣2. How much did everything cost?

Mia went to the beach for vacation. Her parents gave her ₣1200 to buy whatever she wanted. At the souvenir store, fudge was on sale for "Buy 15 kilograms at ₣22 per kilogram, get 4 kilograms 1/4 off." She scooped up 22 kilograms. She also bought a mixed bag of sand dollars for ₣11.25 and 15 postcards that were ₣20.25 each. How much money does Mia have left?
Chen can peel 12 shrimps a minute and saute 30 shrimps in 11 minutes. How long will it take her to peel and saute 60 shrimps?

Andre has a flower stand at the community market. He sells three kinds of flowers: orchids, sunflowers and daisies. He usually sells orchids for ₣1.59 per basket, sunflowers for ₣2.79 per basket and daisies for ₣5.16 per basket. Andre has no change today, so he has decided to round all his prices to the nearest dollar. If Andre sells 7 baskets of orchids, 25 baskets of sunflowers and 40 baskets of daisies, how much will he make?

A medical center has a capacity of 1500 wards with 1/5 occupied. Due to the major accident, 55 patients are admitted into the medical center each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied wards in the medical center after 3 weeks.
Hiroshi has 1 €100 bills. He buys 5 action figures for €4 each. He also buys 2 packs of candy bars for €2 each. How much money does he have left?
The area of Alejandro's rectangular living room is 651 square feet. If the length of his room is 7 yards, what is the perimeter of the room in feet?
Kimia scored 324 points in one game of basketball. Ali scored 11 points more than 2/3 as many as Kimia. How many points did Kimia and Ali have in total?

Mia is learning to write and decides to keep re-writing the alphabet until she knows it. She writes it in full ten times, writes three-sixths of it once, then re-writes everything she has already written. How many letters has Mia written in total?

Noah has 9 tubes of orange paint and 11 tubes of magenta paint. Xavier has four-sixths as many tubes of orange paint as Noah, and two times as many tubes of magenta paint as Noah. How many tubes of paint does Xavier have?
There are 15 girls in the park. If there are two-fifths the number of boys in the park, how many kids are in the park?
Ananya sliced a whole orange into 29 pieces. She ate 3 slices, her cousin ate 7 more than her, and her friend ate 3 more than her cousin. How many slices of orange did they all eat?
A cup of lemonade is 12 ounces of lemonade. Arjun drinks 2 cups of lemonade. If lemonade has 8 calories per ounce how many calories did he consume?

Benjamin collects garbage from 4 different apartment complexes. The first 3 have 400 apartments each and the last one is 55% bigger than the other 3 combined. Benjamin collects garbage 4 times a week from each place and he gets paid ₣0.25 per collection for each apartment. How much money does he make in a week?

One miner can mine 5 pounds of ore per day with bare hands. He can mine twice as much with a nickel pickaxe and 60% more with a steel pickaxe than with a nickel pickaxe. How many pounds of ore can 22 miners with steel pickaxes mine in a month with 28 days?
In a set of scientist's cards, there are 60 yellow cards, and 65% more purple cards. Orange cards are as many as the sum of yellow and purple cards. How many cards of all mentioned colors are there?

I have 20 liters of lemon drink that are two-fifths water and I wish to add it to 30 liters of grape drink that is one-tenth water. But as I pour it, I spill 5 liters of the lemon drink. How much water is in the remaining 45 liters?

Yara has a flower bed that is 201 feet long. Yara wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Yara's flowers grow 4 feet wide so she needs to leave 16.75 feet between every plant. Yara already owns 10 flowers. Each flowering plant costs €3 at the store, how much money will Yara spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?
A kid has 10 toys. His cousin has 5 fewer toys than he has. How many toys do they have together?

Leilani has 4 jars of icing in her kitchen cabinet. Each jar of icing can decorate 6 brownies. Leilani wants to bake enough brownies to use up all of her icing. If each baking sheet holds 8 brownies, how many baking sheets worth of brownies should she bake?
Nia has 73 light purple spools of thread, 140 dark purple spools of thread, 60 light blue spools of thread, and 82 dark blue spools of thread. What percent of the spools are purple?

Ananya is trying to decide whether to do her taxes herself or hire one tax consultant. If she does it herself, she'll be able to do 8 fewer hours of part-time work, losing ₣23/hour in missed income. The tax consultant charges ₣120. How much more money will she have if she hires the tax consultant?

Arjun's car breaks down. The car weighs 1900 pounds and he has luggage in it weighing 100 pounds. He also has his 2 young children who weigh 80 pounds each in it. If the force to move the car is 5% of the weight, how much force does he need to push the car?

On Saturday, Esteban wants to exercise for seven times the amount of time he did on Friday and Thursday combined. On Thursday he exercised for 51 minutes. On Friday he exercised for 48 minutes. How many minutes does he have to exercise on Saturday to reach his goal?

Luis works a 7-hour shift each day, 4 days a week. He earns ₺25 per hour and gets a ₺554 bonus each week if the company performs well. How much money did Luis make in March if the company performed very well for the whole month?
A electrician works for 4 weeks every month and for 6 days every week. If he gets paid €150 every day, how much does he earn if he works for a year?

Umar is feeding his livestock grain. Each alpaca needs 8 kg, and each cow needs 1 kg less than twice the amount each alpaca needs. If there are 36 alpacas and 17 cows, how many kg of grain does Umar need?
It takes Zahra 25 minutes to finish a word puzzle and 9 minutes to finish a riddle. Over the free time she solved 8 word puzzles and 4 riddles. How much time did she spend playing these games?

There are currently 16 orange balls, 18 pink balls, and 30 green balls in the shop. Orange balls cost ¥10, green balls cost ¥6, and pink balls cost ¥7. How much will the shop have received after all the balls are sold?

Comet Encke orbits the sun every 50 years. Oliver's grandfather saw the Comet when he was 28 years old. Oliver saw the comet a second time when he was two times the age his grandfather was when he saw the Comet. How old was Oliver when he saw the Comet for the first time?

Pavel has a bag of buttons with 68 inside. He tripped over rock while carrying it and dropped two-fourths of them. He scrambled to search for them but only came up with 16. When he went back home, he inspected the buttons further. Two of them he picked up weren't buttons, but actually buttons so he got rid of it. How many buttons did Pavel end up with?
Camila is required to submit a 165-page essay. She already finished writing 4/5 of the essay. How many pages does she have left to write?

Yusuf was a pen pal with 7 people. He stopped being penpals with 1 of them. They each send 3 letters a week that are 10 pages long. He responds in kind. He can write a page every 11 minutes. How many hours does he spend writing a week?

There are 67 fourth-graders at Sunny Hill School. 38 of them are girls. On Thursday, 6 fourth-grade girls and 6 fourth-grade boys were absent. How many fourth grade boys were at Sunny Hill School on Thursday?
Gabrielle finished 2/4 of a 254 piece puzzle, and then started and finished another 718 piece puzzle within an hour. How many puzzle pieces did Gabrielle place during that hour?
The Charity fundraiser team hid 150 coins. The Lopez twins each found 27 coins. All the other coins except 12 were found by their friends. How many coins did the friends find?

At the beginning of the conference, there were 52 engineers and 63 nurses. After 45 minutes, four-fifths of the total number of people left. How many nurses are left if 21 engineers stayed at the conference?
If Oliver and Kayla have 580 meters of fence between them, and they agree to split it with Kayla getting 160 meters more than Oliver, how much is left over for Oliver?

The Brown family is busy making biscuits. So far, they've made 7275 biscuits. They have 2204 peanut butter biscuits, 2847 lemon biscuits, and some blueberry biscuits. How many blueberry biscuits have they made?

Leilani qualified for a spot on the volleyball team, so she went shopping for some athletic gear. She bought a jersey for ₺16, a pair of volleyball leggings for ₺12 more than the jersey cost, and a pair of cleats that were originally ₺76 but were on sale for three-fourths price. She had a coupon for ₺4 off the package of ₺11 athletic headbands that she also bought. How much did she spend on athletic gear?

The biggest waterslide at Splash World is 250 yards long, and people slide down at 50 yards/minute. The second biggest waterslide is 210 yards long, but steeper, so people slide down at 70 yards/minute. How much longer does it take to ride the biggest slide compared to the second biggest slide?

580 people apply for a job at Tesla. Of the people that apply, only 25% receive interviews. Of those who receive interviews, 40% receive a job offer. Of those who receive a job offer, one-half of the people accept the position. How many people accept the position?

Elena can run nine times faster than she can walk, but she can skip at a rate of speed that is four-sixths as fast as she can run. If she can skip at 2 miles per hour, how many miles can she travel in 6 hours if she spends three-sixths of the time running and 2/4 of the time walking?

The go-karts cost €11 a ride. How many friends can she invite?

There are 13 students playing football and nine times that number playing basketball. There are 14 boys and 11 girls playing volleyball. If each student only participates in one group, how many students are there in total?

At Sanjay's house, there are three times as many pears as apples. He has a total of 34 apples in his house. Sanjay bought 62 more apples at the store and 46 fewer pears than the number of apples. Find the combined total of the number of pears and apples Sanjay has in the house?

Gabrielle operates the cash register exactly nine times as fast as her less-experienced colleague Olivia. Daily, Olivia processes 66 customers. What is the total weekly production for the two if they work all days of the week?
If Theo eats 3 eggs a day for 107 days and then increases it to 5 eggs a day for 87 days, how many dozens of eggs will Theo need for 194 days?
The vending machines sell crackers for 25 cents and pretzels for 100 cents. Arjun spent ¥1100 and got 4 bags of crackers and had 1% of his money left in change. How many pretzels did he buy?

Mia saw a 240-foot shark with 4 36-inch remoras attached to it. What percentage of the shark's body length is the combined length of the remoras?

When Aisha watches her brother, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 72 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 36 stuffed animals inside. The tower of stacking rings has 22 multicolored rings on it. Aisha recently bought a tube of bouncy balls, bringing her total number of toys for her brother up to 153. How many bouncy balls came in the tube?

Olga is popping popcorn for a snack. As the skillet of kernels heats up, the kernels start popping faster. 40 pop in the first 16 seconds of cooking, then 4 times that amount in the next 16 seconds. After Olga takes the skillet off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 16 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. How many pieces of popcorn does Olga have to eat?

Xena makes tea using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in the ratio of 150:80. If she used a total of 1380 teaspoons of sugar and cups of water, calculate the number of teaspoonfuls of sugar she used.

If he makes 8 giant cubes, 24 small cubes, and 12 medium cubes, how many ounces of water does he have left?

It takes Gabrielle 6 minutes to finish a riddle and 3 minutes to finish a brain teaser. Over the free time she solved 9 riddles and 5 brain teasers. How much time did she spend playing these games?

Benjamin has a bag of beads with 100 inside. He tripped over stick while carrying it and dropped 2/5 of them. He scrambled to search for them but only came up with 15. When he went back home, he inspected the beads further. Nine of them he picked up weren't beads, but actually coins so he got rid of it. How many beads did Benjamin end up with?

On Wednesday, Esteban wants to exercise for thrice the amount of time he did on Tuesday and Monday combined. On Monday he exercised for 40 minutes. On Tuesday he exercised for 55 minutes. How many minutes does he have to exercise on Wednesday to reach his goal?

Mia has a flower bed that is 195 meters long. Mia wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Mia's flowers grow 4 meters wide so she needs to leave 15.0 meters between every plant. Mia already owns 12 flowers. Each flowering plant costs €14 at the store, how much money will Mia spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?

Haruka is trying to decide whether to do her financial planning herself or hire one tax consultant. If she does it herself, she'll be able to do 9 fewer hours of part-time work, losing ₺93/hour in missed income. The tax consultant charges ₺148. How much more money will she have if she hires the tax consultant?

I have 18 liters of apple drink that are 2/3 water and I wish to add it to 30 liters of lemon drink that is 4/5 water. But as I pour it, I spill 3 liters of the apple drink. How much water is in the remaining 45 liters?
A carpenter works for 4 weeks every month and for 6 days every week. If he gets paid ¥85 every day, how much does he earn if he works for a year?

There are currently 14 yellow balls, 21 blue balls, and 33 red balls in the store. Yellow balls cost ₣11, red balls cost ₣4, and blue balls cost ₣6. How much will the store have received after all the balls are sold?

There are 129 second-graders at Oak Ridge School. 58 of them are girls. On Tuesday, 3 second-grade girls and 6 second-grade boys were absent. How many second grade boys were at Oak Ridge School on Tuesday?
Ananya is required to submit a 36-page report. She already finished writing five-sixths of the report. How many pages does she have left to write?

Comet Encke orbits the sun every 55 years. Viktor's grandfather saw the Comet when he was 41 years old. Viktor saw the comet a second time when he was two times the age his grandfather was when he saw the Comet. How old was Viktor when he saw the Comet for the first time?

Yusuf works a 7-hour shift each day, 5 days a week. He earns $24 per hour and gets a $166 bonus each week if the company performs well. How much money did Yusuf make in July if the company performed very well for the whole month?
Yara finished two-fifths of a 140 piece puzzle, and then started and finished another 650 piece puzzle within an hour. How many puzzle pieces did Yara place during that hour?

Umar was a pen pal with 7 people. He stopped being penpals with 2 of them. They each send 3 letters a week that are 6 pages long. He responds in kind. He can write a page every 6 minutes. How many hours does he spend writing a week?
The Halloween candy hunt team hid 170 eggs. The Mirzakhani twins each found 35 eggs. All the other eggs except 17 were found by their friends. How many eggs did the friends find?

At the beginning of the gathering, there were 30 artists and 36 lawyers. After an hour, two-fourths of the total number of people left. How many lawyers are left if 19 artists stayed at the gathering?

Kai is feeding his livestock silage. Each goat needs 13 pounds, and each cow needs 4 pounds less than twice the amount each goat needs. If there are 13 goats and 37 cows, how many pounds of silage does Kai need?
If Gabriel and Oscar have 580 yards of fence between them, and they agree to split it with Oscar getting 190 yards more than Gabriel, how much is left over for Gabriel?
Aisha buys 5 shares of a stock for ₣56 each. The stock price increases 75% the first year Aisha holds it, then decreases 10% in the second year. What is the final value of all Aisha's shares?

Haruka qualified for a spot on the volleyball team, so she went shopping for some athletic gear. She bought a sports bra for ₺20, a pair of volleyball sweatpants for ₺8 more than the sports bra cost, and a pair of athletic shoes that were originally ₺50 but were on sale for one-half price. She had a coupon for ₺2 off the package of ₺10 athletic wristbands that she also bought. How much did she spend on athletic gear?

The Jones family is busy making biscuits. So far, they've made 8050 biscuits. They have 2066 peanut butter biscuits, 2492 blueberry biscuits, and some strawberry biscuits. How many strawberry biscuits have they made?

Esteban's SUV breaks down. The SUV weighs 2000 kilograms and he has furniture in it weighing 450 kilograms. He also has his 2 young teammates who weigh 65 kilograms each in it. If the force to move the SUV is 5% of the weight, how much force does he need to push the SUV?

But Esteban, having forgotten his sword at home, slew one-fifth as many giants as Sanjay using a nail file. How many giants has Esteban slain?

The go-karts cost $5 a ride. How many friends can she invite?

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 12 minutes to cover every 4 miles of the city. If the city is 76 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover the whole city?

How many signatures do the sisters need to collect to reach their goal?

Later, her husband also bought a package of 19 new plates and gave them to Gabrielle. While Gabrielle was making the shrimp scampi, she used seven of the plates to sample her shrimp scampi. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 34 plates. How many plates were in the package that Gabrielle bought?
Ravi receives 100 emails a day. 18% of those emails don't require any response. Ravi responds to the rest of them. How many emails does Ravi respond to in a 5 day work week?

Zahra is knitting winter wear for her 5 grandchildren. They're quintuplets, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a beanie, poncho, vest, booties, and gloves for each of them. It takes 10 skeins of wool to make a beanie, 9 for a poncho, 13 for a vest, 17 for a pair of booties, and 15 for a pair of gloves. How many skeins of wool will she need to buy?
Aisha and Arash are currently 24 years apart in age. If Aisha, who is younger than Arash, is 65 years old, what's the average of their ages?
Theo is 23 years old. In 6 years his cousin Leilani will be 4 times as old as Theo is now. How old is Leilani right now?
A grandfather eats 3 pizzas per day, his partner eats 3 pizzas per day, and their son eats 4 pizzas per day. How many pizzas does this family eat in one month?
Leon has ₣96.44 and wants to buy 28 washers from a bin at the construction supply store. Each washer costs ₣0.23. How much money does Leon have left after paying for the washers?

Valeria walks 32 kilometers every day on her favorite walking trail, which includes 15 kilometers of walking on the beach and 17 kilometers of walking on the sidewalk. On the sidewalk, Valeria walks at two times the rate of speed that she does on the beach. If 60 minutes of her walk is spent on the beach, how long does it take for her to complete the entire 32-kilometer walk, in minutes?

A medical center has a capacity of 1700 rooms with 1/10 occupied. Due to the major accident, 30 patients are admitted into the medical center each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied rooms in the medical center after 4 weeks.

Leon watches TV after he finishes his homework every night. On Thursday and Friday, he watched a 4-hour episode of his favorite show each night. On Saturday, he watched a few episodes of a 15-minute show. On Sunday, he finished homework early and watched a 5-hour episode and a 15-minute show. On Monday, he got to stay up late, so he watched three 2-hour episodes. If he watched 21 hours of TV in all, how many 15-minute episodes did he watch on Saturday?

Mrs. Lee is looking for a townhouse that will not go beyond her $480000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $440000. On top of that, the buyer has to pay a brokerage fee which is 6% of the selling price, and also the transfer fee that is 13% of the selling price. How much more is the total price of the townhouse than Mrs. Lee's budget?

Nadia and Aisha are sisters from Stockholm who love collecting signatures from movie stars. During their winter break from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After 4 weeks, Nadia and Aisha compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. Nadia has 16 signatures in her book, and Aisha has 37. The sisters have 3 more weeks of winter break, and they decide they want to reach 105 signatures between them by the end of the break. How many signatures do the sisters need to collect to reach their goal?

Elena went to the patisserie and bought various types of baked goods. She bought 4 dozen croissants which cost $17 per dozen, 5 dozen macarons which cost $77 per dozen, and 5 dozen brownies for $115 per dozen. How much was the total cost?
A loaf of sourdough at the cafe costs €6. Muffins cost €3 each. How much more do 7 loaves of sourdough cost than 2 muffins?

Luis goes to the store to buy some rice. The normal brand of rice he buys costs ¥20 per kg. He had to buy a more expensive brand that costs 15% more since his favorite brand was sold out. He decides to buy a week's worth of rice and he uses 1 kg of rice per day. He also decided to buy himself a bagel for ¥3. How much did everything cost?
Keisha went to their backyard to pick some cherries and found three-sixths as many bees as ladybugs in the field. If there were 58 ladybugs, calculate the total number of insects in the field.

A maintenance worker has to clean a university with 120 rooms. They have 5 days to get it done. It takes them 20 minutes per room. If they work 16 hours each day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning rooms?
A building is made out of 5 black bricks, three times as many pink bricks, and an unknown number of white bricks. If there are 29 bricks in the building in total, how many white bricks are there?

Mr. Williams sold his condo for $620000. He paid the transfer fees that amount to 4% of the selling price and also paid a brokerage fee that is 3% of the selling price. If he also paid $520000 for the remaining loan amount of the condo, how much is Mr. Williams's net proceeds from selling the condo?

Riverside Academy is holding graduation in their Gymnasium this year which has space for 3500 people. After accounting for 850 seats for graduates and 100 seats for faculty attending, how many tickets would each graduate receive to give to their friends and family if the tickets are split equally?
There are 36 girls in the garden. If there are one-sixth the number of boys in the garden, how many kids are in the garden?
A cake has 24 portions. If Esteban can eat 3 portions a day while Keisha can eat seven times as much, how many days will the cake last?

Leilani hid 9 dozen eggs in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Roya finds 5 eggs. Tariq finds eight times as many as Roya. Liam finds 2 less than Tariq, and Santiago finds 1/2 as many as Liam. How many eggs are still hidden in the yard?

Thiago is raising money for a science fair. He has applied for help from the parent association, which has decided to cover 1/5 of the cost of the science fair. How much money is Thiago missing if he has ₺115 and the science fair costs ₺570?

Yusuf has a flower stand at the community market. He sells three kinds of flowers: roses, sunflowers and daisies. He usually sells roses for $2.58 per basket, sunflowers for $5.13 per basket and daisies for $5.47 per basket. Yusuf has no change today, so he has decided to round all his prices to the nearest dollar. If Yusuf sells 18 baskets of roses, 28 baskets of sunflowers and 35 baskets of daisies, how much will he make?

Sanjay collects garbage from 3 different apartment complexes. The first 2 have 100 apartments each and the last one is 30% bigger than the other 2 combined. Sanjay collects garbage 3 times a week from each place and he gets paid $0.3 per collection for each apartment. How much money does he make in a week?
Rania scored 357 points in one game of darts. Winnie scored 46 points more than four-sixths as many as Rania. How many points did Rania and Winnie have in total?
Gabrielle sliced a whole peach into 32 pieces. She ate 3 slices, her cousin ate 5 more than her, and her brother ate 4 more than her cousin. How many slices of peach did they all eat?
The area of Xavier's rectangular kitchen is 675 square meters. If the length of his room is 5 meters, what is the perimeter of the room in meters?
Luis has 9 $10 bills. He buys 3 toy cars for $4 each. He also buys 6 packs of stickers for $5 each. How much money does he have left?

Ali has 15 tubes of teal paint and 18 tubes of indigo paint. Santiago has 1/3 as many tubes of teal paint as Ali, and eight times as many tubes of indigo paint as Ali. How many tubes of paint does Santiago have?

Sophia has a flower bed that is 150 feet long. Sophia wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Sophia's flowers grow 6 feet wide so she needs to leave 12.5 feet between every plant. Sophia already owns 11 flowers. Each flowering plant costs ₣7 at the store, how much money will Sophia spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?
Sofia can peel 4 mushrooms a minute and saute 40 mushrooms in 17 minutes. How long will it take her to peel and saute 120 mushrooms?
In a set of artist's cards, there are 75 green cards, and 20% more purple cards. Orange cards are as many as the sum of green and purple cards. How many cards of all mentioned colors are there?
A cup of tea is 10 ounces of tea. Yusuf drinks 2 cups of tea. If tea has 2 calories per ounce how many calories did he consume?

James works a 11-hour shift each day, 6 days a week. He earns $11 per hour and gets a $437 bonus each week if the company performs well. How much money did James make in January if the company performed very well for the whole month?

Liam has a bag of marbles with 42 inside. He tripped over root while carrying it and dropped one-half of them. He scrambled to search for them but only came up with 9. When he went back home, he inspected the marbles further. Eight of them he picked up weren't marbles, but actually beads so he got rid of it. How many marbles did Liam end up with?
A kid has 11 stickers. His cousin has 8 fewer stickers than he has. How many stickers do they have together?

Olivia has 4 jars of sprinkles in her pantry. Each jar of sprinkles can decorate 6 cupcakes. Olivia wants to bake enough cupcakes to use up all of her sprinkles. If each pan holds 12 cupcakes, how many pans worth of cupcakes should she bake?

I have 17 liters of grape drink that are 1/4 water and I wish to add it to 16 liters of mango drink that is three-sixths water. But as I pour it, I spill 5 liters of the grape drink. How much water is in the remaining 28 liters?

Valeria went to the boardwalk for vacation. Her parents gave her €1300 to buy whatever she wanted. At the gift shop, saltwater taffy was on sale for "Buy 15 kilograms at €20 per kilogram, get 5 kilograms 1/4 off." She scooped up 22 kilograms. She also bought a mixed bag of starfish for €11.5 and 17 keychains that were €20.5 each. How much money does Valeria have left?

One gnome can mine 5 pounds of ore per day with wooden pickaxe. He can mine two times as much with a silver pickaxe and 60% more with a mithril pickaxe than with a silver pickaxe. How many pounds of ore can 20 gnomes with mithril pickaxes mine in a month with 31 days?

On Tuesday, Benjamin wants to exercise for five times the amount of time he did on Monday and Sunday combined. On Sunday he exercised for 25 minutes. On Monday he exercised for 44 minutes. How many minutes does he have to exercise on Tuesday to reach his goal?
Pavel has 96 light purple spools of thread, 80 dark purple spools of thread, 71 light cyan spools of thread, and 73 dark cyan spools of thread. What percent of the spools are purple?

It takes Camila 24 minutes to finish a word puzzle and 7 minutes to finish a chess puzzle. Over the day off she solved 5 word puzzles and 4 chess puzzles. How much time did she spend playing these games?

Theo is feeding his livestock feed. Each turkey needs 8 pounds, and each duck needs 1 pounds less than twice the amount each turkey needs. If there are 44 turkeys and 24 ducks, how many pounds of feed does Theo need?
A landscaper works for 4 weeks every month and for 4 days every week. If he gets paid ₺115 every day, how much does he earn if he works for a year?

Comet Hale-Bopp orbits the sun every 50 years. Arjun's father saw the Comet when he was 20 years old. Arjun saw the comet a second time when he was four times the age his father was when he saw the Comet. How old was Arjun when he saw the Comet for the first time?

There are 195 second-graders at Maple Grove School. 59 of them are girls. On Tuesday, 3 second-grade girls and 2 second-grade boys were absent. How many second grade boys were at Maple Grove School on Tuesday?

Priya is trying to decide whether to do her business accounting herself or hire one bookkeeper. If she does it herself, she'll be able to do 6 fewer hours of contract work, losing $46/hour in missed income. The bookkeeper charges $109. How much more money will she have if she hires the bookkeeper?
Emma is required to submit a 144-page thesis. She already finished writing one-third of the thesis. How many pages does she have left to write?

Sanjay caught 4 trouts last Tuesday, the first trout he caught weighs 63 pounds, the second trout he caught weighs 54 pounds, and the last trout he caught weighs 23 pounds. If a pound of trout costs ₣1.0, how much will he earn after selling all the trouts to the market?

Valeria is learning to write and decides to keep re-writing the farsi alphabet (with 32 letters) until she knows it. She writes it in full six times, writes three-sixths of it once, then re-writes everything she has already written. How many letters has Valeria written in total?
Fatima finished 1/3 of a 102 piece puzzle, and then started and finished another 363 piece puzzle within an hour. How many puzzle pieces did Fatima place during that hour?
The Treasure hunt team hid 90 treats. The Lee twins each found 40 treats. All the other treats except 6 were found by their friends. How many treats did the friends find?

The Smith family is busy making muffins. So far, they've made 9550 muffins. They have 2165 peanut butter muffins, 1869 strawberry muffins, and some blueberry muffins. How many blueberry muffins have they made?

There are currently 7 green balls, 10 orange balls, and 37 blue balls in the store. Green balls cost ¥6, blue balls cost ¥5, and orange balls cost ¥5. How much will the store have received after all the balls are sold?

There are 6 periods in the day for a normal student but Faisal has to take 2 extra classes. Each class is 30 minutes long. He goes to class for 4 days a week. He then spends one-eighth of his weekly minutes each on Saturday and Sunday as extra learning time. How many hours a week does he spend learning?

Carlos's van breaks down. The van weighs 1950 kilograms and he has groceries in it weighing 275 kilograms. He also has his 4 young friends who weigh 50 kilograms each in it. If the force to move the van is 4% of the weight, how much force does he need to push the van?
If Haruka and Andre have 180 feet of fence between them, and they agree to split it with Andre getting 70 feet more than Haruka, how much is left over for Haruka?

The biggest waterslide at Neptunes Kingdom is 280 meters long, and people slide down at 70 meters/minute. The second biggest waterslide is 270 meters long, but steeper, so people slide down at 90 meters/minute. How much longer does it take to ride the biggest slide compared to the second biggest slide?

Ananya qualified for a spot on the cycling team, so she went shopping for some athletic gear. She bought a t-shirt for €11, a pair of cycling shorts for €6 more than the t-shirt cost, and a pair of sneakers that were originally €54 but were on sale for two-thirds price. She had a coupon for €4 off the package of €13 athletic socks that she also bought. How much did she spend on athletic gear?
Kayla buys 15 shares of a stock for €65 each. The stock price increases 80% the first year Kayla holds it, then decreases 20% in the second year. What is the final value of all Kayla's shares?
Bodhi has nine times as many Twitter friends as Viktor. Chen has seven times as many friends on Twitter as Viktor. If Bodhi has 27 friends on Twitter, how many Twitter friends does Chen have?

Leon was a pen pal with 8 people. He stopped being penpals with 4 of them. They each send 4 letters a week that are 9 pages long. He responds in kind. He can write a page every 10 minutes. How many hours does he spend writing a week?

Jamal slew 50 trolls with his mighty sword, while Oliver, using a spear, slew 1/5 as many trolls as Jamal. Using a rusty iron axe, Santiago slew eight times as many trolls as Oliver. But Alejandro, having forgotten his sword at home, slew four-fifths as many trolls as Santiago using a nail file. How many trolls has Alejandro slain?

There are 4 students playing volleyball and seven times that number playing table tennis. There are 20 boys and 28 girls playing basketball. If each student only participates in one group, how many students are there in total?
Xavier hires a boat from 5 PM to 9 PM. He gets 2 hours free. The first paid hour is €30 and each hour after that is twice the cost. How much did he pay?
The vending machines sell pretzels for 70 cents and gum for 105 cents. Santiago spent €1100 and got 4 bags of pretzels and had 2% of his money left in change. How many gum did he buy?

Olivia can run nine times faster than she can walk, but she can skip at a rate of speed that is two-thirds as fast as she can run. If she can skip at 6 miles per hour, how many miles can she travel in 6 hours if she spends four-sixths of the time running and one-third of the time walking?

At Alejandro's house, there are three times as many pears as corns. He has a total of 43 corns in his house. Alejandro bought 48 more corns at the store and 10 fewer pears than the number of corns. Find the combined total of the number of pears and corns Alejandro has in the house?

510 people apply for a job at Netflix. Of the people that apply, only 40% receive interviews. Of those who receive interviews, 50% receive a job offer. Of those who receive a job offer, four-sixths of the people accept the position. How many people accept the position?
At the beginning of the party, there were 67 artists and 32 doctors. After half an hour, 1/3 of the total number of people left. How many doctors are left if 30 artists stayed at the party?
If Gabriel eats 3 eggs a day for 84 days and then increases it to 4 eggs a day for 48 days, how many dozens of eggs will Gabriel need for 132 days?

Olga operates the cash register exactly seven times as fast as her less-experienced colleague Ananya. Daily, Ananya processes 35 customers. What is the total weekly production for the two if they work all days of the week?

When the water is cold Chen swims a mile in 20 minutes. When the water is warm Chen swims a mile in 6 minutes more than two times as long. How much longer does Chen take to swim 9 miles on a hot day than a cold day?

Xena's aunt said that she had ¥160 budgeted for her birthday party. The go-karts cost ¥7 a ride. How many friends can she invite?

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 323 minutes to cover every 25 miles of the city. If the city is 25 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover the whole city?
Luis has 70 square yards of plum field. There are 88 plums per square yard. Luis can harvest his plums every 12 months. How many plums can Luis harvest within a year?

Yara makes tea using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in the ratio of 29:5. If she used a total of 476 teaspoons of sugar and cups of water, calculate the number of teaspoonfuls of sugar she used.

Noah saw a 220-foot whale with 2 66-inch remoras attached to it. What percentage of the whale's body length is the combined length of the remoras?

A farmer is buying feed for his sheep. He buys a variety of hay, corns, beets and apples. Since apples are a rare treat, he only buys four 3-kg boxes of them for the whole stable. He only wants enough beets to feed the sheep while the vegetables are fresh, so he buys twelve 7-kg bags. Hay are the main diet of his sheep, so he buys thirty five 39-kg packs. Noah places bananas on some baskets. Each basket can hold 23 bananas. If he has 286 bananas and 12 baskets, how many bananas won't he be able to place on the basket?

The kernels increase to 3 times the initial popping rate in the next 20 seconds, but in the final 20 seconds, the popping slows down to half the rate as the past 20 seconds. After Viktor takes the skillet off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 20 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. How many pieces of popcorn does Viktor have to eat?

Thiago wants to make different sized ice cubes with 330 grams of water. He can make giant cubes that use 13 grams per cube, medium cubes that use 11 grams, and small cubes that use 1/8 of gram. If he makes 9 giant cubes, 24 small cubes, and 12 medium cubes, how many grams of water does he have left?

The area of DeShawn's rectangular living room is 360 square feet. If the length of his room is 5 yards, what is the perimeter of the room in feet?

Ravi has 12 tubes of white paint and 11 tubes of yellow paint. Noah has one-sixth as many tubes of white paint as Ravi, and nine times as many tubes of yellow paint as Ravi. How many tubes of paint does Noah have?
Qasim has 7 $50 bills. He buys 12 toy cars for $9 each. He also buys 2 packs of stickers for $9 each. How much money does he have left?
There are 42 girls in the garden. If there are two-thirds the number of boys in the garden, how many kids are in the garden?
Ava sliced a whole mango into 31 pieces. She ate 4 slices, her sister ate 5 more than her, and her brother ate 7 more than her sister. How many slices of mango did they all eat?

Fatima is learning to write and decides to keep re-writing the hiragana (with 48 letters) until she knows it. She writes it in full three times, writes 2/4 of it once, then re-writes everything she has already written. How many letters has Fatima written in total?
A kid has 11 toys. His cousin has 9 fewer toys than he has. How many toys do they have together?
In a set of chef's cards, there are 60 yellow cards, and 30% more red cards. Purple cards are as many as the sum of yellow and red cards. How many cards of all mentioned colors are there?

Kimia has a flower bed that is 210 feet long. Kimia wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Kimia's flowers grow 6 feet wide so she needs to leave 17.5 feet between every plant. Kimia already owns 11 flowers. Each flowering plant costs ¥14 at the store, how much money will Kimia spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?

Nia has 12 jars of icing in her kitchen cabinet. Each jar of icing can decorate 12 brownies. Nia wants to bake enough brownies to use up all of her icing. If each baking sheet holds 8 brownies, how many baking sheets worth of brownies should she bake?

One gnome can mine 5 pounds of ore per day with basic shovel. He can mine twice as much with a bronze pickaxe and 30% more with a mithril pickaxe than with a bronze pickaxe. How many pounds of ore can 25 gnomes with mithril pickaxes mine in a month with 29 days?
Keisha has 82 light cyan spools of thread, 116 dark cyan spools of thread, 74 light turquoise spools of thread, and 88 dark turquoise spools of thread. What percent of the spools are cyan?

Benjamin works a 6-hour shift each day, 6 days a week. He earns $11 per hour and gets a $404 bonus each week if the company performs well. How much money did Benjamin make in February if the company performed very well for the whole month?
It takes Priya 22 minutes to finish a brain teaser and 16 minutes to finish a riddle. Over the free time she solved 5 brain teasers and 6 riddles. How much time did she spend playing these games?

Olga is trying to decide whether to do her taxes herself or hire one tax consultant. If she does it herself, she'll be able to do 10 fewer hours of part-time work, losing ¥34/hour in missed income. The tax consultant charges ¥64. How much more money will she have if she hires the tax consultant?

I have 13 liters of grape drink that are one-eighth water and I wish to add it to 15 liters of mango drink that is two-sixths water. But as I pour it, I spill 5 liters of the grape drink. How much water is in the remaining 23 liters?

Hiroshi's SUV breaks down. The SUV weighs 2150 kilograms and he has furniture in it weighing 250 kilograms. He also has his 4 young teammates who weigh 50 kilograms each in it. If the force to move the SUV is 1% of the weight, how much force does he need to push the SUV?

Yuki has a bag of pebbles with 84 inside. He tripped over rock while carrying it and dropped 3/4 of them. He scrambled to search for them but only came up with 11. When he went back home, he inspected the pebbles further. Three of them he picked up weren't pebbles, but actually buttons so he got rid of it. How many pebbles did Yuki end up with?
A landscaper works for 4 weeks every month and for 6 days every week. If he gets paid ₺95 every day, how much does he earn if he works for a year?
Oscar is feeding his livestock hay. Each pig needs 11 kg, and each duck needs 8 kg less than twice the amount each pig needs. If there are 11 pigs and 10 ducks, how many kg of hay does Oscar need?

On Monday, Oscar wants to exercise for six times the amount of time he did on Sunday and Saturday combined. On Saturday he exercised for 23 minutes. On Sunday he exercised for 44 minutes. How many minutes does he have to exercise on Monday to reach his goal?
Emma is required to submit a 75-page thesis. She already finished writing 1/3 of the thesis. How many pages does she have left to write?

Viktor was a pen pal with 6 people. He stopped being penpals with 1 of them. They each send 2 letters a week that are 9 pages long. He responds in kind. He can write a page every 10 minutes. How many hours does he spend writing a week?

There are 186 third-graders at Sunny Hill School. 28 of them are girls. On Wednesday, 5 third-grade girls and 2 third-grade boys were absent. How many third grade boys were at Sunny Hill School on Wednesday?
Alejandro finished two-fourths of a 490 piece puzzle, and then started and finished another 951 piece puzzle within an hour. How many puzzle pieces did Alejandro place during that hour?

There are currently 14 red balls, 18 blue balls, and 26 yellow balls in the warehouse. Red balls cost ₺6, yellow balls cost ₺7, and blue balls cost ₺5. How much will the warehouse have received after all the balls are sold?
The Treasure hunt team hid 200 balls. The Lee twins each found 39 balls. All the other balls except 16 were found by their friends. How many balls did the friends find?

There are 8 periods in the day for a normal student but Oscar has to take 3 extra classes. Each class is 40 minutes long. He goes to class for 5 days a week. He then spends one-tenth of his weekly minutes each on Saturday and Sunday as extra learning time. How many hours a week does he spend learning?

The Smith family is busy making cupcakes. So far, they've made 7225 cupcakes. They have 2303 peanut butter cupcakes, 1218 lemon cupcakes, and some blueberry cupcakes. How many blueberry cupcakes have they made?
Emma buys 12 shares of a stock for ₣40 each. The stock price increases 75% the first year Emma holds it, then decreases 40% in the second year. What is the final value of all Emma's shares?
If Uma and Ananya have 460 meters of fence between them, and they agree to split it with Ananya getting 100 meters more than Uma, how much is left over for Uma?

The biggest waterslide at Aqua Adventure is 270 meters long, and people slide down at 45 meters/minute. The second biggest waterslide is 260 meters long, but steeper, so people slide down at 65 meters/minute. How much longer does it take to ride the biggest slide compared to the second biggest slide?

Mohammed caught 5 steelheads last Tuesday, the first steelhead he caught weighs 64 kgs, the second steelhead he caught weighs 48 kgs, and the last steelhead he caught weighs 23 kgs. If a kg of steelhead costs €1.0, how much will he earn after selling all the steelheads to the market?

Comet Hyakutake orbits the sun every 70 years. Santiago's uncle saw the Comet when he was 44 years old. Santiago saw the comet a second time when he was two times the age his uncle was when he saw the Comet. How old was Santiago when he saw the Comet for the first time?

Isabella has four times as many Snapchat friends as Olga. Mohammed has ten times as many friends on Snapchat as Olga. If Isabella has 160 friends on Snapchat, how many Snapchat friends does Mohammed have?

Luca slew 300 orcs with his mighty mace, while Jamal, using a lance, slew one-sixth as many orcs as Luca. Using a wooden club, Mohammed slew eight times as many orcs as Jamal. But Qasim, having forgotten his axe at home, slew one-fourth as many orcs as Mohammed using a butter knife. How many orcs has Qasim slain?

Fatima qualified for a spot on the soccer team, so she went shopping for some athletic gear. She bought a jersey for ¥17, a pair of soccer leggings for ¥7 more than the jersey cost, and a pair of cleats that were originally ¥42 but were on sale for 2/4 price. She had a coupon for ¥3 off the package of ¥6 athletic headbands that she also bought. How much did she spend on athletic gear?

Fatima can run four times faster than she can walk, but she can skip at a rate of speed that is 3/4 as fast as she can run. If she can skip at 9 miles per hour, how many miles can she travel in 8 hours if she spends three-fourths of the time running and 1/4 of the time walking?

When the water is cold Sophia swims a mile in 24 minutes. When the water is warm Sophia swims a mile in 7 minutes more than twice as long. How much longer does Sophia take to swim 3 miles on a hot day than a cold day?

There are 4 students playing football and seven times that number playing table tennis. There are 19 boys and 10 girls playing basketball. If each student only participates in one group, how many students are there in total?

384 people apply for a job at Facebook. Of the people that apply, only 50% receive interviews. Of those who receive interviews, 50% receive a job offer. Of those who receive a job offer, one-eighth of the people accept the position. How many people accept the position?
James hires a party bus from 6 PM to 11 PM. He gets 2 hours free. The first paid hour is ¥44 and each hour after that is twice the cost. How much did he pay?
The vending machines sell crackers for 25 cents and popcorn for 125 cents. Yusuf spent €800 and got 1 bags of crackers and had 2% of his money left in change. How many popcorn did he buy?
If Oliver eats 3 eggs a day for 59 days and then increases it to 7 eggs a day for 93 days, how many dozens of eggs will Oliver need for 152 days?

Leilani operates the cash register exactly eight times as fast as her less-experienced colleague Chen. Daily, Chen processes 68 customers. What is the total weekly production for the two if they work all days of the week?
At the beginning of the meeting, there were 65 teachers and 45 artists. After two hours, 1/5 of the total number of people left. How many artists are left if 28 teachers stayed at the meeting?

Sophia's aunt said that she had €120 budgeted for her birthday party. She wants to make sure she and her friends all get to play one round of mini-golf, have €6 in arcade tokens, and get to ride the go-karts three times. A round of mini-golf is €4. The go-karts cost €10 a ride. How many friends can she invite?
A new parasite infects 5 people. Every day, each infected person infects 4 others. How many people are infected after 4 days?

At Ravi's house, there are ten times as many persimmons as grapes. He has a total of 31 grapes in his house. Ravi bought 44 more grapes at the store and 24 fewer persimmons than the number of grapes. Find the combined total of the number of persimmons and grapes Ravi has in the house?

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 92 minutes to cover every 9 miles of the city. If the city is 45 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover the whole city?

Haruka makes coffee using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in the ratio of 74:6. If she used a total of 1280 teaspoons of sugar and cups of water, calculate the number of teaspoonfuls of sugar she used.
Theo has 5 hectares of banana field. There are 20 bananas per hectare. Theo can harvest his bananas every 6 months. How many bananas can Theo harvest within a year?

Camila is popping popcorn for a snack. As the pot of kernels heats up, the kernels start popping faster. 40 pop in the first 30 seconds of cooking, then 2 times that amount in the next 30 seconds. The kernels increase to 4 times the initial popping rate in the next 30 seconds, but in the final 30 seconds, the popping slows down to half the rate as the past 30 seconds. After Camila takes the pot off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 30 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. How many pieces of popcorn does Camila have to eat?

A group of 154 students has various hobbies. 13 like to bake, 40 like to play football, and the rest like to either play music or read. How many like to play music if the number that like to read is twice the number that prefer playing football?
Emma saw a 360-foot dolphin with 6 72-inch remoras attached to it. What percentage of the dolphin's body length is the combined length of the remoras?

A farmer is buying feed for his horses. He buys a variety of oats, apples, carrots and corns. Since corns are a rare treat, he only buys six 5-pound boxes of them for the whole stable. He only wants enough carrots to feed the horses while the vegetables are fresh, so he buys fourteen 6-pound bags. Oats are the main diet of his horses, so he buys thirty two 41-pound packs. Apples are a staple to supplement the oats, so he buys eighteen 18-pound sacks. If his farm truck can carry 250 pounds at a time, how many trips does the farmer need to transport all the feed?

When Uma watches her nephew, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 71 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 41 stuffed animals inside. The tower of stacking rings has 32 multicolored rings on it. Uma recently bought a tube of bouncy balls, bringing her total number of toys for her nephew up to 222. How many bouncy balls came in the tube?
A juggler can juggle 960 balls. 1/10 of the balls are golf balls, and 1/6 of the golf balls are gray. How many gray golf balls are there?
James is rolling a d20 die. How much more likely is it (expressed as a percentage) that he rolls a number greater than 2 than that he rolls two even numbers in a row?

Carlos wants to make different sized ice cubes with 324 ounces of water. He can make giant cubes that use 12 ounces per cube, medium cubes that use 11 ounces, and small cubes that use 1/2 of ounce. If he makes 10 giant cubes, 24 small cubes, and 12 medium cubes, how many ounces of water does he have left?
To make a call from a phone booth, you must pay €0.8 for each minute of your call. After 10 minutes, that price drops to €0.7 per minute. How much would a 80-minute call cost?
Xavier places bananas on some baskets. Each basket can hold 24 bananas. If he has 294 bananas and 12 baskets, how many bananas won't he be able to place on the basket?

Hiroshi and Rania have 81 minutes to walk to the gym together. It takes them 13 minutes to get to the corner where the mall is. It takes them another 13 minutes to get to the park. How much longer do they have to get to gym without being late?

Chen walks 26 miles every day on her favorite walking trail, which includes 13 miles of walking on the beach and 13 miles of walking on the sidewalk. On the sidewalk, Chen walks at two times the rate of speed that she does on the beach. If 52 minutes of her walk is spent on the beach, how long does it take for her to complete the entire 26-mile walk, in minutes?
Pavel picks 374 bananas on Friday. Then he picks 141 bananas on Saturday. On Sunday, he picks triple the number of bananas he did on Friday. How many bananas does Pavel have?

Camila is an avid gardener. Last week, she received 38 new potted plants from her favorite plant nursery. She already has 9 potted plants on each of the 55 window ledges of her large country home. Feeling generous, she has decided that she will give 3 potted plants from each ledge to friends and family tomorrow. How many potted plants will Camila remain with?
Deshawn went to buy some school supplies. He bought 16 rulers which cost $5.5 each, 6 erasers which cost $15.5 each, and a rim of bond paper which cost $22. How much did DeShawn spend on everything?

Fatima is knitting winter wear for her 4 grandchildren. They're quadruplets, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a tunic, sweater, shawl, mittens, and gloves for each of them. It takes 13 skeins of wool to make a tunic, 6 for a sweater, 11 for a shawl, 5 for a pair of mittens, and 17 for a pair of gloves. How many skeins of wool will she need to buy?

Ibrahim is selling brownie and pear pie for a fundraiser. On Sunday, he sold 21 boxes of brownie and 14 fewer boxes of pear pie, than on Monday. On Monday, he sold 13 more boxes of brownies than on Sunday and 22 boxes of pear pie. If the brownie cost $9 and the pear pie cost $28, how much did Ibrahim earn for two days?

Faisal watches TV after he finishes his homework every night. On Sunday and Monday, he watched a 5-hour episode of his favorite show each night. On Tuesday, he watched a few episodes of a 45-minute show. On Wednesday, he finished homework early and watched a 5-hour episode and a 15-minute show. On Thursday, he got to stay up late, so he watched three 5-hour episodes. If he watched 31 hours of TV in all, how many 45-minute episodes did he watch on Tuesday?
A father eats 7 sushi rolls per day, his wife eats 2 sushi rolls per day, and their daughter eats 7 sushi rolls per day. How many sushi rolls does this family eat in one week?

Ananya was preparing for a lunch party at her house, where she intended to serve shrimp scampi. She noticed that she was out of plastic plates, so she bought a new package of plates. Later, her husband also bought a package of 17 new plates and gave them to Ananya. While Ananya was making the shrimp scampi, she used seven of the plates to sample her shrimp scampi. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 31 plates. How many plates were in the package that Ananya bought?

In Mr. Smith's class of 100 students, 40% of the class are basketball players. Out of the remaining class, 35% of the students are choir members or part of debate team members. These 3 groups of students will need to leave early today to travel to an away tournament. How many students are leaving early?

According to its nutritional info, a bag of breads has 225 calories per serving. If a 250 ounces bag has 5 servings, how many ounces can you eat if your daily calorie target is 1975 and you have already consumed 1750 calories?
Jasmine and Santiago are currently 24 years apart in age. If Jasmine, who is younger than Santiago, is 26 years old, what's the average of their ages?

In a 100-item quiz, 40% of the questions are geography, and the rest are equally divided as history and chemistry questions. If Isabella is sure to get 70% of the geography questions, and 1/2 of the history and chemistry questions correctly, how many points is she sure to get?

Sophia and Emma are sisters from Auckland who love collecting signatures from musicians. During their fall break from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After 6 weeks, Sophia and Emma compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. Sophia has 25 signatures in her book, and Emma has 51. The sisters have 4 more weeks of fall break, and they decide they want to reach 100 signatures between them by the end of the break. How many signatures do the sisters need to collect to reach their goal?
Mateo has ₺60.08 and wants to buy 39 anchors from a bin at the hardware store. Each anchor costs ₺0.72. How much money does Mateo have left after paying for the anchors?

Mrs. Lee is looking for a townhouse that will not go beyond her $350000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $320000. On top of that, the buyer has to pay a brokerage fee which is 6% of the selling price, and also the transfer fee that is 12% of the selling price. How much more is the total price of the townhouse than Mrs. Lee's budget?

A medical center has a capacity of 1500 beds with 1/3 occupied. Due to the major accident, 25 patients are admitted into the medical center each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied beds in the medical center after 4 weeks.

Mr. Jones sold his cottage for $280000. He paid the transfer fees that amount to 3% of the selling price and also paid a brokerage fee that is 3% of the selling price. If he also paid $120000 for the remaining loan amount of the cottage, how much is Mr. Jones's net proceeds from selling the cottage?
A cake has 36 pieces. If Nia can eat 3 pieces a day while Jasmine can eat twice as much, how many days will the cake last?

Noah is raising money for a conference. He has applied for help from the local charity, which has decided to cover 1/2 of the cost of the conference. How much money is Noah missing if he has ₣135 and the conference costs ₣850?
