A loaf of bread at the bakery costs ¥9. Bagels cost ¥2 each. How much more do 7 loaves of bread cost than 9 bagels?
A building is made out of 3 orange bricks, eight times as many pink bricks, and an unknown number of green bricks. If there are 48 bricks in the building in total, how many green bricks are there?

A janitor has to clean a office building with 90 rooms. They have 10 days to get it done. It takes them 30 minutes per room. If they work 9 hours each day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning rooms?
Ravi went to their greenhouse to pick some blueberries and found 2/5 as many caterpillars as wasps in the plot. If there were 55 wasps, calculate the total number of insects in the plot.

Bodhi hid 9 dozen eggs in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Ava finds 9 eggs. Valeria finds thrice as many as Ava. Olivia finds 3 less than Valeria, and Yusuf finds 1/8 as many as Olivia. How many eggs are still hidden in the yard?

She also bought a mixed bag of coral pieces for ₺11.75 and 13 pins that were ₺21.25 each. How much money does Isabella have left?

Sakura can peel 8 carrots a minute and saute 40 carrots in 16 minutes. How long will it take her to peel and saute 120 carrots?

There are 22 girls in the field. If there are two times the number of boys in the field, how many kids are in the field?
A child has 20 pencils. His friend has 9 fewer pencils than he has. How many pencils do they have together?

Pavel's car breaks down. The car weighs 1700 pounds and he has luggage in it weighing 450 pounds. He also has his 2 young children who weigh 75 pounds each in it. If the force to move the car is 4% of the weight, how much force does he need to push the car?

It takes Leilani 16 minutes to finish a brain teaser and 13 minutes to finish a word puzzle. Over the holiday she solved 6 brain teasers and 6 word puzzles. How much time did she spend playing these games?

Elena qualified for a spot on the soccer team, so she went shopping for some athletic gear. She bought a t-shirt for ¥12, a pair of soccer shorts for ¥6 more than the t-shirt cost, and a pair of sneakers that were originally ¥62 but were on sale for one-half price. After accounting for 600 seats for graduates and 300 seats for faculty attending, how many tickets would each graduate receive to give to their friends and family if the tickets are split equally?

Prof. Jones sold his cottage for $640000. He paid the registration fees that amount to 2% of the selling price and also paid a agent fee that is 5% of the selling price. If he also paid $130000 for the remaining loan amount of the cottage, how much is Prof. Jones's net proceeds from selling the cottage?

Mateo hid 9 dozen eggs in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Daphne finds 3 eggs. Roya finds ten times as many as Daphne. Haruka finds 4 less than Roya, and Benjamin finds half as many as Haruka. How many eggs are still hidden in the yard?

Xavier collects garbage from 7 different apartment complexes. The first 6 have 400 apartments each and the last one is 30% bigger than the other 6 combined. Xavier collects garbage 5 times a week from each place and he gets paid $0.3 per collection for each apartment. How much money does he make in a week?
Fatima scored 232 points in one game of archery. Olivia scored 33 points more than two-fourths as many as Fatima. How many points did Fatima and Olivia have in total?
Fatima can peel 10 clams a minute and saute 30 clams in 7 minutes. How long will it take her to peel and saute 90 clams?

Beatriz went to the coast for vacation. Her parents gave her ₺1400 to buy whatever she wanted. At the seaside store, cotton candy was on sale for "Buy 15 pounds at ₺20 per pound, get 5 pounds 1/4 off." She scooped up 23 pounds. She also bought a mixed bag of coral pieces for ₺11.5 and 14 pins that were ₺20.75 each. How much money does Beatriz have left?
Olivia sliced a whole mango into 28 pieces. She ate 4 slices, her brother ate 5 more than her, and her sister ate 4 more than her brother. How many slices of mango did they all eat?

Santiago has a plant stand at the town square. He sells three kinds of plants: orchids, tulips and sunflowers. He usually sells orchids for ¥2.58 per bundle, tulips for ¥3.31 per bundle and sunflowers for ¥6.4 per bundle. Santiago has no change today, so he has decided to round all his prices to the nearest dollar. If Santiago sells 17 bundles of orchids, 21 bundles of tulips and 37 bundles of sunflowers, how much will he make?
A cup of sparkling water is 9 ounces of sparkling water. Jin drinks 3 cups of sparkling water. If sparkling water has 6 calories per ounce how many calories did he consume?
The area of Qasim's rectangular living room is 840 square feet. If the length of his room is 8 yards, what is the perimeter of the room in feet?
Esteban has 8 ₣5 bills. He buys 6 coloring books for ₣2 each. He also buys 3 packs of trading cards for ₣9 each. How much money does he have left?

One troll can mine 5 kgs of ore per day with basic shovel. He can mine twice as much with a bronze pickaxe and 50% more with a titanium pickaxe than with a bronze pickaxe. How many kgs of ore can 20 trolls with titanium pickaxes mine in a month with 31 days?

Rania is learning to write and decides to keep re-writing the hiragana (with 48 letters) until she knows it. She writes it in full four times, writes four-sixths of it once, then re-writes everything she has already written. How many letters has Rania written in total?
A boy has 13 toys. His brother has 9 fewer toys than he has. How many toys do they have together?

Benjamin has 18 tubes of blue paint and 18 tubes of cyan paint. Deshawn has 2/4 as many tubes of blue paint as Benjamin, and twice as many tubes of cyan paint as Benjamin. How many tubes of paint does DeShawn have?

Nadia has 12 jars of chocolate chips in her storage room. Each jar of chocolate chips can decorate 9 muffins. Nadia wants to bake enough muffins to use up all of her chocolate chips. If each rack holds 6 muffins, how many racks worth of muffins should she bake?

Viktor works a 10-hour shift each day, 5 days a week. He earns €28 per hour and gets a €158 bonus each week if the company performs well. How much money did Viktor make in January if the company performed very well for the whole month?

Tara is trying to decide whether to do her financial planning herself or hire one accountant. If she does it herself, she'll be able to do 12 fewer hours of freelance work, losing ¥41/hour in missed income. The accountant charges ¥75. How much more money will she have if she hires the accountant?

I have 19 liters of grape drink that are two-sixths water and I wish to add it to 15 liters of peach drink that is one-fifth water. But as I pour it, I spill 4 liters of the grape drink. How much water is in the remaining 30 liters?

Chen has a flower bed that is 213 meters long. Chen wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Chen's flowers grow 7 meters wide so she needs to leave 17.75 meters between every plant. Chen already owns 11 flowers. Each flowering plant costs ¥11 at the store, how much money will Chen spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?
In a set of chef's cards, there are 45 red cards, and 60% more green cards. Yellow cards are as many as the sum of red and green cards. How many cards of all mentioned colors are there?
Daphne has 47 light cyan spools of thread, 87 dark cyan spools of thread, 46 light indigo spools of thread, and 88 dark indigo spools of thread. What percent of the spools are cyan?
A plumber works for 4 weeks every month and for 4 days every week. If he gets paid $160 every day, how much does he earn if he works for a year?

It takes Tara 19 minutes to finish a chess puzzle and 15 minutes to finish a jigsaw puzzle. Over the weekend she solved 9 chess puzzles and 13 jigsaw puzzles. How much time did she spend playing these games?

Deshawn is feeding his livestock hay. Each llama needs 13 kilograms, and each alpaca needs 6 kilograms less than twice the amount each llama needs. If there are 27 llamas and 22 alpacas, how many kilograms of hay does DeShawn need?

On Monday, Umar wants to exercise for nine times the amount of time he did on Sunday and Saturday combined. On Saturday he exercised for 26 minutes. On Sunday he exercised for 58 minutes. How many minutes does he have to exercise on Monday to reach his goal?

There are currently 12 blue balls, 16 pink balls, and 44 purple balls in the store. Blue balls cost ₣12, purple balls cost ₣7, and pink balls cost ₣6. How much will the store have received after all the balls are sold?

There are 71 third-graders at Sunny Hill School. 59 of them are girls. On Wednesday, 3 third-grade girls and 8 third-grade boys were absent. How many third grade boys were at Sunny Hill School on Wednesday?

Arash caught 3 steelheads last Monday, the first steelhead he caught weighs 72 kilograms, the second steelhead he caught weighs 31 kilograms, and the last steelhead he caught weighs 38 kilograms. If a kilogram of steelhead costs ¥1.0, how much will he earn after selling all the steelheads to the market?
Leilani is required to submit a 110-page thesis. She already finished writing one-fifth of the thesis. How many pages does she have left to write?
Luca finished two-fourths of a 498 piece puzzle, and then started and finished another 443 piece puzzle within an hour. How many puzzle pieces did Luca place during that hour?

Bodhi was a pen pal with 5 people. He stopped being penpals with 2 of them. They each send 4 letters a week that are 5 pages long. He responds in kind. He can write a page every 7 minutes. How many hours does he spend writing a week?
At the beginning of the gathering, there were 52 artists and 68 nurses. After half an hour, 3/4 of the total number of people left. How many nurses are left if 19 artists stayed at the gathering?
The Treasure hunt team hid 110 balls. The Lee twins each found 44 balls. All the other balls except 11 were found by their friends. How many balls did the friends find?

The Williams family is busy making cupcakes. So far, they've made 7075 cupcakes. They have 1643 blueberry cupcakes, 2422 strawberry cupcakes, and some vanilla cupcakes. How many vanilla cupcakes have they made?

Oliver has a bag of pebbles with 24 inside. He tripped over toy while carrying it and dropped five-sixths of them. He scrambled to search for them but only came up with 16. When he went back home, he inspected the pebbles further. Five of them he picked up weren't pebbles, but actually pebbles so he got rid of it. How many pebbles did Oliver end up with?
Yara buys 10 shares of a stock for $34 each. The stock price increases 75% the first year Yara holds it, then decreases 40% in the second year. What is the final value of all Yara's shares?

The biggest waterslide at Neptunes Kingdom is 330 meters long, and people slide down at 55 meters/minute. The second biggest waterslide is 240 meters long, but steeper, so people slide down at 60 meters/minute. How much longer does it take to ride the biggest slide compared to the second biggest slide?

Oscar's SUV breaks down. The SUV weighs 1300 kilograms and he has furniture in it weighing 300 kilograms. He also has his 4 young teammates who weigh 90 kilograms each in it. If the force to move the SUV is 5% of the weight, how much force does he need to push the SUV?
The vending machines sell pretzels for 75 cents and popcorn for 100 cents. Xavier spent €900 and got 8 bags of pretzels and had 4% of his money left in change. How many popcorn did he buy?
Valeria has four times as many Twitter friends as Leon. Beatriz has thrice as many friends on Twitter as Leon. If Valeria has 104 friends on Twitter, how many Twitter friends does Beatriz have?

Quinn can run three times faster than she can walk, but she can skip at a rate of speed that is one-third as fast as she can run. If she can skip at 2 miles per hour, how many miles can she travel in 10 hours if she spends two-fifths of the time running and 3/5 of the time walking?

Comet Hyakutake orbits the sun every 80 years. Arash's uncle saw the Comet when he was 21 years old. Arash saw the comet a second time when he was four times the age his uncle was when he saw the Comet. How old was Arash when he saw the Comet for the first time?

There are 8 periods in the day for a normal student but Diego has to take 1 extra classes. Each class is 50 minutes long. He goes to class for 4 days a week. He then spends 3/4 of his weekly minutes each on Saturday and Sunday as extra learning time. How many hours a week does he spend learning?

When the water is cold Isabella swims a kilometer in 13 minutes. When the water is warm Isabella swims a kilometer in 5 minutes more than thrice as long. How much longer does Isabella take to swim 2 kilometers on a hot day than a cold day?
Alejandro hires a boat from 4 PM to 9 PM. He gets 1 hours free. The first paid hour is ¥36 and each hour after that is twice the cost. How much did he pay?

Kai slew 100 trolls with his mighty war hammer, while Yuki, using a halberd, slew two-fifths as many trolls as Kai. Using a bone dagger, Leon slew six times as many trolls as Yuki. But Faisal, having forgotten his hammer at home, slew two-thirds as many trolls as Leon using a feather. How many trolls has Faisal slain?

600 people apply for a job at Microsoft. Of the people that apply, only 50% receive interviews. Of those who receive interviews, 50% receive a job offer. Of those who receive a job offer, one-half of the people accept the position. How many people accept the position?
If Mia eats 4 eggs a day for 52 days and then increases it to 7 eggs a day for 68 days, how many dozens of eggs will Mia need for 120 days?
If Chen and Aisha have 940 feet of fence between them, and they agree to split it with Aisha getting 30 feet more than Chen, how much is left over for Chen?
A new virus infects 13 people. Every day, each infected person infects 2 others. How many people are infected after 4 days?

Mei operates the cash register exactly nine times as fast as her less-experienced colleague Ava. Daily, Ava processes 80 customers. What is the total weekly production for the two if they work all days of the week?

There are 20 students playing volleyball and seven times that number playing badminton. There are 22 boys and 21 girls playing basketball. If each student only participates in one group, how many students are there in total?

Sakura's mom said that she had ₺200 budgeted for her birthday party. She wants to make sure she and her friends all get to play one round of mini-golf, have ₺3 in arcade tokens, and get to ride the go-karts five times. A round of mini-golf is ₺7. The go-karts cost ₺18 a ride. How many friends can she invite?

Amelia qualified for a spot on the basketball team, so she went shopping for some athletic gear. She bought a jersey for ₣24, a pair of basketball leggings for ₣11 more than the jersey cost, and a pair of cleats that were originally ₣40 but were on sale for one-half price. She had a coupon for ₣3 off the package of ₣11 athletic headbands that she also bought. How much did she spend on athletic gear?

At Esteban's house, there are three times as many pears as figs. He has a total of 67 figs in his house. Esteban bought 48 more figs at the store and 38 fewer pears than the number of figs. Find the combined total of the number of pears and figs Esteban has in the house?

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 29 minutes to cover every 2 miles of the city. If the city is 36 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover the whole city?
Valentina saw a 90-foot whale with 2 54-inch remoras attached to it. What percentage of the whale's body length is the combined length of the remoras?

A group of 122 students has various hobbies. 35 like to paint, 18 like to play badminton, and the rest like to either read or hike. How many like to read if the number that like to hike is twice the number that prefer playing badminton?
Carlos has 20 square yards of pear field. There are 43 pears per square yard. Carlos can harvest his pears every 4 months. How many pears can Carlos harvest within a year?
A juggler can juggle 960 balls. An eighth of the balls are tennis balls, and 1/5 of the tennis balls are indigo. How many indigo tennis balls are there?

Chen makes tea using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in the ratio of 83:99. If she used a total of 1456 teaspoons of sugar and cups of water, calculate the number of teaspoonfuls of sugar she used.

A farmer is buying feed for his sheep. He buys a variety of hay, apples, cucumbers and corns. Since corns are a rare treat, he only buys six 7-pound boxes of them for the whole stable. He only wants enough cucumbers to feed the sheep while the vegetables are fresh, so he buys thirteen 6-pound bags. Hay are the main diet of his sheep, so he buys thirty four 40-pound packs. Apples are a staple to supplement the hay, so he buys twenty 16-pound sacks. If his farm truck can carry 120 pounds at a time, how many trips does the farmer need to transport all the feed?

When Beatriz watches her nephew, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 71 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 41 stuffed animals inside. The tower of stacking rings has 25 multicolored rings on it. Beatriz recently bought a tube of bouncy balls, bringing her total number of toys for her nephew up to 234. How many bouncy balls came in the tube?
To make a call from a hotel room phone, you must pay ₺0.5 for each minute of your call. After 26 minutes, that price drops to ₺0.4 per minute. How much would a 41-minute call cost?

Santiago and Arjun have 121 minutes to walk to the cinema together. It takes them 16 minutes to get to the corner where the mall is. It takes them another 56 minutes to get to the park. How much longer do they have to get to cinema without being late?
Tariq's dog has 1020 puppies, 230 of which have spots. Tara's dog has 460 puppies, 140 of which have spots. What percentage of all the puppies have spots?
Luca is rolling a twelve-sided die. How much more likely is it (expressed as a percentage) that he rolls a number greater than 6 than that he rolls two even numbers in a row?
Carlos places bananas on some baskets. Each basket can hold 40 bananas. If he has 346 bananas and 7 baskets, how many bananas won't he be able to place on the basket?

Kai wants to make different sized ice cubes with 344 ounces of water. He can make giant cubes that use 12 ounces per cube, medium cubes that use 11 ounces, and small cubes that use 3/5 of ounce. If he makes 10 giant cubes, 15 small cubes, and 13 medium cubes, how many ounces of water does he have left?

James is popping popcorn for a snack. As the pan of kernels heats up, the kernels start popping faster. 80 pop in the first 20 seconds of cooking, then 3 times that amount in the next 20 seconds. The kernels increase to 6 times the initial popping rate in the next 20 seconds, but in the final 20 seconds, the popping slows down to half the rate as the past 20 seconds. After James takes the pan off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 20 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. How many pieces of popcorn does James have to eat?

Mohammed went to buy some school supplies. He bought 16 markers which cost ₺8.5 each, 4 crayons which cost ₺10.5 each, and a rim of bond paper which cost ₺13. How much did Mohammed spend on everything?

Mateo is selling muffin and pomegranate pie for a fundraiser. On Tuesday, he sold 25 boxes of muffin and 11 fewer boxes of pomegranate pie, than on Wednesday. On Wednesday, he sold 14 more boxes of muffins than on Tuesday and 22 boxes of pomegranate pie. If the muffin cost ₣12 and the pomegranate pie cost ₣31, how much did Mateo earn for two days?

Sophia walks 23 miles every day on her favorite walking trail, which includes 11 miles of walking on the beach and 12 miles of walking on the sidewalk. On the sidewalk, Sophia walks at three times the rate of speed that she does on the beach. If 55 minutes of her walk is spent on the beach, how long does it take for her to complete the entire 23-mile walk, in minutes?
Hiroshi picks 172 oranges on Sunday. Then he picks 227 oranges on Monday. On Tuesday, he picks quadruple the number of oranges he did on Sunday. How many oranges does Hiroshi have?

In a 40-item quiz, 50% of the questions are physics, and the rest are equally divided as geography and geometry questions. If Quinn is sure to get 65% of the physics questions, and a tenth of the geography and geometry questions correctly, how many points is she sure to get?
Alejandro receives 50 emails a day. 22% of those emails don't require any response. Alejandro responds to the rest of them. How many emails does Alejandro respond to in a 4 day work week?

Ava was preparing for a lunch party at her house, where she intended to serve creme brulee. She noticed that she was out of plastic spoons, so she bought a new package of spoons. Later, her husband also bought a package of 6 new spoons and gave them to Ava. While Ava was making the creme brulee, she used seven of the spoons to sample her creme brulee. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 20 spoons. How many spoons were in the package that Ava bought?

Kayla is knitting winter wear for her 4 grandchildren. They're quadruplets, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a hat, poncho, cardigan, leg warmers, and socks for each of them. It takes 14 skeins of wool to make a hat, 18 for a poncho, 5 for a cardigan, 9 for a pair of leg warmers, and 3 for a pair of socks. How many skeins of wool will she need to buy?

According to its nutritional info, a bag of breads has 375 calories per serving. If a 300 ounces bag has 5 servings, how many ounces can you eat if your daily calorie target is 2225 and you have already consumed 1325 calories?

Rania is an avid gardener. Two days ago, she received 26 new potted plants from her favorite plant nursery. She already has 10 potted plants on each of the 51 window ledges of her large country home. Feeling generous, she has decided that she will give 3 potted plants from each ledge to friends and family tomorrow. How many potted plants will Rania remain with?

In Mrs. Garcia's class of 100 students, 20% of the class are swimmers. Out of the remaining class, 35% of the students are debate team members or part of dancers. These 3 groups of students will need to leave early today to travel to an away meet. How many students are leaving early?

Viktor watches TV after he finishes his homework every night. On Tuesday and Wednesday, he watched a 3-hour episode of his favorite show each night. On Thursday, he watched a few episodes of a 30-minute show. On Friday, he finished homework early and watched a 5-hour episode and a 30-minute show. On Saturday, he got to stay up late, so he watched two 5-hour episodes. If he watched 22 hours of TV in all, how many 30-minute episodes did he watch on Thursday?
Kimia has $66.14 and wants to buy 51 screws from a bin at the home improvement store. Each screw costs $0.14. How much money does Kimia have left after paying for the screws?
Mia and Kai are currently 18 years apart in age. If Mia, who is younger than Kai, is 62 years old, what's the average of their ages?
An uncle eats 8 pizzas per day, his spouse eats 7 pizzas per day, and their grandchild eats 5 pizzas per day. How many pizzas does this family eat in one month?
A cake has 30 pieces. If Valentina can eat 3 pieces a day while Sofia can eat four times as much, how many days will the cake last?

Ms. Johnson is looking for a apartment that will not go beyond her $300000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $260000. On top of that, the buyer has to pay a brokerage fee which is 6% of the selling price, and also the transfer fee that is 11% of the selling price. How much more is the total price of the apartment than Ms. Johnson's budget?
Liam is 11 years old. In 7 years his sister Ananya will be 2 times as old as Liam is now. How old is Ananya right now?

A hospital has a capacity of 1700 wards with 1/10 occupied. Due to the flu season, 70 patients are admitted into the hospital each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied wards in the hospital after 2 weeks.

Prof. Johnson sold his apartment for $350000. He paid the registration fees that amount to 1% of the selling price and also paid a agent fee that is 5% of the selling price. If he also paid $170000 for the remaining loan amount of the apartment, how much is Prof. Johnson's net proceeds from selling the apartment?

Sakura went to the patisserie and bought various types of baked goods. She bought 2 dozen croissants which cost $14 per dozen, 5 dozen macarons which cost $85 per dozen, and 8 dozen brownies for $114 per dozen. How much was the total cost?
A loaf of sourdough at the market costs €6. Biscuits cost €4 each. How much more do 6 loaves of sourdough cost than 6 biscuits?

Benjamin is raising money for a music festival. He has applied for help from the youth club, which has decided to cover 1/2 of the cost of the music festival. How much money is Benjamin missing if he has ¥100 and the music festival costs ¥980?

Aisha and Yara are sisters from Bangkok who love collecting signatures from athletes. During their winter break from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After 7 weeks, Aisha and Yara compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. Aisha has 38 signatures in her book, and Yara has 48. The sisters have 2 more weeks of winter break, and they decide they want to reach 120 signatures between them by the end of the break. How many signatures do the sisters need to collect to reach their goal?
A stack is made out of 4 white tiles, thrice as many purple tiles, and an unknown number of orange tiles. If there are 22 tiles in the stack in total, how many orange tiles are there?

A cleaner has to clean a hospital with 120 floors. They have 10 days to get it done. It takes them 30 minutes per floor. If they work 10 hours each day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning floors?
Emma went to their greenhouse to pick some blueberries and found four-sixths as many bees as ladybugs in the plot. If there were 165 ladybugs, calculate the total number of insects in the plot.

Riverside Academy is holding graduation in their Gymnasium this year which has space for 6600 people. After accounting for 1300 seats for graduates and 100 seats for faculty attending, how many tickets would each graduate receive to give to their friends and family if the tickets are split equally?

Xena hid 9 dozen eggs in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Sophia finds 8 eggs. Tariq finds five times as many as Sophia. Keisha finds 4 less than Tariq, and Rania finds 1/4 as many as Keisha. How many eggs are still hidden in the yard?

Oliver goes to the store to buy some sugar. The normal brand of sugar he buys costs $20 per kg. He had to buy a more expensive brand that costs 15% more since his favorite brand was sold out. He decides to buy a week's worth of sugar and he uses 2 kg of sugar per day. He also decided to buy himself a bagel for $1. How much did everything cost?
There are 28 girls in the park. If there are five times the number of boys in the park, how many kids are in the park?
The area of Santiago's rectangular kitchen is 486 square meters. If the length of his room is 6 meters, what is the perimeter of the room in meters?

Jamal collects garbage from 4 different apartment complexes. The first 3 have 450 apartments each and the last one is 70% bigger than the other 3 combined. Jamal collects garbage 4 times a week from each place and he gets paid €0.25 per collection for each apartment. How much money does he make in a week?

Pavel has a herb stand at the street bazaar. He sells three kinds of herbs: roses, orchids and sunflowers. He usually sells roses for €1.26 per bouquet, orchids for €3.83 per bouquet and sunflowers for €6.4 per bouquet. Pavel has no change today, so he has decided to round all his prices to the nearest dollar. If Pavel sells 7 bouquets of roses, 26 bouquets of orchids and 38 bouquets of sunflowers, how much will he make?

Olivia went to the boardwalk for vacation. Her parents gave her ¥1400 to buy whatever she wanted. At the gift shop, saltwater taffy was on sale for "Buy 15 kilograms at ¥22 per kilogram, get 6 kilograms 1/4 off." She scooped up 23 kilograms. She also bought a mixed bag of starfish for ¥11.75 and 17 keychains that were ¥20.25 each. How much money does Olivia have left?
James has 8 ₺50 bills. He buys 3 board games for ₺4 each. He also buys 9 packs of erasers for ₺1 each. How much money does he have left?

Theo has 6 tubes of black paint and 2 tubes of indigo paint. Diego has two-thirds as many tubes of black paint as Theo, and twice as many tubes of indigo paint as Theo. How many tubes of paint does Diego have?
Roya sliced a whole kiwi into 25 pieces. She ate 3 slices, her brother ate 5 more than her, and her cousin ate 4 more than her brother. How many slices of kiwi did they all eat?
Emma can peel 10 onions a minute and saute 35 onions in 7 minutes. How long will it take her to peel and saute 140 onions?

Aisha is learning to write and decides to keep re-writing the hiragana (with 48 letters) until she knows it. She writes it in full nine times, writes 1/4 of it once, then re-writes everything she has already written. How many letters has Aisha written in total?
A cup of juice is 14 ounces of juice. Tariq drinks 5 cups of juice. If juice has 6 calories per ounce how many calories did he consume?

Tariq scored 322 points in one game of archery. Mia scored 32 points more than 1/2 as many as Tariq. How many points did Tariq and Mia have in total?

Sakura has 12 jars of sprinkles in her pantry. Each jar of sprinkles can decorate 18 cupcakes. Sakura wants to bake enough cupcakes to use up all of her sprinkles. If each pan holds 18 cupcakes, how many pans worth of cupcakes should she bake?
In a set of chef's cards, there are 36 purple cards, and 50% more orange cards. Red cards are as many as the sum of purple and orange cards. How many cards of all mentioned colors are there?
A boy has 12 books. His brother has 7 fewer books than he has. How many books do they have together?
It takes Olga 27 minutes to finish a jigsaw puzzle and 11 minutes to finish a riddle. Over the weekend she solved 3 jigsaw puzzles and 4 riddles. How much time did she spend playing these games?

Luis works a 11-hour shift each day, 4 days a week. He earns €14 per hour and gets a €540 bonus each week if the company performs well. How much money did Luis make in September if the company performed very well for the whole month?

Amelia already owns 11 flowers. Each flowering plant costs $8 at the store, how much money will Amelia spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?

On Sunday, Bodhi wants to exercise for five times the amount of time he did on Saturday and Friday combined. On Friday he exercised for 18 minutes. On Saturday he exercised for 41 minutes. How many minutes does he have to exercise on Sunday to reach his goal?

Arash's truck breaks down. The truck weighs 1350 pounds and he has equipment in it weighing 275 pounds. He also has his 2 young colleagues who weigh 75 pounds each in it. If the force to move the truck is 4% of the weight, how much force does he need to push the truck?
A electrician works for 2 weeks every month and for 6 days every week. If he gets paid €55 every day, how much does he earn if he works for a year?

Daphne is trying to decide whether to do her financial planning herself or hire one bookkeeper. If she does it herself, she'll be able to do 10 fewer hours of contract work, losing ₺29/hour in missed income. The bookkeeper charges ₺191. How much more money will she have if she hires the bookkeeper?

Mateo has a bag of buttons with 54 inside. He tripped over root while carrying it and dropped two-fourths of them. He scrambled to search for them but only came up with 13. When he went back home, he inspected the buttons further. Three of them he picked up weren't buttons, but actually beads so he got rid of it. How many buttons did Mateo end up with?

There are 103 fourth-graders at Sunny Hill School. 73 of them are girls. On Thursday, 5 fourth-grade girls and 3 fourth-grade boys were absent. How many fourth grade boys were at Sunny Hill School on Thursday?

Mateo was a pen pal with 6 people. He stopped being penpals with 4 of them. They each send 3 letters a week that are 10 pages long. He responds in kind. He can write a page every 11 minutes. How many hours does he spend writing a week?

There are currently 14 purple balls, 27 pink balls, and 41 orange balls in the shop. Purple balls cost ₣9, orange balls cost ₣3, and pink balls cost ₣8. How much will the shop have received after all the balls are sold?
