A father eats 6 sushi rolls per day, his wife eats 5 sushi rolls per day, and their daughter eats 4 sushi rolls per day. How many sushi rolls does this family eat in one week?

Rania is knitting winter wear for her 4 grandchildren. They're quadruplets, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a sweater, cardigan, beanie, mittens, and booties for each of them. It takes 15 skeins of wool to make a sweater, 16 for a cardigan, 18 for a beanie, 13 for a pair of mittens, and 9 for a pair of booties. How many skeins of wool will she need to buy?
Ava receives 100 emails a day. 17% of those emails don't require any response. Ava responds to the rest of them. How many emails does Ava respond to in a 4 day work week?

Quinn is an avid gardener. Two days ago, she received 45 new potted plants from her favorite plant nursery. She already has 10 potted plants on each of the 58 window ledges of her large country home. Feeling generous, she has decided that she will give 7 potted plants from each ledge to friends and family tomorrow. How many potted plants will Quinn remain with?
Viktor has ₣84.32 and wants to buy 34 washers from a bin at the home improvement store. Each washer costs ₣0.48. How much money does Viktor have left after paying for the washers?
Beatriz and Roya are currently 8 years apart in age. If Beatriz, who is younger than Roya, is 37 years old, what's the average of their ages?

In Mr. Smith's class of 144 students, 25% of the class are basketball players. Out of the remaining class, 25% of the students are robotics club members or part of choir members. These 3 groups of students will need to leave early today to travel to an away tournament. How many students are leaving early?

Rania and Yara are sisters from Lisbon who love collecting signatures from politicians. During their winter break from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After 5 weeks, Rania and Yara compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. Rania has 27 signatures in her book, and Yara has 52. The sisters have 2 more weeks of winter break, and they decide they want to reach 105 signatures between them by the end of the break. How many signatures do the sisters need to collect to reach their goal?

According to its nutritional info, a bag of popcorn has 150 calories per serving. If a 100 grams bag has 4 servings, how many grams can you eat if your daily calorie target is 2100 and you have already consumed 1350 calories?

Ms. Johnson is looking for a apartment that will not go beyond her $310000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $300000. On top of that, the buyer has to pay a brokerage fee which is 4% of the selling price, and also the transfer fee that is 13% of the selling price. How much more is the total price of the apartment than Ms. Johnson's budget?
Alejandro is 24 years old. In 5 years his sister Nadia will be 3 times as old as Alejandro is now. How old is Nadia right now?

Mr. Jones sold his cottage for $610000. He paid the transfer fees that amount to 3% of the selling price and also paid a brokerage fee that is 5% of the selling price. If he also paid $480000 for the remaining loan amount of the cottage, how much is Mr. Jones's net proceeds from selling the cottage?

Ibrahim is raising money for a music festival. He has applied for help from the youth club, which has decided to cover a quarter of the cost of the music festival. How much money is Ibrahim missing if he has ¥185 and the music festival costs ¥400?

A hospital has a capacity of 1900 wards with 1/4 occupied. Due to the flu season, 25 patients are admitted into the hospital each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied wards in the hospital after 4 weeks.
A cake has 48 pieces. If Winnie can eat 2 pieces a day while Luca can eat twice as much, how many days will the cake last?
A loaf of bread at the bakery costs ₺7. Bagels cost ₺1 each. How much more do 4 loaves of bread cost than 2 bagels?

A maintenance worker has to clean a university with 55 rooms. They have 5 days to get it done. It takes them 30 minutes per room. If they work 11 hours each day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning rooms?

Sakura went to their allotment to pick some raspberries and found ten times as many beetles as grasshoppers in the patch. If there were 32 grasshoppers, calculate the total number of insects in the patch.

Luis goes to the store to buy some sugar. The normal brand of sugar he buys costs €15 per kg. He had to buy a more expensive brand that costs 40% more since his favorite brand was sold out. He decides to buy a week's worth of sugar and he uses 2 kg of sugar per day. He also decided to buy himself a bagel for €3. How much did everything cost?

Mia went to the cafe and bought various types of treats. She bought 4 dozen danishes which cost $17 per dozen, 7 dozen tarts which cost $88 per dozen, and 6 dozen scones for $117 per dozen. How much was the total cost?
A pyramid is made out of 9 white cubes, two times as many black cubes, and an unknown number of pink cubes. If there are 31 cubes in the pyramid in total, how many pink cubes are there?

Oliver hid 9 dozen eggs in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Daphne finds 12 eggs. Amelia finds thrice as many as Daphne. Pavel finds 1 less than Amelia, and Alejandro finds a fifth as many as Pavel. How many eggs are still hidden in the yard?

Greenville High School is holding graduation in their Convention Center this year which has space for 7900 people. After accounting for 1250 seats for graduates and 400 seats for faculty attending, how many tickets would each graduate receive to give to their friends and family if the tickets are split equally?
The area of Bodhi's rectangular office is 930 square feet. If the length of his room is 10 yards, what is the perimeter of the room in feet?
Valeria can peel 7 carrots a minute and saute 35 carrots in 6 minutes. How long will it take her to peel and saute 70 carrots?
Haruka sliced a whole peach into 31 pieces. She ate 3 slices, her cousin ate 5 more than her, and her brother ate 11 more than her cousin. How many slices of peach did they all eat?

Kai has a plant stand at the town square. He sells three kinds of plants: roses, lilies and orchids. He usually sells roses for €1.26 per bundle, lilies for €4.35 per bundle and orchids for €5.78 per bundle. Kai has no change today, so he has decided to round all his prices to the nearest dollar. If Kai sells 15 bundles of roses, 30 bundles of lilies and 39 bundles of orchids, how much will he make?
There are 8 girls in the yard. If there are three-fourths the number of boys in the yard, how many kids are in the yard?

Umar collects garbage from 7 different apartment complexes. The first 6 have 250 apartments each and the last one is 75% bigger than the other 6 combined. Umar collects garbage 4 times a week from each place and he gets paid ¥0.25 per collection for each apartment. How much money does he make in a week?
Gabriel scored 446 points in one game of bowling. Roya scored 17 points more than one-half as many as Gabriel. How many points did Gabriel and Roya have in total?
Diego has 3 €50 bills. He buys 3 action figures for €3 each. He also buys 8 packs of candy bars for €2 each. How much money does he have left?
A bottle of lemonade is 11 ozs of lemonade. Faisal drinks 2 bottles of lemonade. If lemonade has 4 calories per oz how many calories did he consume?

Liam has 7 tubes of orange paint and 6 tubes of pink paint. Ravi has 1/7 as many tubes of orange paint as Liam, and ten times as many tubes of pink paint as Liam. How many tubes of paint does Ravi have?

Sakura went to the boardwalk for vacation. Her parents gave her ¥1300 to buy whatever she wanted. At the gift shop, saltwater taffy was on sale for "Buy 15 kgs at ¥21 per kg, get 5 kgs 1/4 off." She scooped up 22 kgs. She also bought a mixed bag of starfish for ¥11.5 and 15 keychains that were ¥21.25 each. How much money does Sakura have left?
In a set of athlete's cards, there are 50 red cards, and 68% more yellow cards. Blue cards are as many as the sum of red and yellow cards. How many cards of all mentioned colors are there?
A child has 12 pencils. His friend has 2 fewer pencils than he has. How many pencils do they have together?

Fatima has 10 jars of chocolate chips in her storage room. Each jar of chocolate chips can decorate 16 muffins. Fatima wants to bake enough muffins to use up all of her chocolate chips. If each rack holds 8 muffins, how many racks worth of muffins should she bake?

Daphne has a flower bed that is 175 meters long. Daphne wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Daphne's flowers grow 2 meters wide so she needs to leave 12.5 meters between every plant. Daphne already owns 13 flowers. Each flowering plant costs ₺5 at the store, how much money will Daphne spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?

I have 19 liters of peach drink that are three-sixths water and I wish to add it to 16 liters of apple drink that is 3/4 water. But as I pour it, I spill 5 liters of the peach drink. How much water is in the remaining 30 liters?

Xena is trying to decide whether to do her taxes herself or hire one bookkeeper. If she does it herself, she'll be able to do 8 fewer hours of contract work, losing ₣48/hour in missed income. The bookkeeper charges ₣101. How much more money will she have if she hires the bookkeeper?

Sakura is learning to write and decides to keep re-writing the hiragana (with 48 letters) until she knows it. She writes it in full four times, writes three-sixths of it once, then re-writes everything she has already written. How many letters has Sakura written in total?

James's truck breaks down. The truck weighs 2150 pounds and he has equipment in it weighing 450 pounds. He also has his 2 young colleagues who weigh 50 pounds each in it. If the force to move the truck is 3% of the weight, how much force does he need to push the truck?

It takes Uma 16 minutes to finish a chess puzzle and 5 minutes to finish a jigsaw puzzle. Over the free time she solved 7 chess puzzles and 7 jigsaw puzzles. How much time did she spend playing these games?

On Monday, DeShawn wants to exercise for four times the amount of time he did on Sunday and Saturday combined. On Saturday he exercised for 53 minutes. On Sunday he exercised for 32 minutes. How many minutes does he have to exercise on Monday to reach his goal?

Hiroshi has a bag of beads with 48 inside. He tripped over root while carrying it and dropped 1/3 of them. He scrambled to search for them but only came up with 13. When he went back home, he inspected the beads further. Three of them he picked up weren't beads, but actually beads so he got rid of it. How many beads did Hiroshi end up with?

Jamal works a 11-hour shift each day, 3 days a week. He earns $21 per hour and gets a $119 bonus each week if the company performs well. How much money did Jamal make in December if the company performed very well for the whole month?

One miner can mine 5 pounds of ore per day with basic shovel. He can mine twice as much with a bronze pickaxe and 40% more with a steel pickaxe than with a bronze pickaxe. How many pounds of ore can 23 miners with steel pickaxes mine in a month with 29 days?
Yusuf has 94 light gray spools of thread, 89 dark gray spools of thread, 28 light red spools of thread, and 94 dark red spools of thread. What percent of the spools are gray?

Comet Encke orbits the sun every 55 years. Faisal's grandfather saw the Comet when he was 40 years old. Faisal saw the comet a second time when he was two times the age his grandfather was when he saw the Comet. How old was Faisal when he saw the Comet for the first time?

There are currently 17 yellow balls, 9 pink balls, and 17 orange balls in the warehouse. Yellow balls cost $5, orange balls cost $3, and pink balls cost $5. How much will the warehouse have received after all the balls are sold?
Valentina finished one-fourth of a 160 piece puzzle, and then started and finished another 388 piece puzzle within an hour. How many puzzle pieces did Valentina place during that hour?

Santiago was a pen pal with 10 people. He stopped being penpals with 2 of them. They each send 3 letters a week that are 5 pages long. He responds in kind. He can write a page every 10 minutes. How many hours does he spend writing a week?
A plumber works for 2 weeks every month and for 4 days every week. If he gets paid $100 every day, how much does he earn if he works for a year?

Qasim is feeding his livestock grain. Each alpaca needs 14 kg, and each cow needs 5 kg less than twice the amount each alpaca needs. If there are 13 alpacas and 36 cows, how many kg of grain does Qasim need?

There are 101 third-graders at Sunny Hill School. 69 of them are girls. On Wednesday, 9 third-grade girls and 2 third-grade boys were absent. How many third grade boys were at Sunny Hill School on Wednesday?

There are 9 periods in the day for a normal student but Luis has to take 3 extra classes. Each class is 35 minutes long. He goes to class for 5 days a week. He then spends three-sixths of his weekly minutes each on Saturday and Sunday as extra learning time. How many hours a week does he spend learning?

The Smith family is busy making brownies. So far, they've made 5650 brownies. They have 1555 blueberry brownies, 1649 strawberry brownies, and some lemon brownies. How many lemon brownies have they made?
The Halloween candy hunt team hid 160 eggs. The Johnson twins each found 45 eggs. All the other eggs except 8 were found by their friends. How many eggs did the friends find?

Umar caught 7 salmons last Tuesday, the first salmon he caught weighs 45 kgs, the second salmon he caught weighs 33 kgs, and the last salmon he caught weighs 36 kgs. If a kg of salmon costs ₣1.5, how much will he earn after selling all the salmons to the market?
Quinn is required to submit a 105-page report. She already finished writing 3/5 of the report. How many pages does she have left to write?

Yara qualified for a spot on the cycling team, so she went shopping for some athletic gear. She bought a jersey for €23, a pair of cycling leggings for €4 more than the jersey cost, and a pair of cleats that were originally €32 but were on sale for one-half price. She had a coupon for €4 off the package of €13 athletic headbands that she also bought. How much did she spend on athletic gear?

The biggest waterslide at Splash World is 350 yards long, and people slide down at 50 yards/minute. The second biggest waterslide is 210 yards long, but steeper, so people slide down at 70 yards/minute. How much longer does it take to ride the biggest slide compared to the second biggest slide?

Alejandro has two times as many LinkedIn friends as Mohammed. Jin has eight times as many friends on LinkedIn as Mohammed. If Alejandro has 128 friends on LinkedIn, how many LinkedIn friends does Jin have?
Kimia buys 10 shares of a stock for ¥90 each. The stock price increases 40% the first year Kimia holds it, then decreases 15% in the second year. What is the final value of all Kimia's shares?
If Sanjay and Tariq have 720 feet of fence between them, and they agree to split it with Tariq getting 100 feet more than Sanjay, how much is left over for Sanjay?

250 people apply for a job at Amazon. Of the people that apply, only 26% receive interviews. Of those who receive interviews, 40% receive a job offer. Of those who receive a job offer, two-fourths of the people accept the position. How many people accept the position?

When the water is cold Andre swims a kilometer in 27 minutes. When the water is warm Andre swims a kilometer in 3 minutes more than twice as long. How much longer does Andre take to swim 7 kilometers on a hot day than a cold day?
Arjun hires a luxury car from 4 PM to 10 PM. He gets 2 hours free. The first paid hour is ₣26 and each hour after that is thrice the cost. How much did he pay?

There are 9 students playing table tennis and nine times that number playing football. There are 20 boys and 12 girls playing volleyball. If each student only participates in one group, how many students are there in total?

Sakura can run five times faster than she can walk, but she can skip at a rate of speed that is one-sixth as fast as she can run. If she can skip at 2 miles per hour, how many miles can she travel in 10 hours if she spends 1/2 of the time running and three-sixths of the time walking?
If Priya eats 3 eggs a day for 106 days and then increases it to 6 eggs a day for 67 days, how many dozens of eggs will Priya need for 173 days?
The vending machines sell gum for 50 cents and pretzels for 75 cents. Yuki spent ₣600 and got 9 bags of gum and had 3% of his money left in change. How many pretzels did he buy?

At Liam's house, there are ten times as many pears as apples. He has a total of 31 apples in his house. Liam bought 58 more apples at the store and 44 fewer pears than the number of apples. Find the combined total of the number of pears and apples Liam has in the house?

Roya operates the cash register exactly ten times as fast as her less-experienced colleague Valeria. Daily, Valeria processes 47 customers. What is the total weekly production for the two if they work all days of the week?

Fatima's dad said that she had €210 budgeted for her birthday party. She wants to make sure she and her friends all get to play one round of bowling, have €7 in game room tokens, and get to ride the bumper cars two times. A round of bowling is €9. The bumper cars cost €7 a ride. How many friends can she invite?
A new virus infects 19 people. Every day, each infected person infects 5 others. How many people are infected after 3 days?
At the beginning of the party, there were 70 teachers and 54 engineers. After 45 minutes, 1/4 of the total number of people left. How many engineers are left if 27 teachers stayed at the party?

Arjun slew 500 orcs with his mighty war hammer, while Mateo, using a halberd, slew one-fourth as many orcs as Arjun. Using a bone dagger, Arash slew seven times as many orcs as Mateo. But Ibrahim, having forgotten his hammer at home, slew 4/5 as many orcs as Arash using a feather. How many orcs has Ibrahim slain?

A class of 150 students has various hobbies. 20 like to paint, 8 like to play chess, 13 like to swim, 17 like to play football, and the rest like to either dance or read. What percentage of the students like to dance if the number of the students that like to read is 2 less than two times the number that prefer playing football?

Oliver is popping popcorn for a snack. As the skillet of kernels heats up, the kernels start popping faster. 60 pop in the first 22 seconds of cooking, then 3 times that amount in the next 22 seconds. The kernels increase to 4 times the initial popping rate in the next 22 seconds. In the final 22 seconds, the popping slows down to half the rate as the past 22 seconds. After Oliver takes the skillet off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 22 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. Oliver gives one-tenth of the made popcorn to his brother Thiago. How many more pieces of popcorn does Oliver have to eat than his brother?

Mohammed is rolling a 20-sided die. How much more likely is it (expressed as a difference in percentage points) that he rolls a number greater than 10 twice in a row, than that he rolls four even numbers in a row?

Mohammed has 35 square meters of grape field. There are 12 grapes per 2/3 of a square meter. Mohammed can harvest his grapes every 6 months. In addition, Mohammed owns a 11-square meter apricot field that produces 18 apricots per square meter. The apricots can be harvested every 4 months. In the span of two years, how many more grapes does Mohammed harvest than apricots?

When Nia watches her cousin, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 36 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 8 stuffed animals inside. The number of action figures in the action figure pack is twice the number of blocks and stuffed animals combined. The crayon box has 12 different colors of crayon, and the sticker book has 9 pages, each with 11 stickers. The tower of stacking rings has 26 multicolored rings on it. Nia recently bought a tube of bouncy balls, bringing her total number of items for her cousin up to 310. How many bouncy balls came in the tube?

Gabrielle makes tea using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in a ratio of 54:12. She also uses 7 tablespoons of milk for every 2 cups of water, and uses 2 tablespoons of heavy cream for every teaspoon of sugar. She used a total of 240 teaspoons of sugar, cups of water, tablespoons of cream, and tablespoons of milk. How many teaspoons of sugar did she use?

A farmer is buying feed for his cows. He buys a variety of wheat, oats, carrots and corn. Since corn are a rare treat, he only buys seven 5-kg boxes of them for the whole stable. He only wants enough carrots to feed the cows while the vegetables are fresh, so he buys eleven 7-kg bags. Wheat are the main diet of his cows, so he buys thirty four 39-kg packs. Oats are a staple to supplement the wheat, so he buys nineteen 18-kg sacks. Finally, he buys 43 kgs of groceries, and 27 kgs of tools, and 100 kgs of wood. A farm truck can carry 130 kgs at a time. If the farmer has three trucks, how many trips does the farmer need to transport all the purchased items?

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 60 minutes to cover every 3 miles of the city. However, we know that the wind speed is going to be halved in one hour. If the city is 54 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover 1/3 of the city?

A juggler can juggle 360 balls. A tenth of the balls are golf balls, and the rest are tennis balls. 1/3 of the golf balls are white, of which 1/4 are marked. Half of the tennis balls are magenta, and all except 1/2 of those magenta balls are marked. How many marked balls are there in total?

Nadia and Sanjay have 261 minutes to walk to the grocery store together starting from their home. It takes them 24 minutes to get to the corner where the gym is. It takes them another 27 minutes to get to the mall. When they reach the mall, they remember they forgot their wallets at home, so they have to return to pick up their wallets and then walk all the way back to the mall again. Once they reach the mall for the second time, how much longer do they have to get to the grocery store without being late?

To make a call from a hotel room phone, you must pay €0.4 for each minute of your call. After 15 minutes, the price drops to €0.3 per minute. After 35 minutes from the start of the call, the price drops even more to €0.2 per two minutes. If your total bill is more than €15, you get a 10% discount on your total bill. How much would a 115-minute call cost?

Noah wants to make different sized ice cubes with 336 ounces of water. He can make giant cubes that use 15 ounces per cube, medium cubes that use 4 ounces, small cubes that use 1/2 of a ounce, and tiny cubes that are half the size of small cubes. He makes 49 total ice cubes, including 8 giant cubes, 14 small cubes, 15 medium cubes, and some tiny cubes. How many ounces of water does Noah have left?

Jasmine saw a 32-foot dolphin with 24 remoras, each 12 inches long attached to it. Then, 1/3 of the remoras swam away. Later, Jasmine saw another 8-foot dolphin with 4 remoras, each 6 inches long, attached to it. On average, what percentage of each dolphin's body length is covered by the remoras?

Sanjay places almonds on bowls and plates. Each bowl can hold 30 almonds while each plate can hold three times that. Sanjay has 675 almonds, 12 bowls and 3 plates. Unfortunately, 2 plates break. Sanjay then eats one-ninth of all the almonds. How many more bowls does Sanjay need so he can place all the remaining almonds?

Amelia is an avid gardener. Last week, she received 25 new potted plants from her favorite plant nursery. She already has 12 potted plants on each of the 54 window ledges of her large country home. She also purchased 110 new plants yesterday at a 50% discount. Feeling generous, she has decided that she will give 4 potted plants from each ledge to friends and family tomorrow. How many potted plants will Amelia remain with?

Deshawn went to buy some school supplies. He bought 14 erasers which cost ₺7.5 each, 4 rulers which cost ₺18.5 each, and a ream of bond paper which cost ₺21. He also bought 8 folders which cost ₺10 each. Deshawn can either pay a one-time ₺20 fee to become a member and get a 20% discount on all purchases, or not become a member and receive only a 5% discount. What is the least amount DeShawn can spend on everything?

Leon picks 80 apples on Thursday. Then he picks 50 apples on Friday. On Saturday, he picks triple the number of apples he did on Thursday. On Sunday, he picks half the amount of what he picked in the past 3 days combined. On Monday, Leon is going to sell apples in boxes of 15 apples each. He is going to sell each box for $12. How much is Leon going to make?

In a 80-item quiz, 55% of the questions are physics, 20% are geometry, and the rest are equally divided as literature and geography questions. If Rania is sure to get 25% of the geometry questions, 100% of the physics questions, and 1/2 of the literature and geography questions correctly, how many points is she sure to get?

Umar is selling muffins and apricot pies for a fundraiser. On Thursday, he sold 28 boxes of muffin and 13 fewer boxes of apricot pie, than on Friday. On Friday, he sold 13 more boxes of muffins than on Thursday and 21 boxes of apricot pie. On Saturday, he sold as much as he did in the past two days combined. If the muffin cost $11 and the apricot pie cost $30, what was Umar's average daily earning?

Leon's dog has 99 puppies, 23 of which have spots. James's dog has 53 puppies, 12 of which have spots. Hiroshi has 58 dogs, each having 11 puppies with spots. After a visit to the vet, Leon discovered that half of his unspotted puppies actually have spots that were not visible before. What percentage of all the puppies have spots?

Thiago watches TV after he finishes his homework every night. On Tuesday and Wednesday, he watched 5-hour episodes of his favorite show each night. On Thursday, he watched a few episodes of a 30-minute show. On Friday, he finished homework early and watched a 5-hour episode and a 30-minute show. On Saturday, he got to stay up late, so he watched three 4-hour episodes. On Sunday, he watched two episodes, each 15 minutes. If he watched 31 hours of TV in all, how many 30-minute episodes did he watch on Thursday?

Xena was preparing for a birthday party at her house, where she intended to serve creme brulee. She noticed that she was out of plastic forks, so she bought a new package of forks. Later, her husband also bought a package of 16 new forks and gave them to Xena. While Xena was making the creme brulee, she used seven of the forks to sample her creme brulee, then threw away 8 defective forks. The guests also brought 2 packs of forks, each having 8 inside them. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 39 forks. How many forks were in the package that Xena bought?

Fatima walks 26 miles every day on her favorite walking trail, which includes 11 miles of walking on the beach and 15 miles of walking on the sidewalk. On the sidewalk, Fatima walks at three times the rate of speed that she does on the beach. However, due to a recent injury, Fatima's speed has decreased by half both on the beach and sidewalk. If 44 minutes of her walk is spent on the beach, how long does it take for her to complete the entire 26-mile walk, in minutes?

Kai is 22 years old. In 5 years, his cousin Uma will be 4 times as old as Kai is now. Kai's brother, Jamal, is 6 years younger than Kai, and Uma sister Rania is 11 years older than Jamal. What will be the average of all four in 4 years?

Oliver receives 32 emails a day. 25% of those emails don't require any response. From the rest, Oliver can only respond to 2 less than the 1/2 of them. How many emails does Oliver respond to in a 4 day work week? Oliver work overtime on the last day so he can respond to 10% more emails than usual.

Kimia and Yusuf went to a construction supply store. Yusuf is a member, but Kimia is not. Kimia has ¥91.25 and wants to buy 16 nails from a bin at the store. She also needs 9 washers, each costing ¥0.65. Each nail costs ¥0.4. Additionally, Kimia picks up 8 gallons of paint. Yusuf starts with ¥80 and wants 10 gallons of paint, each priced at ¥7.0, and 4 carpenter pencils, each costing ¥2. The store offers a 10% discount on paint for members. How much more money does Kimia have left than Yusuf after they leave the store?

Valeria is knitting winter wear for her 4 grandchildren. They're quadruplets, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a tunic, hat, shawl, booties, and gloves for each of them. It takes 6 skeins of wool to make a tunic, 6 for a hat, 12 for a shawl, 12 for a pair of booties, and 13 for a pair of gloves. Valeria wants to make two warm jackets for herself, each needing 4 skeins of wool. Each dozen skeins of wool costs $9. The store has a promotion where customers receive a $20 discount on purchases over $100. How much should Valeria pay for all the skeins of wool she needs?

According to its nutritional info, a bag of breads has 250 calories per serving. A 350 ounces bag has 5 servings. The healthy daily calorie target is 15 calories per pound of body weight. Yuki weighs 210 lbs, and he has already consumed 1050 calories and burned 150 calories through exercise. Jasmine weighs 140 lbs, and she has already consumed 900 in food and 200 calories in ice cream. How many more ounces of breads does Yuki need to consume than Jasmine?

Benjamin, Luca are currently 29 years apart in age. Benjamin and Sofia are currently 17 years apart. Benjamin, who is younger than Luca but older than Sofia, will be 27 in 4 years. How much younger is Sofia than the average age of all three?

In Mrs. Garcia's class of 160 students, 50% of the class are swimmers. Out of the remaining class, 35% of the students are debate team members or part of dancers. These 3 groups of students will need to leave early today to travel to an away tournament. Half of the swimmers are absent for being sick. Also, 3 cheerleaders will accompany each of these groups. How many students are leaving early to the tournament?

A clinic has a capacity of 1600 rooms with 1/10 occupied and two-fifths of all the rooms being out of service. Due to the natural disaster, 30 patients are admitted into the clinic each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied rooms in the clinic after 3 weeks.

A father eats 5 burritos per day, his wife eats 25 burritos per day, and their daughter eats one-third of the combined number of burritos they eat per day. After one month, the family decides to go on a diet in the second month, reducing their food consumption by 60% for the first half of the month, and then by an additional 50% for the second half. How many burritos does this family eat in two months?

Prof. Miller sold his apartment for $810000. He paid the registration fees that amounted to 3% of the selling price and also paid a agent fee that is 3% of the selling price. He also paid $670000 for the remaining loan amount on the apartment, and $20000 for closing costs. Prof. Miller used the net proceeds from selling the apartment to invest in stocks. The stocks gained 10% each year for two years. How much were Prof. Miller's net proceeds after two years?

Ava and Quinn are sisters from Helsinki who love collecting signatures from authors. During their spring break from school, the sisters spend every afternoon collecting signatures. After 3 weeks, Ava and Quinn compare their autograph books, counting up the number of signatures each sister has collected. Ava has 30 signatures in her book, and Quinn has 37. The sisters have 2 more weeks of spring break, and they decide they want to reach 135 signatures between them by the end of the break. However, during the remaining 2 weeks, Ava is only able to collect signatures on weekends, reducing her weekly collection by 5 per week, while Quinn decides to increase her weekly collection. How many signatures will Quinn need to collect per week to make sure they reach their goal?

A loaf of sourdough at the cafe costs ¥15. The cost of a muffin is 1/4 of a loaf of sourdough. The cafe has a promotion that if one buys 6 muffins or more, they get a 20% discount on muffins. How much more do 5 loaves of sourdough cost than 8 muffins?

A giant pie has 122 pieces. Ananya can eat 2 pieces a day while Kimia can eat thrice as much and Fatima can eat five times as much as Kimia. After 2 days, Fatima decides to go on a diet and cut the consumption by half. How many days will it take for the pie to be fully eaten?

Ms. Johnson is looking for a new apartment that will not go beyond her $430000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $400000. On top of that, the buyer has to pay a brokerage fee which is 7% of the selling price, and also the transfer fee that is 14% of the selling price. If Ms. Johnson can get 5% discount on the selling price, how much more will be the total cost than Ms. Johnson's budget?

Ava went to the confectionery and bought various types of desserts. She bought 36 eclairs at $13 per dozen, 60 cookies at $26 per dozen, and 24 muffins. After a 20% discount, she paid a total of $980. What was the cost of muffins per dozen?
A stack is made out of 8 pink tiles, two times as many green tiles, and an unknown number of orange tiles. If there are 48 tiles in the stack in total, what percentage of tiles are orange?

A janitor has to clean a building with 135 floors. They have 3 days to get it done. It takes them 5 minutes per floor. However, due to a recent injury, the janitor has become slower and it will take them twice as long to clean a floor these days. If they work for 15 hours a day, what percentage of their day, on average, is spent cleaning floors?
There are 22 girls in the garden. If there are three times the number of boys in the garden, what percentage of the kids in the garden are girls?

Arjun goes to the store to buy some tea. The normal brand of tea he buys costs ¥10 per kilogram. He has to buy a more expensive brand that costs 40% more since his favorite brand was sold out. He decides to buy a week's worth of tea and he uses 2 kilograms of tea per day. The store has a 10% discount on tea which applies only up to 10 kilograms; any additional tea is sold at the regular price. Arjun also decides to buy himself a muffin for ¥4. How much does Arjun have to pay?

Jasmine went to her backyard to pick some cherries and found one-half as many wasps as ants in the field. Jasmine then found 46 white animals, half of which were rabbits. In addition, she saw 39 bees, and 10 ants. What percentage of animals in the field were rabbits?

Chen went to the boardwalk for vacation. Her parents gave her $1300 to buy whatever she wanted. At the gift shop, saltwater taffy was on sale for "Buy 16 kgs at $22 per kg, get 6 kgs 1/4 off." She scooped up 23 kgs. She also bought a mixed bag of starfish for $11.0 and 11 keychains that were $21.0 each. Chen then donated $5 at a charity stand along the way. How much money does Chen have left?

Riverside Academy is holding graduation in its Gymnasium this year which has space for 7800 people. After accounting for the 1050 seats for graduate, 350 seats for the faculty attending, and reserving 100 seats for the event's staff, how many tickets would each graduate receive to give to their friends and family if the tickets are split equally?

Chen can peel 5 clams a minute and saute 20 clams in 16 minutes. How many minutes will it take her to peel and saute 120 clams if it takes 15 seconds to wash each clam before peeling it? Note that Chen can't work in parallel and needs to take a 6-minute break after peeling the clams before she can start sautéing them.

Benjamin is raising money for a 3-day science fair. Each day costs ₺250 for hotel, ₺30 for food, and ₺20 for transportation. Benjamin only has ₺165. His friends have chipped in and will cover the cost of all the food for the science fair. Benjamin has also applied for help from the parent association, which has decided to cover a tenth of the remaining cost of the science fair. How much money is Benjamin still missing?

Tariq collects garbage from 4 different apartment complexes. The first 3 have 100 apartments each and the last one is 30% bigger than the other 3 combined. However, this week, 10 apartments from each of the first 3 complexes were vacant and did not require collection service. Tariq collects garbage 3 times a week from each place and he gets paid ₺0.5 per collection for each apartment. He also earns an additional 10% in tips. How much money does he make in a week?

Beatriz initially had 10 dozen pancakes, then ate 3 pancakes for breakfast, and then hid the rest in the yard for the Easter egg hunt. Kimia finds 6 pancakes. Sophia finds three times as many as Kimia. Mateo finds 2 less than Sophia. Umar finds half as many as Mateo, and Mei finds two dozen pancakes more than Sophia and Kimia combined. How many pancakes are still hidden in the yard?

Mei has a flower bed that is 120 meters long. Mei wants to fill her flower bed with plants. Mei's flowers grow 4meters wide so she needs to leave 12 meters between every plant (including the plants width). Mei already owns 6 flowers. Each flowering plant costs $5 at the store. However, if she buys more than 2 plants, she'll receive a $5 discount on the entire purchase. How much money will Mei spend at the store to fill up her flower bed?

A group of 150 students has various hobbies. 27 like to play music, 8 like to play chess, 13 like to swim, 9 like to play football, and the rest like to either paint or play video games. What percentage of the students like to paint if the number of the students that like to play video games is 3 less than two times the number that prefer playing football?

Viktor is rolling a 20-sided die. How much more likely is it (expressed as a difference in percentage points) that he rolls a number greater than 2 twice in a row, than that he rolls four even numbers in a row?

Thiago is popping popcorn for a snack. As the skillet of kernels heats up, the kernels start popping faster. 40 pop in the first 26 seconds of cooking, then 3 times that amount in the next 26 seconds. The kernels increase to 4 times the initial popping rate in the next 26 seconds. In the final 26 seconds, the popping slows down to half the rate as the past 26 seconds. After Thiago takes the skillet off the heat, a quarter of the number of kernels that popped in the final 26 seconds of cooking also pop from the residual heat. Thiago gives 1/10 of the made popcorn to his brother Sanjay. How many more pieces of popcorn does Thiago have to eat than his brother?

Mia makes coffee using teaspoons of sugar and cups of water in a ratio of 48:7. She also uses 9 tablespoons of milk for every 7 cups of water, and uses 2 tablespoons of heavy cream for every teaspoon of sugar. She used a total of 170 teaspoons of sugar, cups of water, tablespoons of cream, and tablespoons of milk. How many teaspoons of sugar did she use?

Luis saw a 48-foot dolphin with 24 remoras, each 18 inches long attached to it. Then, a third of the remoras swam away. Later, Luis saw another 10-foot dolphin with 6 remoras, each 8 inches long, attached to it. On average, what percentage of each dolphin's body length is covered by the remoras?

A farmer is buying feed for his cows. He buys a variety of hay, wheat, carrots and apples. Since apples are a rare treat, he only buys five 7-pound boxes of them for the whole stable. He only wants enough carrots to feed the cows while the vegetables are fresh, so he buys fourteen 5-pound bags. Hay are the main diet of his cows, so he buys thirty five 44-pound packs. Wheat are a staple to supplement the hay, so he buys nineteen 15-pound sacks. Finally, he buys 43 pounds of groceries, and 27 pounds of tools, and 100 pounds of wood. A farm truck can carry 100 pounds at a time. If the farmer has three trucks, how many trips does the farmer need to transport all the purchased items?

When Kayla watches her brother, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 32 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 5 stuffed animals inside. The number of action figures in the action figure pack is twice the number of blocks and stuffed animals combined. The crayon box has 12 different colors of crayon, and the sticker book has 6 pages, each with 11 stickers. The tower of stacking rings has 32 multicolored rings on it. Kayla recently bought a tube of bouncy balls, bringing her total number of items for her brother up to 270. How many bouncy balls came in the tube?

A juggler can juggle 240 balls. 1/4 of the balls are tennis balls, and the rest are golf balls. 1/3 of the tennis balls are black, of which 1/5 are marked. A third of the golf balls are cyan, and all except half of those cyan balls are marked. How many marked balls are there in total?

Yusuf has 10 square yards of watermelon field. There are 19 watermelons per two-sixths of a square yard. Yusuf can harvest his watermelons every 2 months. In addition, Yusuf owns a 9-square yard grape field that produces 14 grapes per square yard. The grapes can be harvested every 4 months. In the span of two years, how many more watermelons does Yusuf harvest than grapes?

To make a call from a phone booth, you must pay ₺0.8 for each minute of your call. After 10 minutes, the price drops to ₺0.7 per minute. After 30 minutes from the start of the call, the price drops even more to ₺0.4 per two minutes. If your total bill is more than ₺15, you get a 15% discount on your total bill. How much would a 120-minute call cost?

Elena is an avid gardener. Two days ago, she received 38 new potted plants from her favorite plant nursery. She already has 12 potted plants on each of the 55 window ledges of her large country home. She also purchased 70 new plants yesterday at a 50% discount. Feeling generous, she has decided that she will give 3 potted plants from each ledge to friends and family tomorrow. How many potted plants will Elena remain with?

A fog bank rolls in from the ocean to cover a city. It takes 60 minutes to cover every 6 miles of the city. However, we know that the wind speed is going to be halved in one hour. If the city is 72 miles across from the oceanfront to the opposite inland edge, how many minutes will it take for the fog bank to cover 1/3 of the city?

Viktor wants to make different sized ice cubes with 313 ounces of water. He can make giant cubes that use 12 ounces per cube, medium cubes that use 4 ounces, small cubes that use 1/2 of a ounce, and tiny cubes that are half the size of small cubes. He makes 50 total ice cubes, including 12 giant cubes, 14 small cubes, 12 medium cubes, and some tiny cubes. How many ounces of water does Viktor have left?

Thiago and Ali have 163 minutes to walk to the gym together starting from their home. It takes them 21 minutes to get to the corner where the bank is. It takes them another 28 minutes to get to the cinema. When they reach the cinema, they remember they forgot their wallets at home, so they have to return to pick up their wallets and then walk all the way back to the cinema again. Once they reach the cinema for the second time, how much longer do they have to get to the gym without being late?

Pavel's dog has 100 puppies, 22 of which have spots. Hiroshi's dog has 40 puppies, 15 of which have spots. Santiago has 55 dogs, each having 12 puppies with spots. After a visit to the vet, Pavel discovered that half of his unspotted puppies actually have spots that were not visible before. What percentage of all the puppies have spots?

In a 40-item quiz, 50% of the questions are chemistry, 10% are history, and the rest are equally divided as geography and biology questions. If Olga is sure to get 25% of the history questions, 85% of the chemistry questions, and 1/8 of the geography and biology questions correctly, how many points is she sure to get?

Carlos places crackers on bowls and tables. Each bowl can hold 20 crackers while each table can hold three times that. Carlos has 525 crackers, 13 bowls and 4 tables. Unfortunately, 2 tables break. Carlos then eats one-fifth of all the crackers. How many more bowls does Carlos need so he can place all the remaining crackers?

Andre went to buy some school supplies. He bought 20 markers which cost ₣8.0 each, 10 pencils which cost ₣18.0 each, and a ream of bond paper which cost ₣15. He also bought 5 rulers which cost ₣9 each. Andre can either pay a one-time ₣20 fee to become a member and get a 20% discount on all purchases, or not become a member and receive only a 5% discount. What is the least amount Andre can spend on everything?

Luis picks 55 grapes on Friday. Then he picks 170 grapes on Saturday. On Sunday, he picks quintuple the number of grapes he did on Friday. On Monday, he picks half the amount of what he picked in the past 3 days combined. On Tuesday, Luis is going to sell grapes in boxes of 15 grapes each. He is going to sell each box for $10. How much is Luis going to make?

Rania walks 28 kilometers every day on her favorite walking trail, which includes 14 kilometers of walking on the beach and 14 kilometers of walking on the sidewalk. On the sidewalk, Rania walks at two times the rate of speed that she does on the beach. However, due to a recent injury, Rania's speed has decreased by half both on the beach and sidewalk. If 42 minutes of her walk is spent on the beach, how long does it take for her to complete the entire 28-kilometer walk, in minutes?

Tariq is selling brownies and apricot pies for a fundraiser. On Thursday, he sold 25 boxes of brownie and 12 fewer boxes of apricot pie, than on Friday. On Friday, he sold 14 more boxes of brownies than on Thursday and 24 boxes of apricot pie. On Saturday, he sold as much as he did in the past two days combined. If the brownie cost ₣9 and the apricot pie cost ₣20, what was Tariq's average daily earning?

Arash watches TV after he finishes his homework every night. On Sunday and Monday, he watched 4-hour episodes of his favorite show each night. On Tuesday, he watched a few episodes of a 45-minute show. On Wednesday, he finished homework early and watched a 2-hour episode and a 15-minute show. On Thursday, he got to stay up late, so he watched five 2-hour episodes. On Friday, he watched four episodes, each 30 minutes. If he watched 26 hours of TV in all, how many 45-minute episodes did he watch on Tuesday?

Valentina is knitting winter wear for her 5 grandchildren. They're quintuplets, so they're all the same size. She wants to make a shawl, tunic, cardigan, booties, and gloves for each of them. It takes 5 skeins of wool to make a shawl, 3 for a tunic, 9 for a cardigan, 10 for a pair of booties, and 11 for a pair of gloves. Valentina wants to make two warm jackets for herself, each needing 7 skeins of wool. Each dozen skeins of wool costs $7. The store has a promotion where customers receive a $20 discount on purchases over $100. How much should Valentina pay for all the skeins of wool she needs?

According to its nutritional info, a bag of cookies has 175 calories per serving. A 125 oz bag has 5 servings. The healthy daily calorie target is 15 calories per pound of body weight. Theo weighs 250 lbs, and he has already consumed 1100 calories and burned 150 calories through exercise. Sakura weighs 130 lbs, and she has already consumed 900 in food and 175 calories in ice cream. How many more oz of cookies does Theo need to consume than Sakura?

Carlos is 14 years old. In 8 years, his cousin Yara will be 4 times as old as Carlos is now. Carlos's brother, Jin, is 11 years younger than Carlos, and Yara sister Mia is 8 years older than Jin. What will be the average of all four in 6 years?

Luis receives 30 emails a day. 20% of those emails don't require any response. From the rest, Luis can only respond to 4 less than the 1/2 of them. How many emails does Luis respond to in a 5 day work week? Luis work overtime on the last day so he can respond to 25% more emails than usual.

Sakura, Arash are currently 29 years apart in age. Sakura and Tara are currently 11 years apart. Sakura, who is younger than Arash but older than Tara, will be 66 in 5 years. How much younger is Tara than the average age of all three?

In Ms. Johnson's class of 20 students, 20% of the class are soccer players. Out of the remaining class, 50% of the students are debate team members or part of choir members. These 3 groups of students will need to leave early today to travel to an away competition. Half of the soccer players are absent for being sick. Also, 3 cheerleaders will accompany each of these groups. How many students are leaving early to the competition?

Chen was preparing for a birthday party at her house, where she intended to serve beef stew. She noticed that she was out of plastic forks, so she bought a new package of forks. Later, her husband also bought a package of 9 new forks and gave them to Chen. While Chen was making the beef stew, she used sixteen of the forks to sample her beef stew, then threw away 12 defective forks. The guests also brought 2 packs of forks, each having 12 inside them. Later, when she went to set the table, she had a total of 32 forks. How many forks were in the package that Chen bought?

Valentina and Liam went to a construction supply store. Liam is a member, but Valentina is not. Valentina has ¥99.41 and wants to buy 17 screws from a bin at the store. She also needs 9 washers, each costing ¥0.59. Each screw costs ¥0.3. Additionally, Valentina picks up 8 gallons of paint. Liam starts with ¥90 and wants 10 gallons of paint, each priced at ¥8.0, and 3 carpenter pencils, each costing ¥2. The store offers a 10% discount on paint for members. How much more money does Valentina have left than Liam after they leave the store?

A grandfather eats 10 sushi rolls per day, his partner eats 15 sushi rolls per day, and their son eats four-fifths of the combined number of sushi rolls they eat per day. After one month, the family decides to go on a diet in the second month, reducing their food consumption by 20% for the first half of the month, and then by an additional 25% for the second half. How many sushi rolls does this family eat in two months?

A medical center has a capacity of 1300 beds with 1/5 occupied and one-fourth of all the beds being out of service. Due to the major accident, 30 patients are admitted into the medical center each day. Calculate the total number of unoccupied beds in the medical center after 2 weeks.

Prof. Miller sold his apartment for $760000. He paid the registration fees that amounted to 3% of the selling price and also paid a agent fee that is 4% of the selling price. He also paid $570000 for the remaining loan amount on the apartment, and $15000 for closing costs. Prof. Miller used the net proceeds from selling the apartment to invest in stocks. The stocks gained 10% each year for two years. How much were Prof. Miller's net proceeds after two years?

Mrs. Smith is looking for a new house that will not go beyond her $410000 budget. She saw a property that has a selling price of $480000. A building is made out of 4 white bricks, twice as many orange bricks, and an unknown number of purple bricks. If there are 40 bricks in the building in total, what percentage of bricks are purple?

Roya went to the patisserie and bought various types of baked goods. She bought 48 croissants at $19 per dozen, 48 macarons at $31 per dozen, and 24 brownies. After a 25% discount, she paid a total of $1530. What was the cost of brownies per dozen?

Leilani went to her allotment to pick some raspberries and found two-fourths as many ants as wasps in the patch. Leilani then found 40 white animals, half of which were rabbits. In addition, she saw 36 grasshoppers, and 16 wasps. What percentage of animals in the patch were rabbits?

When Xena watches her cousin, she gets out a variety of toys for him. The bag of building blocks has 33 blocks in it. The bin of stuffed animals has 8 stuffed animals inside. The number of action figures in the action figure pack is twice the number of blocks and stuffed animals combined. To make a call from a hotel room phone, you must pay ₺0.6 for each minute of your call. After 10 minutes, the price drops to ₺0.4 per minute. Faisal went to buy some school supplies. He bought 18 pencils which cost ₣6.0 each, 14 rulers which cost ₣14.5 each, and a ream of bond paper which cost ₣24. He also bought 5 colored pencils which cost ₣9 each.
